tickets, [573035,89,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","database creation script improvement suggestion for version 0.1.3",2,"Date: Thu, 22 Oct 2009 15:46:40 +0200\nFrom: Hans Zandbelt <hans.zandbelt@surfnet.nl>\nReply-To: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nTo: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nSubject: [filesender-dev] [feature] version 0.1.3 database creation script\n\nHi,\n\nCan I suggest to drop te \"WITH (OIDS=FALSE)\" clause from the\ntable creation statements?\n\nIt seems to be incompatibile with PostgreSQL 8.1.18 which comes with\nRedhat Enterprise Linux 5.4; above that there's also a \"default_with_oids\"\nconfiguration parameter which sorts it out for newer installations on\na system level.\n\nThis way at least the PostgreSQL version requirement can be narrowed\ndown from \"latest version\" to \">= 8.1.18\".\n\nRegards,\n\nHans.\n\n-- \nHans Zandbelt                    hans.zandbelt@surfnet.nl\nSURFnet                             http://www.surfnet.nl\n\n--- filesender_db.sql.org       2009-10-19 11:43:00.000000000 +0200\n+++ filesender_db.sql   2009-10-22 15:39:16.000000000 +0200\n@@ -18,8 +18,7 @@\n   fileexpirydate timestamp without time zone,\n   fileactivitydate timestamp without time zone,\n   CONSTRAINT files_pkey PRIMARY KEY (fileid)\n-)\n-WITH (OIDS=FALSE);\n+);\n ALTER TABLE files OWNER TO postgres;\n GRANT ALL ON TABLE files TO postgres;\n GRANT ALL ON TABLE files TO public;\n@@ -58,6 +57,5 @@\n   logmessage text,\n   logvoucheruid character varying(60),\n   CONSTRAINT logs_pkey PRIMARY KEY (logid)\n-)\n-WITH (OIDS=FALSE);\n-ALTER TABLE logs OWNER TO postgres;\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+);\n+ALTER TABLE logs OWNER TO postgres;\n\n","2009-10-23T14:17:29.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:18.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-16T02:59:50.000+00:00",0.0,0,-10.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:18.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [573039,90,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","[feature] configurable attribute names",2,"Date: Thu, 22 Oct 2009 15:49:37 +0200\nFrom: Hans Zandbelt <hans.zandbelt@surfnet.nl>\nReply-To: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nTo: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nSubject: [filesender-dev] [feature] configurable attribute names\n\nHi,\n\nI would like the hardcoded attribute names in fs_param.php to be\nconfigurable through config/config.xml since variable names can\ndiffer between different IDPs/federations. Eg. we now have for\nSURFfederatie:\n\n  $username = $session->getAttribute('urn:mace:dir:attribute-def:displayName');\n  $useremail =  $session->getAttribute('urn:mace:dir:attribute-def:mail');\n\ninstead of the default \"short\" names that come in version 0.1.3.\n\nThanks,\n\nHans.\n","2009-10-23T14:19:28.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:18.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-16T04:19:22.000+00:00",0.0,0,-11.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:18.000+00:00",null]
