tickets, [661941,96,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","flash upload over https fails with FireFox",2,"Gears upload works fine, flash upload doesn't over https.  \n\nPreliminary trouble investigation showed this is ONLY an issue for FireFox.  With IE and Safari it works just fine.  Several sources on the web state that supplying the site with a non-selfsigned SSL certificate fixed the issue.  I'll try that and if it works at least there's a workaround.  Still, the software shouldn't mandate someone to buy a server cert.\n","2009-11-23T11:50:00.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:54.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-18T10:38:28.000+00:00",0.0,0,96.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [661995,97,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","flash front end hangs browser when path can't be found in back end",3,"The flash front end hangs the browser (FireFox, Windows) when a path can't be found in the back end.  This shouldn't happen.  Of course it's a bug in the flash front end which shouldn't do that but still.  An easy way to prevent this is to check on start whether the paths that need to exist actually exist and if not, give a reasonable error back to the user.  ","2009-11-23T12:05:15.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:54.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-02-25T04:30:16.000+00:00",0.0,0,97.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [667339,98,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","download notification does not distinguish between users if file uploaded to multiple users",3,"When a file is uploaded to multiple recipients, the backend generates different hash URLs per recipient (which is good) but when a download is completed from one of these distinct URLs, the download notification email does not make a distinction as to which user has downloaded the file. Here as an example is one such notification:\n\n\"The File HPIM0346.JPG has just been downloaded by jan.meijer@uninett.no, guido.aben@aarnet.edu.au.\"\n\nThe same notification was received regardless of whether the file was downloaded from the URL made available to Jan, or the URL made available to Guido (which, I repeat, were different URLs).\n\nThe end user workflow would be greatly improved upon if the notification email would make a disctinction to reveal exactly from what URL the download had been initiated/completed.","2009-11-24T17:39:53.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:54.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ","2010-03-24T02:38:12.000+00:00",0.0,0,98.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [676991,99,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","On download warning to mobile device users [S]",3,"implement device detection so we can warn mobile device users (iPhones, HTCs, Blackberries) that they're about to download a large file and they may rack up a huge bill with their mobile data provider\n\nThe tricky bit is likely in the actual device detection: this is one warning where you do not want false positives.","2009-11-26T00:56:24.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:17:00.000+00:00",114011,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,0.0,0,20.0,0,0,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:17:00.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [707899,100,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","parallelise upload / download",3,"use the existing chunking mechanism provided by the gears plugin to parallelise uploads -- upload multiple chunks simultaneously, using separate http sessions (and consequently tcp streams) so upload on suboptimally tuned machines is improved","2009-12-01T08:52:50.000+00:00","2010-09-22T07:32:29.000+00:00",114011,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,null,0,100.0,0,0,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [713693,101,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","give user error message when email doesn't get sent after succesful upload",2,"If the file is uploaded, stored on disk, entered into the database, but the email doesn't get sent, there is a PHP error that gets reported.  The user currently doesn't get any feedback.  This must change.\n\nProbable solution: make this part of some visible feedback thing to the user that shows *all* steps that need to be taken before the transaction is completed and turns the various steps green (or shows some vertical progress bar in front of them slowly turning green.\n\nlike  <red> enter email address\n       <red> select file\n       <red> file uploaded\n       <red> email sent\n\nwhere the red slowly turns into green as the proces sprogresses. ","2009-12-02T16:42:33.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:54.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-31T10:52:14.000+00:00",0.0,0,101.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
