tickets, [1039817,127,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","How to handle multiple email addresses from user's LDAP entry",3,"This was the original issue posted:\n\n======================================================\nDate: Thu, 25 Feb 2010 12:46:43 +0100\nFrom: Mario Vandaele <>\nTo: filesender-dev\nSubject: [filesender-dev] LDAP authentication and multiple e-mail address entries in\n    \"mail\" attribute\n\nHello,\n\nCurrently I use LDAP authentication/attributes during my tests.\nI use my organisation's ldap server, which contains multiple e-mail address entries for\nmy \"mail\" attribute.\nThe 1st is my office e-mail address, but the others are aliases for distribution lists\nwithin the organisation.\nSo, whenever I successfully log in, the \"From\"-field is already filled in with all\nentries and also stored as such in \"filefrom\" in \"files\" table in db.\nAs a consequence the receiver of the files gets to see these entries as well, but when\nhe successfully downloaded the file, then an e-mail is sent to all e-mail entries\n(=spam,=confidentiality, =major issue).\nSo, my suggestion is to make the \"From\"-field editable, by which I mean that the\nparameter value is parsed and a checklist is created with all found e-mail addresses,\nso you can tick off the ones you do/don't want to use (at least one selected) and then\nstored as such in the db.\n======================================================================\n\nWe had similar issues in the Confusa project.  Users can have multiple email addresses.\n\nOptions the software should have:\n   -take first address\n   -give user option to pick from addresses (display multiple addresses with checkboxes in front) but require at least one address\n\nin both options the From: field would need to be editable.\n\nWe would need a configuration option indicating which of the two the software would use.\n\nhow does that sound?\n","2010-03-03T08:42:47.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:56:48.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-05-01T12:27:58.000+00:00",0.0,0,127.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
