tickets, [1119145,150,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Return Path for non existant email",3,"A valid, but non-existant e-mail address has been entered in the \"To: \" field. \n\n\nHow do you find this out after filesender said: \"Your file has been sent.\"? \n\nNormally an e-mail containing an error message will be sent to the e-mail address in \"Return-Path:\" field. \n\nIn my setup this is by default www-data@belnet.be, i.e. the apache daemon, which is useless, as it should be to the {filefrom} e-mail address. \n\nChanging the value of this parameter ranges from easy to tough depending on the underlying system used. \n\n\nProposal to solve in ../filesender_0.1.9/classes/Mail.php: \n\n\nAfter the \"$headers\"-section, add the line: $returnpath = \"-r\".$mailobject['filefrom'].\"\\n\"; \n\n\nChange line 49: if (mail($to, $subject, $body, $headers)) { \n\nTo: if (mail($to, $subject, $body, $headers, $returnpath)) { \n\n\nWith this change the sender will always get the e-mail with the error message (if there is one) \n\n","2010-03-22T12:44:32.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",345073,null,"","2010-03-24T02:34:56.000+00:00",0.0,0,-22.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [1119169,151,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","re-send a file without re-uploading ",3,"Solution 2: The normal user has the tab \"Files Available\" as per\n     Admin in which he can select the respective file, press a button\n     \"resend\" and fill in the correct e-mail adddress in the \"To:\"\n     field, (optional) subject & (optional) message.\n\n     Note: This is linked to feature request to provide the normal user\n     with tabs like the Admin has, but then restricted to his files &\n     vouchers, plus the appropriate buttons 5.\n\n     _*Feature*_: Administrative tabs for normal user\n\n         o\n\n           A tab \"Uploads\" as per Admin:\n\n         o\n\n           A tab \"Downloads\" as per Admin;\n\n         o\n\n           A tab \"Errors\" as per Admin;\n\n         o\n\n           A tab \"Files Available\" as per Admin:\n\n               +\n\n                 a \"resend\" button to resend notification e-mail with\n                 \"To:\",\"Subject:\",\"Message\" to be filled;\n\n               +\n\n                 a \"delete\" button to send notification e-mail to all\n                 listed receivers and \"Subject:\",\"Message\" to be filled\n                 in;\n\n\n","2010-03-22T12:48:31.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-24T11:30:04.000+00:00",0.0,0,-23.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [1119207,152,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","include voucher issuer on recipient list of file ",3,"When a person uses a voucher to upload a file, the voucher issuer will be included by default on the recipient list of that file. ","2010-03-22T12:57:49.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-04-16T01:25:30.000+00:00",0.0,0,-24.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [1119215,153,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","more control for voucher issuer",3,"A voucher issuer needs to be able to execute control over files uploaded using that voucher.  So preferably everything that a file uploader can do normally (delete, change recipients etc.) that voucher issuer should also be able to do.   Underlying assumption is that the voucher issuer is responsible for what the voucher user does.","2010-03-22T12:59:43.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-28T22:10:54.000+00:00",0.0,0,-25.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:19.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [1119427,154,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","use cronjob for clean up ",3,"At the moment a clean up process runs whenever *a* user logs in.  To improve robustness and scalability the clean up process needs to be moved to a cronjob-like solution.","2010-03-22T13:34:08.000+00:00","2010-09-08T23:23:30.000+00:00",114623,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-09-08T23:23:30.000+00:00",0.0,0,154.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1119545,155,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","remove deprecated config file directives from default config file",3,"check the administrator manual to see which ones ;)\n\nhttp://www.assembla.com/spaces/file_sender/wiki?id=file_sender&wiki_id=Administrator_reference_manual","2010-03-22T13:44:18.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:20.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-22T23:35:16.000+00:00",0.0,0,-26.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:20.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [1119607,156,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Overhaul log mechanism",3,"Logging is done at two places at the moment.  Logging goes into log files and logging goes into a database.  I would say that both are needed.  Logging to log files makes it easy for a sysadmin to investigate faults in the service.  Logging to the database means that a service manager can easily generate custom reports and stats without bothering the sysadmin.  But, this needs a thorough rethink for 2.0 so we have some solid and consistent thinking behind our logging mechanism: clear goals for what needs to be achieved that will lead to a clear implementation of logging and loglevels as well as what is logged where (when).","2010-03-22T13:49:03.000+00:00","2010-11-12T07:35:43.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,0.0,0,156.0,0,0,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1119757,157,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","available space depleted warning",3,"Create a trigger to the FileSender admin when the available space is down to so many% of the total'.  Requires a config file directive 'notEnoughSpaceLeftPercentage'.  Note though: how would the admin be warned?  Presumably email?\n\n==\nYou'd make us at AARNet immensely happy if you'd write it as a Nagios plugin.\nhttp://nagios.sourceforge.net/docs/3_0/pluginapi.html\n\nGuido\n==","2010-03-22T14:14:06.000+00:00","2015-11-11T10:46:20.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-03-25T23:21:17.000+00:00",0.0,0,-27.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-11T10:46:20.000+00:00",null]
