tickets, [1216293,160,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","email address unsuitable as GUID",3,"We use the email address as the GUID.  That means that if you can get your CEOs email address\nin your IdP entry, you have full access to his files on FileSender.\n\nUp until now that didn't matter because well, you could see what files he had there.  Then we added\nthe capability to delete.  Still didn't matter, but opened for DoS.  But from beta-1.10, you can\nadd new recipients to existing uploads.  And then it matters.  Inadvertent data disclosure sucks.\n\nWe're thinking it should be solvable by not using email address but ePPN and/or\neduPersonTargetedId.\n\nAfter some discussion probably what needs to be done is:\n-add GUID=eduPersontargetedId attribute mapping to config file\n-use this GUID as the GUID in the app throughout\n\nNote: we really should think of a way to still be able to use OpenId as well?","2010-04-06T13:44:37.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:08.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-04-16T08:07:00.000+00:00",0.0,0,160.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
