tickets, [1230873,162,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","improve feedback when log directory is missing",3,"When the log directory is missing, or can't be written to, the flash application loads but doesn't display a login button or the splash text.  It's fairly easy to debug *once you look in the PHP logging*.  Even then, the error reported there requires you to either understand what's going on or dive in the code to figure out exactly which file/directory is missing.  That can be done better.\n\nIt would be really good if the FileSender app has a better sanity check when starting up, and actually reports back.  In the case of a missing log directory, I guess the sane thing to do is to report this through the UI.  So giving some sane feedback where an admin can read it.\n\nThinking a bit more.  Usually you want all error logging to go to the error log.  There are two things in particular that can not be logged to the error log.\n\n1. config file parsing error\n2. logfile not writable\n\nThese two circumstances should simply be reported through the UI?","2010-04-08T11:32:35.000+00:00","2010-10-26T02:04:10.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-10-26T02:04:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,162.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1230977,163,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","add 'back to home page' button in logged out page",3,"When you log out you now get 'logout complete'.  If a user logged out by mistake, it's a bit unpractical to relogin.  One solution is to add a link 'back to home' that points back to the opening window.  Another solution is to add a login link to the logout page.\n\nThe 'File downloaded' page should maybe have the same or possibly an addition like\n\n'file downloaded\n\nyou can now safely close this page'\n","2010-04-08T12:01:33.000+00:00","2011-09-22T03:51:00.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2011-01-29T11:24:17.000+00:00",0.0,0,163.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
