tickets, [1297515,169,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","language quirks in MyFiles re-send email process",3,"a) in the \"My FIles\" menu, it is possible to resend the original download link email (leftmost button). The mouseover hint correctly reads \"Re-Send Email\". When clicked, however, the popup reads \"are you sure you want to re-send this voucher\" (which should have read \"email\" instead of \"voucher\". When the \"OK\" option is chosen, a popup appears that reads \"Voucher has been sent\". That, too, should read \"email\" instead of \"voucher\". Finally, when the resulting email comes in, it reads\n\n\"Dear Sir, Madam,\nPlease, find below a voucher which grants access to FileSender.\nWith this voucher you can upload once one file and make it available for download to a group of people.\"\n\nbut the link contained in the email is very well a download link, not a voucher link.","2010-04-19T11:22:45.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:55.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ","2010-05-02T11:08:22.000+00:00",0.0,0,169.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
