tickets, [1331627,174,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","size calculation wrong for larger files",3,"It seems that when doing a Gears upload something goes wrong in the file size calculation.\n\nFiles over approximately 4 GB get the wrong size.  Up to 3.96 GB it goes just fine, a 4GB file is reported to be 64.47 MB.  A 16GB file is reported as 3.35 GB.  This might have an impact on the upload.    It at the least confuses users.\n\nAddendum: this looks to be an issue in the Flash UI.  I see the same miscalculation in the 'uploaded file size' of the Uploaded Files tab in the Admin interface.","2010-04-22T14:40:08.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:09.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-05-02T10:30:56.000+00:00",0.0,0,174.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1331779,175,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","saml_uid_attribute parsing code not 100%",3,"In filesender/classes/AuthSaml.php, line 61.\n\nIt reads:\n\n  if(stristr($config['admin'],\n$attributes[$config['saml_uid_attribute']]) === FALSE) {\n\nIt should read:\n\n  if(stristr($config['admin'], $attributes[\"eduPersonTargetedID\"]) ===\nFALSE) {\n\nBased on the test logic further up in the function. I suspect the test\n\"if(isset($attributes[$config['saml_uid_attribute']][0])) {\" above it at\nline 57 needs to be fixed to properly accommodate the scenario where if\nwe're not setting the uid attribute in the config (say we're not using\nEPTID). \n\nIt may accidentally work, but the types are wrong, for in our case the\nsaml_uid_attribute is coming back as an array, and stristr will take an\ninteger or a string, but not an array.\n","2010-04-22T15:05:30.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:09.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-05-02T11:11:52.000+00:00",0.0,0,175.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1335595,176,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb",">2Gb upload on MacOS hangs at ~2Gb (Gears enabled)",1,"MacOSX clients (tested for MacOSX 10.6 and 10.5) that attempt to upload files >2Gb to a FileSender 0.1.12 instalaltion will hang at ~2Gb, even though Gears is enabled. A screenshot of a typical hang is attached; notice that it is stalled at block 2147400000, which corresponds to 1.9999220967 GB.","2010-04-23T08:24:15.000+00:00","2014-10-21T22:19:46.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2013-09-10T13:01:08.000+00:00",0.0,0,176.0,0,0,3316353,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-09-10T13:01:08.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [1335935,177,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","unexpected voucher behaviour when voucher user is already logged in",2,"If a user is already logged in to filesender, clicking on a voucher link in an email takes the user to the standard Upload page, not a voucher upload page, with the user's logged in email address in the from: field (which can be different to the voucher recipient email address for that user! Users can have one email address associated with their account, and another email address they use casually), with the user's login name at the top of the page but no logoff button diplayed.\n\nFrom then on the file uploaded gets treated like a new file, not a voucher file, hence the file gets listed in the MyFiles table, and the voucher does not get deleted after use.\n\nContrast this with previous filesender behaviour, where filesender did not \"recognise\" a voucher user even if already logged in.","2010-04-23T09:42:53.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:09.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ","2010-05-02T11:16:35.000+00:00",0.0,0,177.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1335945,178,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","security bug: back button on download menu",1,"if one explicitly logs out after downloading a file but leaves the browser open. clicking on the back button in the browser brings the user (or a third party!) back to the download page logged in as Guest. It is then possible to download the file again -- disastrous for anyone using a public machine, such as those supplied for use by delegates at conferences or in university libraries.","2010-04-23T09:45:46.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:09.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ","2010-05-02T11:08:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,178.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1335963,179,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","security: log-off behaviour across multiple browser tabs incorrect",1,"if a user is logged in and has filesender open in two browser tabs, and the user then logs off in one of the two browser tabs, the “New Upload” page on that logged-off browser tab remains active. This is a security risk on public machines such as available in university libraries. The Vouchers and MyFiles pages in that logged-off tab however do correctly display: “There has been an error loading voucher data. Please check Log File. notAuthenticated”\n\n(arguably, \"voucher data” isn't correct for the MyFiles page, but that is cosmetics, not security).","2010-04-23T09:49:57.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:09.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ","2010-05-02T11:10:21.000+00:00",0.0,0,179.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1355573,180,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","sender email address gets truncated beyond 3rd domain level",3,"as witnessed on the 0.1.13 early deployment at apps.vetvirtual.org on 28/4/'10, when filesender sends out a notification email for an uploaded file as uploaded by user@example.organisation.edu.au, the \"From\" address got truncated and is now missing the \".au\" ccTLD part (although the \"Reply-To\" and \"To\" addresses are complete).\n\n\n-------- Original Message --------\nSubject:  FileSender: TestUpload \nDate:  Wed, 28 Apr 2010 18:37:11 +1000 \nFrom:  user@example.organisation.edu \nReply-To:  user@example.organisation.edu.au \nTo:  another.user@example.organisation.edu.au, user@example.organisation.edu.au \n\n\n","2010-04-28T09:13:00.000+00:00","2013-09-05T05:18:23.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ","2010-08-02T09:44:32.000+00:00",0.0,0,180.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1364121,181,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Arrange download(s).filesender.org",3,"We publish our downloadable release tarballs in the Assembla file store.  Assembla does not offer us any way to see how often files get downloaded or by which IP address.  We would like to have that information to get some idea on how popular the software is and where's it in use.\n\nTo solve this we'll arrange for a separate webserver 'download.filesender.org'.  It'll only serve up the tarballs.\n\nreachable by:\n\ndownload.filesender.org\ndownloads.filesender.org\n\npointing to same DocumentRoot.  \n\nDoing both HTTP and HTTPS.\n\nChris, myself, Guido and others (possibly) involved in release process can upload files.\n\nSite will have a weblog analysis tool shielded by .htaccess so we can see what's going on.  ","2010-04-29T12:45:00.000+00:00","2011-01-28T16:38:29.000+00:00",213323,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2011-01-28T16:38:29.000+00:00",0.0,0,181.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
