tickets, [1600083,211,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","MyFiles -> Add Recipient: download link in resulting file voucher does not work",3,"If you do this:\n\n-upload a file\n-go to 'my files'\n-with 'add recipient' add a recipient, say \"John\"\n\nJohn receives the email with the download link.  Clicks on the link, and the download does not work.  No feedback in the client as to why not.\n\nThe Apache error log shows what's going on:\n[Thu Jun 17 16:30:59 2010] [error] [client 158.38.62.126] File does not exist: /var/www/filesender/www/files/null0148.JPG\n\nSo it looks like the resulting file pointer is screwed up when adding a new recipient.\n\nThe bug is actually two issues:\n1. the fact that the file is not downloadable\n2. the missing error message to the user about the server side error.\n","2010-06-17T14:36:05.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:11.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-08-02T09:45:21.000+00:00",0.0,0,211.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
