tickets, [1634289,238,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","minor problems with the DoneLoading kludge",4," js/fs_gears.js contains the following snippet:\nfunction DoneLoading() {\nif(jQuery.browser.mozilla) {\n    var img = new Image();\n    img.src = 'http://example.com/any_small_image_use_on_web_page.gif';\n}\n}\n\nTwo minor problems:\n\n1) this gives a http-request that results in a 404 not found to an *unrelated* existing website\n2) when filesender is served over https it leads to a 'partially encrypted page' warning\n\nI tried to replace the image link with something like 'assets/true.png' but that breaks the intended purpose of the function :(","2010-06-25T12:15:52.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:12.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2010-08-12T05:44:26.000+00:00",0.0,0,238.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1638721,239,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","expiry logic: selecting 'today' should be disabled?",3,"It is possible to select the current day as 'expiry date'. This results in almost immediate removal/expiry of the file and the recipient gets \"This file/voucher is no longer available\". Suggestion: make 'tomorrow' the first possible expiry date.","2010-06-26T19:26:21.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:56.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2010-07-08T23:48:44.000+00:00",0.0,0,239.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1638723,240,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","expiry logic: with multiple recipients the shortest expiry wins",3,"With MyFiles: Add Recipient it is possible to give a different expiry date for the new recipient(s) of the file. However if this new expiry date is shorter than the expiry dates of the other recipients the expiry process in the back-end will expire/remove all files, even if the expiry date of those other files hasn't been reached yet.","2010-06-26T19:32:02.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:56.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2010-08-02T11:45:53.000+00:00",0.0,0,240.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
