tickets, [1798333,258,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","plus sign in filename causes upload error",3,"a plus sign in the name of the file to be uploaded causes the file upload to error out at 99% with the \"The file cannot be moved\" message. Removing the plus sign from the file name and subsequentially uploading it is successful.\n\nFirst spotted on a file named \"Linux+ Certification Study Guide.zip\"","2010-07-23T06:29:43.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:13.000+00:00",345073,null,"bcgVDMwiSr3AYAab7jnrAJ","2010-08-02T12:26:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,258.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
