tickets, [1852845,265,"b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","project files case",3," I don't know what is usual with PHP ( I can't find a good programming style guide), but I would argue it is better to only use lower case filenames. www/* is lowercase only while classes/* and includes/* is a sort of hybrid camelcase notation.\n\nAlso I think flex/src/FileSender2.mxml should be renamed to /flex/src/filesender.mxml and the flex source should compile to www/swf/filesender.swf","2010-08-05T13:05:30.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:14.000+00:00",345073,null,"b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-10-05T00:44:03.000+00:00",0.0,0,265.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1852855,266,"b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Project tarball naming",3,"The tarball should be named filesender-<version>, not filesender_<version>. There is no ISO standard for this kind of things, but it is more common to do it this way. Also, debian is more happy with a <project>-<version>.tar.gz file","2010-08-05T13:07:30.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:14.000+00:00",345073,null,"b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-10-05T00:47:15.000+00:00",0.0,0,266.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [1857197,267,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Voucher issue email incorrectly uses file upload email template",3,"It looks like the File / Voucher Upload email template is being incorrectly used for the email body when a Voucher is issued. The email subject seems to be correct though. When a voucher is issued, the email body now contains the following introductory text and table headers:\n\n\"The file below has been uploaded to AARNet cloudstor by email.address@domain.com and you have been granted permission to download this file.\"\nTable with headings \"Filename\" (blank content below), \"Filesize\" (0), \"Download link\" (link to voucher), \"Valid until\" (voucher expiry date)\nTable with heading \"Personal message from email.address@domain.com (optional):\" (blank content below)\n\nwhen it previously contained:\n\n\"Please, find below a voucher which grants access to AARNet cloudstor. With this voucher you can upload once one file and make it available for download to a group of people.\"\nTable with headings \"Issuer\" (issuer email address), \"Voucher link\" (link to voucher), \"Valid until\" (voucher expiry date)","2010-08-06T08:32:32.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:14.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-08-12T05:47:59.000+00:00",0.0,0,267.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
