tickets, [2155183,290,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","File select fails in Linux/Gears for files of 2G or more",3,"Reported by Nikola Garafolic and confirmed by X. When doing a New Upload on Linux (tested on Ubuntu 10.04.1 with FF 3.6.10 and xul-ext-gears package) files larger than or equal to 2GB (base 1024) can be selected in the 'browse' window but aren't picked up in the interface (i.e., no file is listed as ready to be uploaded). Tested against 0.1.15 and svn r209 (and later).","2010-09-24T12:03:30.000+00:00","2013-09-10T12:25:10.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2013-09-10T12:25:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,290.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-09-10T12:25:10.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2164309,291,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Gears cancel - needs to complete last chunk before allowing a new upload",3,"I did note however a 'shoot in the foot' thing when canceling the upload (which was also there before the tmpfile changes I guess) and is most noticable when using larger chunksizes (i.e. 10MB as on my testbox).\n\nWhen I cancel an upload the UI tells me 'Cancelled upload but in the background Gears is still uploading the last started chunk. With a slow uplink and large chunk sizes that can take a while. On the server this last chunk (still in transit) is not yet appended to the tmpfile so when I resume the upload while gears is still uploading the chunk from the previous attempt that could lead to chunks being sent and appended twice.\n\nThe scenario would be in that case that while the previous chunk is still in transit Flex asks for the already uploaded filesize *before* the chunk in transit is appended to the tmpfile on the server. That chunk will thus be sent again but since the one still in transit is also appended to the tmpfile the file on the server will get the chunk twice.\n\nWould it be possible to have the 'Cancel upload' function either wait for Gears to actually finish the chunk being uploaded or have Flex somehow 'kill' the Gears-upload ?\n\nFrom Beta 1.15","2010-09-27T02:12:25.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:56.000+00:00",345073,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-10-21T23:01:43.000+00:00",0.0,0,291.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
