tickets, [2170301,298,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Download fails after changeset 231?",2,"In svn r238 (running on https://filesender.surfnet.nl/latest/ ) downloads are broken. Only 1 MB (of much larger files) is actually downloaded and on the server I get:\n\napache2[16686]: Error: [8] ob_flush() [<a href='ref.outcontrol'>ref.outcontrol</a>]: failed to flush buffer. No buffer to flush. : /var/www/filesender-0.1.16.201009271721/www/download.php [91] \n\nThis looks like it was introduced with changeset 231 (I replaced ErrorHandler.php with the previous one and after that downloads were OK again). Haven't pinpointed the actual cause though.","2010-09-27T21:23:11.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:01:56.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-09-27T23:14:38.000+00:00",0.0,0,298.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
