tickets, [2345897,313,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Warn Mac users about files > 2GB",3,"I talked with Jan about the 2GB limit on Mac OS (#176). It would be nice if we could give Mac users a warning/popup that it currently isn't possible to upload files > 2GB, even with gears. There are basically two situations to consider:\n\n1) User does NOT have gears installed and tries to upload a >2GB file: current hint is to install Gears, on a Mac that doesn't help so it should be something like \"File is too large, it is currently not possible to upload very larges files from a Mac.\"\n\n2) User has gears installed and tries to upload a >2GB file: currently the upload starts but hangs at 2GB, should also be something like \"File is too large, it is currently not possible to upload very larges files from a Mac.\"\n\n","2010-10-23T10:23:34.000+00:00","2011-10-26T07:02:51.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-11-10T23:44:28.000+00:00",0.0,0,313.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
