tickets, [2389315,320,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","PHP session timeout with large (long) flash uploads",3,"When a Flash upload (no gears) takes a long time (for example from a residential ADSL link) the upload can take longer than the PHP session expiry timer (default on debian is 1440 seconds is 24 minutes). During the upload the session-cache file is removed on the server but the upload continues (it started when the session was still valid). After the upload processing the file fails due to the expired session. Also cancelling the upload after the session has expired on the server gives an error:\n\nError: [256] Invalid session supplied. : /var/www/filesender-0.1.17.201010290059/www/fs_uploadit.php [47] \n\nWe could configure a higher value for the session.gc_maxlifetime setting but there are good reasons to keep that value low. Another solution could be to to send some kind of 'keepalive' every now and then from the client to the server during the upload to keep the session 'active'. Note that setting client_specific_logging to true will keep the session active on the server so something similar but less verbose  would probably work.","2010-10-30T11:07:18.000+00:00","2014-10-21T22:19:55.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2010-11-04T17:43:47.000+00:00",0.0,0,320.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2463617,321,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","UTF 8 charachters in name deleted by CRON",3,"On 25.10.2010. 8:55, Nikola Garafolic wrote:\n> How can file get status \"Closed\" other than user deleting it or \n> reaching expiry date?\n> I have some files that have not expired, and users swear they did not \n> delete them, but are in \"Closed\" status, and physically not present \n> inside filesender files directory. I am refering to version 1.16.1.\n\nI believe we found the reason for this behavior.\n\nIn case when filename contains UTF-8 characters field \"fileoriginalname\" \nin the database will be different from the name of file stored on the disc. Because of the discrepancy function cleanUp in cron.php will assume that the file was removed and it will put the file status to Closed. This will be performed in the last loop (\"// close all entries that do not have a pyhsical file in storage\"). File will not be removed immediately but at the next cron.php run (loop \"// Loop through the files\").\n\nThe reason for discrepancy is the following. Field \"fileoriginalname\" \ncomes from the JSON feed sent by Flash and the actual name comes from the _FILES variable. In case of JSON feed UTF-8 chars will be changed to \\uxxxx equivalents by the json_encode. In case of _FILES variable they will simply be turned to \"_\" by the sanitizeFilename function.\n\nI attached a patch for fs_uploadit.php which turns UTF-8 name from _FILES variable to JSON feed equivalent.\n\nCheers,\nemir","2010-10-31T00:17:22.000+00:00","2016-12-12T19:43:49.000+00:00",345073,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-11-17T23:56:50.000+00:00",0.0,0,321.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2463687,322,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Max Upload Size consistency",3,"Some notes about the actual flash upload limits, independent of the exclamation mark problem but relevant to testing filesizes around 2000M.\n\nUpload of 2000M (base 1024) file of 2097152000 bytes, upload from a Win7 box with Opera, no gears\n\nAt the start of the upload I get on the server:\n\nOct 29 12:43:33 apache2[11765]: PHP Warning: POST Content-Length of 2097152672 bytes exceeds the limit of 2097152000 bytes in Unknown on line 0\n\nsimplesamlphp[11765]: Error: [8] Undefined index: Filedata : /usr/share/filesender/www/fs_uploadit.php [62]\napache2[11765]: Error: [8] Undefined index: fid : /usr/share/filesender/www/fs_uploadit.php [62]\napache2[11765]: Error: [8] Undefined index: Filedata : /usr/share/filesender/www/fs_uploadit.php [62]\n\nAfter upload the client gets a 'Can not move file' error. It looks like there is no 'tmp' file created on the server. Also note that the Content-Length is 672 bytes larger than the actual filesize of 2097152000. It would be good to catch this error at the start of the upload so users don't have to wait a possibly long time to see that the upload failed.\n\nThe advertised limit is 2000M (the post_max_size=2000M limit in PHP.ini):\n; Maximum size of POST data that PHP will accept.\npost_max_size = 2000M\n\nSetting post_max_size=2001 (and a restart of apache!) makes it possible to upload a 2000M file. This should be in the installation notes (setting post_max_size a little bit larger than the upload_max_filesize to allow for extra header info which is included in the POST Content-Length.\n\nAs for the maximum filesize with Flash there are two other relevant variables:\n\nIn php.ini:\n\n; Maximum allowed size for uploaded files.\nupload_max_filesize = 2000M\ni\nand in the filesender config.php:\n\n$config['max_flash_upload_size'] = '2147483648'; // 2GB\n\nThese should match (but don't in the default config) so the user will be warned when uploading more than the the minimum of the two settings. We could explain this in the installation notes or perhaps it is possible to add a check on the (three!) relevant variables and only allow uploads that are less than or equal to the minimum of the three settings (taking into account that the post_max_size should allow for some extra bytes, say a few K).\n\nEither way, the current defaults and installation notes are not consistent and will give problems with flash uploads around and above the 2000M (base 1024). ","2010-10-31T00:23:22.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:03:05.000+00:00",345073,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2010-10-31T12:58:42.000+00:00",0.0,0,322.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2482147,323,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Compatibility Mode is required for current version when compiling",3,"In testing we found some browsers will not completely load the flash file.\n\nWith compatibility mode 3 ON it works correctly.\n\n-compatibility-version=3.0\n\nLove flash!!!!!!","2010-11-03T04:39:21.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:03:05.000+00:00",345073,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2010-11-17T23:58:55.000+00:00",0.0,0,323.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2489893,324,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Notification for user and log if file data is missing when sent to php from flex ",3,"On occasions flex is not sending the file data to php.\nUpdate to notify error to user and log error.","2010-11-04T06:36:18.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:03:05.000+00:00",345073,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-11-04T06:37:40.000+00:00",0.0,0,324.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2496643,325,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","UTF-8 in message/subject/selected file field triggers failure after file upload",3,"Symptoms:\n\n-user uploads file\n-user gets \"Your file has been sent\"\n-file is written on disk at server side\n-empty database object is put in database\n-user does NOT receive any emails\n-file does NOT appear in MyFiles\n-the Administrator view shows an empty line\n\nFrom a user's point of view the upload failed silently.  \n\nIt turns out we can reproduce this bug by putting UTF8 characters (øæå etc.) in at least the message field.  \n\nWe need to test the various cases where people could use non-ASCII characters:\n\n- selected filename\n- message subject\n- message text\n\nand those for both flash and gears upload *and* subsequent download (the download of a gears uploaded file currently fails with invalid voucher).\n\nAs part of the bug fix we need to implement a check that lets a \"bad\" or \"empty\" database insert fail loudly so that we can give the user a \"hard error\".\n","2010-11-05T07:01:54.000+00:00","2011-10-26T08:04:18.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2010-12-08T00:38:53.000+00:00",0.0,0,325.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2502095,326,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Download fails with IE7/8 over https (since changeset 251)",3,"Since revision 251 http://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/changesets/251#ch2 downloading a file with IE7 (tested on Win XP) or IE8 (tested on two separate instances of Win7) fails. See the attached image for the specific error.  This error only occurs when downloading over SSL (https), not with http. Tested against apps3 and latest svn on two separate boxes @ surfnet. Commenting out the change in r251 does seem to fix it. \n\nOn a side note: although the download fails at the client side the server still sends a mail that the file actually is downloaded.","2010-11-05T23:05:05.000+00:00","2014-10-21T22:19:56.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-03T02:05:13.000+00:00",0.0,0,326.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2503321,327,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Message box in Admin UI messes up 'Available files' listing",3,"When a user adds a large personal message to a file this message is also shown in the Admin UI (under Files Available) in a rather large table cell. All other listed files have the height of that cell (even when they don't have a personal message) and it looks like not all available files are shown. Note that this somehow doesn't happen always, ie, it looks like the first listed file is the one to determine the height of the table rows.  Perhaps the way it is done in the 'My files' UI for non-administrators (with the small envelope) can be implemented also in the admin UI.\n\nAdditional note from Jan: the message column in the  Upload and Download admin-tabs is empty. It would be great if the \"Message\" could also be shown there, in the same way as it is now implemented in the MyFiles (small envelope) interface\n\nAdditional note from Jan: Currently the date fields in the admin interface (all tabs) display the date.  It would be great if all date fields in the Admin interface could be date/time and also display the exact *time* when something happened.","2010-11-06T17:00:57.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:16.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-11-10T21:39:23.000+00:00",0.0,0,327.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
