tickets, [2545529,333,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Formatting of personal message in outgoing mails",3,"The optional personal message is wrapped at 70 characters and not 'flowed'. This has been mentioned by Wendy. \n\nThe cause is using < pre > delimiters in the HTML part of the mai ltemplates in combination with wordwrap(70) in Mail.php. \n\nI'm currently testing patches for config.php (templates only)  and Mail.php that make the personal message appear as 'flowed' text in the HTML mail message.","2010-11-12T22:03:01.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:03:06.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-11-18T06:26:03.000+00:00",0.0,0,333.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2549795,334,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Logon description modifications",3,"The new logon text (for 0.1.16) currently says: \"FileSender is a secure way to share large files with anyone! Log-in to upload your files or invite people to send you a file.\" I suggest that the new text on the logon page be changed to say \"Logon\" instead of \"Log-in\", to match the Logon button. Also, note that the word \"secure\" only applies if the site takes the advice of making the instalaltion accessible only via https. \n\nThe old text, which is still appearing on apps3, has a hyperlink embedded in the text \"FileSender\", which points to http://filesender.org (which doesn't work) instead of http://www.filesender.org. Also, I assume that not all the authentication options would need to be listed for a local installation. Note comment above about use of \"securely\".","2010-11-15T02:39:23.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:16.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-11-15T11:33:53.000+00:00",0.0,0,334.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2550357,335,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Populate \"About\" page",3,"Suggested text: \"FileSender is an installation of FileSender (www.filesender.org), which is developed to the requirements of the higher education and research community\". Local sysadmins should replace the first instance of FileSender with the local installation's name.","2010-11-15T07:49:51.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:13:55.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-16T00:07:06.000+00:00",0.0,0,-79.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:13:55.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2550407,336,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Populate \"Help\" page",3,"Suggested text (combined effort between Wendy and Guido), configuration variables in brackets to be automatically inserted during configuration from config/config.php. If there are maximums for the number of characters in the email subject and message fields (with or without white spaces), these should be added too.\n\n*Login issues:* If you don’t see your institution in the list of Identity Providers (IdPs), or your institutional login fails, please contact your local IT support.\n*Maximum recipient addresses per email:* 100 [config/config.php: $config[\"max_email_recipients\"] = 100;]; multiple email addresses can be separated by a comma [???]\n*Maximum number of files per upload:* one - to upload several files at once, zip them into a single archive first\n*Maximum file size per upload, without Gears:* 2 GB [$config['max_flash_upload_size'] = '2147483648'; // 2GB]\n*Maximum file size per upload, with Gears:* 100 GB [$config['max_gears_upload_size'] = '100000000000'; // 100 GB] (file uploads over 2 GB currently not possible on Mac OSX 10.6.x)\n*Maximum file / voucher expiry days:* 20 [$config['default_daysvalid'] = 20;]\n\n","2010-11-15T08:03:51.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:13:55.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-16T00:06:56.000+00:00",0.0,0,-80.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:13:55.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2593871,337,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","[cleanup] Pointers to \"history/history.css\"",3,"The following files have stale pointers to history/history.css:\n\nwww/help.php:<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"history/history.css\" />\nwww/about.php:<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"history/history.css\" />\nwww/invalidvoucher.php:<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"history/history.css\" />\nwww/vouchererror.php:<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"history/history.css\" />\n\nCan these be removed or should they be changed to point to \"lib/history/history.css\" ? (see also #111)","2010-11-21T11:43:51.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:13:55.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-01T12:05:45.000+00:00",0.0,0,-81.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:13:55.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2593917,338,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","download blocks other filesender operations in the same session/browser",3,"When using 'session_start()' (r372/r251) in download.php a user can only download *one* file at a time with the same browser. This is probably because PHP only allows one script active at a time on a session. This can be an issue when a user downloads a large file taking a long time and also wants to download other files (with the same browser). \n\nThis also affects other filesender operations, for example when a user is downloading a large file he/she cannot login or do other authenticated actions because the download script is 'blocking' the session.\n\nHow to repeat: start a download of a large file taking a long time. Then try (while the file is downloading) with the same browser to do other actions with filesender (on the same server). They will give you blank screens *until* the download is finished or cancelled.\n\nA solution might be to have download.php to have its own 'session id' for each download. Not sure about the possibilities and/or implications though :(\n\n","2010-11-21T12:48:17.000+00:00","2014-06-25T16:25:59.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2014-06-25T16:25:59.000+00:00",0.0,0,338.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-06-25T16:25:59.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2632043,339,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Prompt when clicking on link to deleted file uses voucher cancellation text",3,"When I click on a link to a file that has been deleted, the window reads \"This voucher has been cancelled\" when it should be referring to a file having been deleted or cancelled.","2010-11-29T08:24:12.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:16.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-03T02:20:44.000+00:00",0.0,0,339.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2653361,340,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","email address validation in flex",3,"Date: Tue, 30 Nov 2010 12:38:54 +0100\nFrom: Nikola Garafolic <nikola.garafolic@srce.hr>\nReply-To: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nTo: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nSubject: [filesender-dev] email validation in flex\n\nHi,\n\nIs is possible to implement some sort of email address validation? Users input all kind of bad\nemail address syntax like:\n\n'my.email@domain.com'\n\"my.email@domain.com\"\nname surname <my.email@domain.com>\n<my.email@domain.com>\n\nFilesender expects email address in the my.email@domain.com form, so all of the above are\nundeliverable email addresses.\n\nSome sort of regex check like this should be enough:\n\n\\b[A-Z0-9._%-]+@[A-Z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Z]{2,4}\\b\n\nRegards,\nNikola\n","2010-12-01T14:42:37.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:03:06.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-16T00:09:44.000+00:00",0.0,0,340.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2653389,341,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document reasoning for having ePTID as default GUID",3,"Grounds: this discussion on the list.  There were some reasons to use ePTID that ought to be properly documented.\n\nDate: Tue, 23 Nov 2010 12:25:52 +0100\nFrom: Guido Aben <Guido.Aben@aarnet.edu.au>\nReply-To: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nTo: filesender-dev@filesender.org\nCc: filesender-dev@filesender.org, epires@fccn.pt, nuno@fccn.pt\nSubject: Re: [filesender-dev] filesender - eduPersonTargetedID attribute\n\nYou can very well operate without ePTID. AARNet runs its filesender install without it. We\nsimply translate the attribute and replace it with the email attribute -- sufficiently\npseudopermanent for our purposes.\n\nGuido\n","2010-12-01T14:48:04.000+00:00","2016-02-26T13:04:37.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,-1.0,0,0,133342,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T13:04:37.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2664257,342,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","download.php often downloads when downloading file from MyFiles table",3,"When I download a file from the MyFiles table, download.php often downloads (I think in addition to the actual file). This doesn't occur every time, but is independent of whether I elect to open or just save the file (in the case of a text file). When electing to open the file upon downlaod, Firefox then prompts me \"'download.php' is a script application downloaded from the internet. Are you sure you want to open it?\". Download.php does NOT download when downloading a file from the link contained in an email. Mac OSX 10.6.5, Firefox 3.6.12, Flash 10.1.102.64.","2010-12-02T07:19:22.000+00:00","2013-09-10T12:27:24.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2013-09-10T12:27:24.000+00:00",0.0,0,342.0,0,0,342706,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-09-10T12:27:24.000+00:00",null]
