tickets, [2672783,347,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Raw html sometimes displayed in browser when clicking on link in email to download file",3,"A few times, when clicking on a link in an email to download an uploaded file using AARNet's Cloudstor 0.1.17 (https://cloudstor.aarnet.edu.au/), I've got the raw html in my browser tab. Refreshing brings up the webpage. Clicking on the link again generally brings up the webpage, not the eaw html, although on one occassion the raw html came up again. One time this happened I thought to read the html (!) and noticed this at the top:\n<pre><code>\n<b>Warning</b>:  session_start() [<a href='function.session-start'>function.session-start</a>]: Cannot send session cache limiter - headers already sent (output started at /srv/www/cloudstor.aarnet.edu.au/filesender-svn/www/download.php:126) in <b>/srv/www/cloudstor.aarnet.edu.au/simplesaml/lib/SimpleSAML/SessionHandlerPHP.php</b> on line <b>58</b><br />\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\n</code></pre>\n","2010-12-03T11:13:06.000+00:00","2011-01-29T11:54:17.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-07T23:48:24.000+00:00",0.0,0,347.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
