tickets, [2746221,353,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Enfore max_expiry_time server-side",3,"Bug found in beta-1.17.   One of SURFnet's customers found out how to increase the time that a file would be available on the server.  Even if we indicate that the max. expiry time is one month in the future, a user can simply set the date of his machine into the future and there you go, your file will stay online longer.  We need to enforce the max. expiry date server-side. \n\nthat means:\n\nif expiry_datetime_as-specified-by-client > max_expiry_datetime_as-set-on-server then\n    set expiry_datetime == config{max_expiry}\nfi\n\n","2010-12-10T12:20:28.000+00:00","2011-01-29T12:03:06.000+00:00",345073,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2010-12-13T11:35:15.000+00:00",0.0,0,353.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2756727,354,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Email address guessing and refusing bad addresses",3,"Expanding on ##340 about email address validation it would be good to be able to accept email addresses in various forms, to match what people get from their email clients.  That means doing \"guessing\" of what people mean while refusing plain bad addresses.  Make sure that email addresses containing internationalised characters can be used.  This requires a proper writeup of what we want to do with email address input!","2010-12-13T12:31:36.000+00:00","2010-12-13T12:31:36.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,354.0,0,0,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2863361,355,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","UI: Configurable <title>",3,"It would be nice to have a configurable <title> for the various pages, perhaps one part configurable end another part context sensitive (i.e. dependent on where in the workflow you are, upload, download etc). Currently it is mostly hardcoded in the various sources with \"Filesender:\"","2011-01-05T14:09:14.000+00:00","2012-02-07T17:34:35.000+00:00",114011,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,355.0,0,0,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2912349,356,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Download email notifications only generated for first download during same browser session",3,"In the same browser session, when downloading the same file more than once using the same url or directly from the MyFiles table, for either a standard upload or file uploaded using a voucher, the download email notifications are only generated for the first download. However if one quits one's browser and tries the same download again, another set of download email notifications is generated. In the past, these emails were generated *every* time a file was downloaded. Note that if a file is downloaded from a url in an email, no email will be generated if the same file is downloaded from the MyFiles table during the same browser session. As an aside, if there are two file recipients, who are each issued with a separate download url, the download notification emails are generated for both recipients for each of their first downloads, but also not for their subsequent repeated downloads. Tested with mac OSX 10.6.5, Firefox 3.6.13, Flash 10.1.102.64. Applies to both Flash and Gears.","2011-01-11T05:56:40.000+00:00","2012-02-11T23:25:48.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2012-02-11T23:25:48.000+00:00",0.0,0,356.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [2920109,357,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Subject and message fields do not clear after cancelling upload using a voucher",3,"When cancelling a file upload using a voucher, the subject and message fields do not reset. However the equivalent fields *do* reset when cancelling a standard authenticated file upload. This applies to both Flash and Gears uploads. Tested with Mac OSX 10.6.5, Firefox 3.6.13, Flash 10.1.102.64.","2011-01-12T01:47:25.000+00:00","2013-03-03T16:27:44.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2013-03-03T16:27:44.000+00:00",0.0,0,357.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-03-03T16:27:44.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2930061,358,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Filename accents not displayed in GUI when using Gears (correlates with known issue)",3,"When using Gears, accents from both special character sets (ISO-8859-1 and non-ISO-8859-1 UTF8) are being removed from *filenames*, but not subjects or messages, in the FileSender GUI when using Gears:\n\n    * Upload and Voucher Upload windows\n    * MyFiles table\n    * Download window\n    * Add New Recipient pop-up\n\nHowever the accents *do* appear in all fields of the autogenerated emails (upload, download, deleted file), including the filename field, as well as in the filename of the actual downloaded file. No issues when using Flash, where accents seem to be displayed under all circumstances. This behaviour correlates with the known issue documented on the [[International_Character_Handling]] page.","2011-01-13T07:57:44.000+00:00","2013-09-10T12:30:18.000+00:00",345073,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2013-09-10T12:30:18.000+00:00",0.0,0,358.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-09-10T12:30:18.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [2931229,359,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Xander and Maarten to discuss build infra and code repo",3,"FileSender 1.0 uses SVN in Assembla plus a Hudson build server.  Xander pointed out we need to figure out whether the presumed move to using a webapp framework means a change in this project infra.  I talked with Maarten today, he indicated he'd first like to work on the prototype the coming weeks to be able to make the problem more concrete, and then he'll contact Xander to discuss this.","2011-01-13T11:27:32.000+00:00","2011-07-29T12:50:10.000+00:00",213323,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-07-29T12:50:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,359.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
