tickets, [3077613,379,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","IPv6 addresses are not stored in the files table",3,"FileSender stores the IP address of the originating user into the 'files' table. This is however only fully implemented for IPv4 addresses. Code for sanitising/checking the originating IPv6 address is available but contains a few bugs:\n\n1) ip2long6/long2ip6 functions need extra declarations and input checks\n2) the fileip6address database column where the IPv6 address should be stored is currently too small (needs to be a 'character varying (45)')\n\nI have patches to implement the logging but they will break existing installations because of 2). Need to device a safe way to deploy (or just leave it a known issue)\n\n","2011-02-05T08:21:48.000+00:00","2012-02-29T20:38:09.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-04-29T12:08:01.000+00:00",0.0,0,379.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
