tickets, [4597238,480,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","New and upgrade-proof configuration of database parameters",3,"1.5 adds multiple database backend support (the DBAL code). Initially the configuration was implemented with a single URL-style dsn parameter. For various reasons it was decided to implement this slightly different to both ease packaging and make the upgrade path (from 1.0.1 to 1.5) a bit 'safer'.\n\nIn config.php (as distributed): replace all pg_* settings with db_* settings (make the prefix db-independent) and add a db_type parameter\n\nIn the code (DBAL.php): check the config settings according to the following flow:\n\n1) check if dsn is defined/set\n2) check if db_* parameters + db_type are defined/set\n3) check pg_* parameters are defined/set\n4) error\n\nFor cases 2) and 3) construct a dsn (with possible defaults like host and port if not explicitly set)\n\nThis will cater for the case were people still use the 'old' pg_* style settings, will introduce a similar (as in 1.0.1) but more flexible config (db_*) and also allows setting a single dsn for new db-types which need more than the generic db_* settings.","2011-08-02T08:58:00.000+00:00","2015-11-17T13:26:46.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-08-27T15:28:49.000+00:00",0.0,0,-44.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-17T13:26:46.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [4603186,481,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Make \"New Upload\" screen consistent between Flash and HTML5 variants",3,"Currently there are some differences in layout/button placement/workflow between the Flash and HTLM5 versions of the New Upload screen (which gives us the opportunity to make a choice about which one is nicer ;-)\n\n1) Fresh screen (no file selected yet):\nFlash: \"Browse\" button\nHTLM5: \"Choose file\" button + \"No file chosen\" text in a box followed by a \"Upload\" button to the right\n\n2) After selecting a file: \nFlash: \"Browse\" and \"Upload\" button followed by name and size below the buttons\nHTML5: \"Choose file\" button + \"<filename>\" text in a box followed by a \"Upload\" button to the right *and*  followed by name, size *and* MIME-type below the buttons\n\n2) After pressing Upload\n\nFlash: \"Browse\" button locked (grayed out), Upload button becomes \"Cancel\" button, name and size stays the same and is followed by a nice green progress bar below\nHTML5: The \"Choose file\"/upload block is replaced by a single \"Cancel\" button, name, size and mime type stays the same and is (after a while!) followed by the nice green progress bar.\n\nI somehow like the Flash variant ;-)\n\nThings that might be relevant:\n\nBrowsers used: FF 3.6.19 on OSX 10.5.8 for Flash, Chrome 13.xxx on OSX 10.5.8 for HTML5. Server version 1.5 Beta Revision: 741 on filesender.surfnet.nl/proto/\n\n\n","2011-08-02T18:37:02.000+00:00","2015-11-17T13:26:46.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-08-26T08:47:55.000+00:00",0.0,0,-45.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-17T13:26:46.000+00:00",null]
