tickets, [5240101,496,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload step descriptions",3,"In FileSender-1.0.1, the upload page (both authenticated and Guest) provided a guide describing each step of the upload process on the right hand side, but this is currently absent from 1.5:\n\"1 Enter delivery email address(es)\n2 Set expiry date\n3 Browse for a file\n4 Click on Send\"\n","2011-08-23T07:53:28.000+00:00","2011-09-26T09:52:04.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-08-25T07:21:52.000+00:00",0.0,0,496.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [5351331,497,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Put \"focus\" on \"close\" button in dialogue popups",3,"When clicking for example \"help\" or \"about\" in FileSender 1.5, a dialogue box pops up.  This box needs to be explicitly closed before a user can return to a \"useful\" FileSender 1.5 window again.  To facilitate easy closing of this dialogue box it would be helpful to put the focus on the \"close\" button when opening this dialogue box, such that a \"space\" or \"enter\" results in box closure and a user doesn't necessarily have to move his mouse pointer.  This would be the same for any dialogue box that is opened in FileSender 1.5","2011-08-24T05:45:57.000+00:00","2011-11-25T07:06:59.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-11-25T07:06:59.000+00:00",0.0,0,497.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [5354901,498,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Minor re-order of AuP, \"select file\" and \"upload\" + suggested name change",3,"1. I suggest to move the \"AuP\" box to the same place as with 1.0.1.  It makes the user's workflow more logic.  You enter To: address, set expiry date if you want, select file, *click AuP* and press \"Send\"\n\n2. I suggest to rename the \"upload\" button to \"Send\", make it *big* and reposition it.  Right now it sits right next to the \"Browse\" button.  However, the steps a user has to take go from top to bottom.  To me it makes more sense to have the \"Send\" button as the last thing to do in a flow that goes from top to bottom.  It needs to big to make sure a user doesn't have to use more effort then needed to both see the button and click on it.\n\n3. Right now, you have a label \"select a file\", followed by a text box followed by a browse button.  Upon selecting a file, the name and size are displayed underneath that textbox.  It would make more sense to start with a label \"Selected file\" followed by an empty field followed by a \"Select a file\" or \"Browse for a file\" button.  The name would then appear in the empty field, the size underneath, and -if possible- the date the file was last changed if that is an attribute that can be asked for.  The text boxes should be un-editable.\n\n","2011-08-24T07:29:50.000+00:00","2011-12-30T21:30:55.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-12-30T21:30:55.000+00:00",0.0,0,498.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
