tickets, [5628761,507,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Create and document upload, add recipient and issue voucher workflow tests using Selenium-IDE",3,"Automate upload (for both authenticated and Guest use cases), add recipient and issue voucher workflow tests using [[url:http://seleniumhq.org/|Selenium's]] Selenium-IDE Firefox browser plugin. Copy and update test descriptions from Test Workflows for v1-1 into scripts as comments. Update test workflow descriptions at [[Test Workflows for v1-5]] using exported comments from scripts. Scripts located in [[url:http://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/nodes/workflowtests/selenium_IDE|root/workflowtests/selenium_IDE]].  *Note:* applies to HTML5 case only (Firefox 4+), and not to the Flash case (Firefox 3.6.x) (see #526); excludes authentication steps (logon, logoff, and activating download and voucher pages), clicking on \"Re-Send Email\", \"Add New Recipient\" and \"Delete\" buttons and email content verification and interaction. ","2011-08-29T02:38:11.000+00:00","2012-03-30T00:52:08.000+00:00",1051963,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-03-30T00:52:08.000+00:00",0.0,0,507.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [5696421,508,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Race condition with file deletion cronjob under certain circumstances",3,"Note: when the quick fix is implemented for 1.5/1.0.1, this ticket should be relabeled to \"under development 2.0\".\n\nI got a number of user reports about a file upload that went through just fine but the file seemed to be automatically deleted when you tried to download it.  So upload went fine, move went fine, email was sent out, download screen popped up, but download went bad.  Nothing significant in the logging.\n\nAfter observing what goes on on our system I made these observations: observations:\n \n1. on our install the php temp upload directory is set to /tmp rather then to /data/filesender/tmp\n2. our FileSender files directory is /data/filesender/files\n3. /tmp and /files are on different partitions.  That means that a move is an actual transfer, rather then just flipping a pointer in an inode.\n4. our cleanup (expiry) cronjob ran every 5 minutes\n \nThis means the move from temp dir to filesender files dir takes time. With an 1.5 GB file this might intersect with the cronjob running.  If I read the cronjob's code correctly, it checks for files that do exist in the filestore but do not have a database entry associated with them.  If it founds such files, it deletes them.  In possibly the same cronjob run, it then notices a stale database entry that is then set to \"closed\".\n \nPresto, the file has disappeared for the user.\n\nThe problem affects both 1.0.1 and 1.5.  There is a quick fix under discussion, which in practice will prevent the problem from occuring unless you configure your site explicitly to trigger it.  The ultimate solution has to wait for a redo of the database schema in the post-1.5 development work.","2011-08-30T08:33:24.000+00:00","2015-12-01T10:23:52.000+00:00",593383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2015-12-01T10:23:52.000+00:00",0.0,0,1.0,0,0,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-01T10:23:52.000+00:00",null]
