tickets, [7073533,549,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Missing language tag in validate_file() in pages/upload.php",3,"I was looking through the code and noticed a missing language tag in\nhttp://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/nodes/filesender/branches/filesender-1.5/pages/upload.php\n\nit looks to me like the particular circumstance (file select returning an empty file descriptor) is unlikely to occur but still, it would be good to have a language tag there :)  I would have had a go at it were it not that I don't exactly know *when* you'd actually end up in that piece of code.  Would be good to include that in the code comments, what circumstances trigger that particular error.\n\n\n// Validate FILE (HTML5 only)\nfunction validate_file()\n{\n        fileMsg(\"\");\n        if(!document.getElementById(\"fileToUpload\").files[0])\n        {\n                fileMsg(\"Please select a file\");\n                return false;\n        } else\n\nJan","2011-09-25T17:12:54.000+00:00","2011-10-11T19:29:16.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-10-11T19:29:16.000+00:00",0.0,0,549.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [7307073,550,"cxFt16lZGr3Q7YeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","progress bar quirk in 1.0.1 plus html5 0.1 module",3,"on a 1.0.1 plus html5 0.1 module deployment (freshly baked by Xander), the progress bar exhibits a quirk when uploading files larger than the default chunksize. Say the chunksize is 2Mb and the file is 6Mb: as soon as the \"send\" button is pressed, the progress bar displays \"99%\" progress; upon completion of the first 2Mb chunk, progress is reset to the actual progress at that moment, which is 33%. From that point on, the progress bar behaves correctly","2011-09-29T06:15:51.000+00:00","2011-10-03T09:31:29.000+00:00",593383,null,"cxFt16lZGr3Q7YeJe5aVNr,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-10-03T09:31:29.000+00:00",0.0,0,550.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [7369853,551,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","1.0.1+ browse button doesn't work in Chrome",3,"Using Chrome (14.0.835.186) on my Mac (10.5.8) *and* on a Windows 7 box, pressing the Browse button doesn't do anything, no browse window is opened. Using FF 6.0 it works.","2011-09-30T08:32:01.000+00:00","2011-10-03T14:33:20.000+00:00",593383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-10-03T14:21:24.000+00:00",0.0,0,551.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [7382903,552,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Add Version.php with re-usable version constant",3,"<pre><code>Date: Fri, 09 Sep 2011 23:39:35 +0200\nFrom: \"Dyonisius (Dick) Visser\" <...@....>\nTo: filesender-dev@....\nSubject: [filesender-dev] Version check\n\nSimilar message sent to simplesaml list:\n\nhttp://groups.google.com/group/simplesamlphp/browse_thread/thread/1c358fa5891f4a27?hl=en_US\n\nFilesender has a version number hhidden away in www/index.php.\nAttached is a patch that moves it to a constant, and add a compare function.\n\nAs explain on the simplesaml list, this patch is useful mostly for\nintegration with other apps.\nWould be best if it got applied to older versions too.\n\ncheers,\n\nDick\n\n</code></pre>\n","2011-09-30T13:50:03.000+00:00","2011-10-10T07:28:13.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-10-10T07:28:13.000+00:00",0.0,0,552.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [7407413,553,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Voucher upload listing in My Files logic",3,"If a voucher recipient is logged in under a different identity to the voucher issuer, the file will be listed in the voucher recipient's My Files table, not that of the voucher issuer. Only if the voucher recipient is not authenticated, or authenticated as the voucher issuer, will the file uploaded using the voucher be listed in the My Files table of the voucher issuer. See #463 for more information and how this was dealt with in 1.5.","2011-09-30T23:47:11.000+00:00","2015-12-01T10:24:16.000+00:00",593383,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2015-12-01T10:24:16.000+00:00",0.0,0,2.0,0,0,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-01T10:24:16.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [7407573,554,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","bcc generation logic",3,"The bcc is generated for both uploads and downloads whether logged in as the voucher issuer or not logged in, however is not generated if logged in as another user (other than the voucher issuer), possibly because the file is stored in the My Files table of the authenticated voucher recipient not the voucher issuer (see #553). See #462 for more information and how this was dealt with in 1.5 (together with related but separate aspects unique to 1.5).  Bcc emails to the voucher issuer are also not triggered when adding recipients to a file which was originally uploaded using a voucher by the voucher recipient.","2011-09-30T23:53:45.000+00:00","2015-12-01T10:24:35.000+00:00",593383,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2015-12-01T10:24:35.000+00:00",0.0,0,3.0,0,0,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-01T10:24:35.000+00:00",null]
