tickets, [7463553,557,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Adapt Help and About standard pages to HTML5",3,"1. replace references to Gears with references to HTML5 and make texts \"flow\" (\"for files > 2GB you need a HTML5 enabled browser ... \" but then better ;)\n2. preferably have a link to a page where they can find which browsers are likely to work.  The browser compat matrix might be a good point.  \n\nad. 2: a browser compatibility matrix on filesender.org is the logical result of testing.  The issue would be maintaining it, and that we direct end users of filesender.org standard installs to our own project development site.  If Assembla is down, that then affects end users which might not be the best of ideas.  We might want to release the browser compatibility matrix as a separate package ;)","2011-10-03T11:17:09.000+00:00","2011-10-24T04:19:35.000+00:00",593383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-10-24T04:19:35.000+00:00",0.0,0,557.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
