tickets, [7464263,560,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Figure out packaging details: how to deal with existing installs on a server",3,"The \"fall special\" won't be an upgrade to prevent people who don't necessarily want that losing the Gears functionality by accident.  A problem that then arises is you can't have two FileSender debian packages installed on the same machine: they use the same paths ;)\n\nXander wants to figure out something smart for this.  So if you have FS installed, it generates a package conflict when you try to install the fall special over it.  The trick is in how this conflict is resolved.  ","2011-10-03T11:29:19.000+00:00","2011-11-01T09:55:13.000+00:00",593383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-11-01T09:55:13.000+00:00",0.0,0,560.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
