tickets, [7928483,569,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Case-sensitive references to Files in cron.php",3,"As reported by Claude Tompers (RESTENA): cron.php contains references to the files column as 'Files' (capital F). This will result in errors when using a database backend that is case-sensitive wrt column names. Noticed with a MySQL backend in 1.5 and fixed in 1.5 with [[r:941]] . Candidate for fixing in interim 1.0/1.1 releases (trivial fix).","2011-10-10T14:16:06.000+00:00","2011-10-22T12:46:37.000+00:00",345073,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-10-22T12:44:11.000+00:00",0.0,0,569.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
