tickets, [8065513,572,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Error handling: no error handling when debug=false and database connection failure",3,"Note: this is NOT a show stopping issue and can perfectly well be fixed after 1.5.  But a fine example of how we need to revisit error logging throughout the code, ensuring it is both consistent, it starts to adhere to various \"log levels\", service-affecting issues are logged in filesender.log and errors in the UI are meaningful.\n\n\nunable to connect to database and debug=true results in the following (expected) entry in the filesender logfile:\n\n2011/10/12 03:07:09 [Session ID: none] Error: [2] pg_connect(): Unable to connect to PostgreSQL server: FATAL:  database \"filesende\" does not exist : /usr/share/php/MDB2/Driver/pgsql.php [435] [86.62.167.38(86.62.167.38)]\n\n\nunable to connect to database and debug=false results in no entry in the filesender logfile and in the following message to the user:\n\nFatal error: Uncaught exception 'DBALException' with message 'Error executing query: MDB2 Error: connect failed' in /var/www/filesender-1.5/classes/DBAL.php:280 Stack trace: #0 /var/www/filesender-1.5/classes/Log.php(136): DBAL->exec('? IN...', '', '', 'Error', '', '', '2011-10-12 03:1...', '', '', 'Error executing...', 'a9f348deeaad60f...') #1 /var/www/filesender-1.5/classes/Functions.php(381): Log->saveLog('', 'Error', 'Error executing...') #2 /var/www/filesender-1.5/pages/vouchers.php(134): Functions->getVouchers() #3 /var/www/filesender-1.5/www/index.php(222): require_once('/var/www/filese...') #4 {main} thrown in /var/www/filesender-1.5/classes/DBAL.php on line 280 ","2011-10-11T16:16:58.000+00:00","2013-08-23T16:50:08.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,10.100000381469727,0,0,238024,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-08-07T12:39:41.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [8070303,573,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","<title> is hardconfigured with \"FileSender:\"",3,"Interesting.  This is exactly the same in FileSender 1.0.1, so not a new issue.  This should probably be set to the $site_name.  Note that this is not a show-stopping bug and FileSender 1.5 can live with it.  Having said that, it is sloppy ;)  There are 5 files with the issue:\n\nroot@jansboks:/var/www/filesender-1.5/www# grep -i '<title>' *\nindex.php:<title>FileSender:</title>\ninvalidvoucher.php:<title>FileSender:</title>\nlogout.php:<title>FileSender:</title>\nvouchererror.php:<title>FileSender:</title>\n","2011-10-11T17:27:32.000+00:00","2011-10-13T06:36:38.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-10-13T06:36:38.000+00:00",0.0,0,573.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8070693,574,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","vouchererror.php no longer used?",3,"From the looks of it, www/vouchererror.php is no longer used?  Please confirm, then we can remove it from www/\n\nroot@jansboks:/var/www/filesender-1.5# grep -R vouchererror.php *\nwww/.svn/all-wcprops:vouchererror.php\nwww/.svn/all-wcprops:/svn/file_sender/!svn/ver/508/filesender/branches/filesender-1.5/www/vouchererror.php\nwww/.svn/entries:vouchererror.php\n","2011-10-11T17:36:21.000+00:00","2011-11-11T23:53:48.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-11-11T23:53:48.000+00:00",0.0,0,574.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8071143,575,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","invalidvoucher.php without language tag",3,"invalidvoucher.php is called from www/download.php wen a file *should* exist (it is there in the database) but can not be found on-disk:\n\nwww/download.php:\n\n        print_r(\"file not found clause\");\n        // physical file was not found\n        logEntry(\"Download: File Not Found - \".$file);\n        // redirect to file is no longer available\n         header( 'Location: invalidvoucher.php' ) ;\n\ninvalidvoucher.php does not have a language tag.  The text is hard-coded in English.  Looking at the message the page should convey, a new language tag might be needed?\n\n_DOWNLOAD_FILE_NOT_FOUND=\"Error: file not found on disk, please contact your site administrator\";\n\nIn addition invalidvoucher.php appears to have significantly more content then pages/vouchercancelled.php so cleanup might be possible?\n \n\n","2011-10-11T17:44:34.000+00:00","2012-02-28T11:42:08.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-02-28T11:42:08.000+00:00",0.0,0,575.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8073173,576,"aD0nWgKfWr3kQaabIlDkbG",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Server side validation of voucher creation",2,"Server side validation for vouchers, like we do for file uploads.","2011-10-11T18:17:41.000+00:00","2012-02-29T16:03:16.000+00:00",394418,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-02-29T16:03:16.000+00:00",0.0,0,576.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8074403,577,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Cosmetic & non-blocking: MyFiles table headers don't auto-size",4,"For post-1.5 consideration.\n\nWhen using Norwegian I noticed that the word \"størrelse\" is larger then the space allocated in the \"size\" table column header.  It looks as if the fields don't auto-size which is what can be expected if we wish to have the FileSender width to be constant.  I don't know if there's a clever way around this but would like us to think a bit about it *after* 1.5 is away.","2011-10-11T18:47:58.000+00:00","2014-10-21T22:20:10.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,577.0,0,0,3325193,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8074643,578,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Update standard 1.5 help text with 1.0.1+html5 \"HTML5\" references",3,"There's a text to direct users to \"html5 browsers\" added to the help file for the 1.0.1+html5 release.  This text needs to be duplicated to the 1.5 help file and the \"red error message\" when file size too big needs to be updated as well.","2011-10-11T18:51:59.000+00:00","2011-12-30T21:29:49.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-12-30T21:29:08.000+00:00",0.0,0,578.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8394793,579,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","No check on available storage space before upload",3,"On a test server with little space I attempted to upload a file that was larger then the amount of available space.  When the server ran out of disk, the client got a stuck progress bar.\n\nfirst thought: ask server whether there is enough space available to perform upload (if size is known before upload start!) and report back a user-friendly error \"out-of-space, contact your service admin\" if not enough space is available.  ","2011-10-17T13:01:01.000+00:00","2011-12-29T14:05:01.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-12-29T14:05:01.000+00:00",0.0,0,579.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8395023,580,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Post-1.5: have numerical progress under progress bar",3,"With large files it takes time, especially on slower links, before the progress bar makes a 1% tick.  It might be informative to have numerical progress as well, under the progress bar.\n\nSomething like \"xxx of xxx bytes/kb/mb/GB transferred.  \n\nImplementing the counter probably is a good step towards a mechanism for doing realtime uploadspeed indicator in FileSender.","2011-10-17T13:03:31.000+00:00","2011-10-17T13:03:31.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,580.0,0,0,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8504253,581,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Only load flash object when required after client side test",3,"If user has HTML5 then we do not need the flash object loaded.","2011-10-19T01:29:16.000+00:00","2011-12-30T21:48:20.000+00:00",394418,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-12-30T21:48:20.000+00:00",0.0,0,581.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8505283,582,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Inconsistent file size limit warnings",3,"*Flash limit:* warning is currently \"File is too large. Please use a HTML5 enabled browser. (Maximum without HTML5: 2.00 GB)\" >> suggest changing \"File is too large\" to \"File size is too large\" and \"a HTML5\" to \"an HTML5\".\n*HTML5 limit:* warning is currently \"File size is too large (Max: [X] GB)\" (where X is the configured maximum) >> suggest changing \"Max:\" to \"Maximum:\".\n","2011-10-19T02:19:30.000+00:00","2011-10-24T04:30:38.000+00:00",593383,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2011-10-24T04:30:38.000+00:00",0.0,0,582.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8507983,583,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Email addresses rejected at maximum for uploads & voucher issue",3,"Recipient email addresses are (correctly) rejected when *exceeding* the configured maximum for adding recipients, but (incorrectly) rejected when *meeting* the configured maximum for uploads and issuing a voucher. For example, when the maximum number of email recipients is set at two, and two email addresses are entered (separated by either a comma or semicolon) for an upload or issuing a voucher, the warning comes up \"The maximum number of email recipients allowed is 2\" (one email address is accepted). See #485 for related discussion for 1.5 release. ","2011-10-19T04:49:44.000+00:00","2011-10-24T09:03:08.000+00:00",593383,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2011-10-24T09:03:08.000+00:00",0.0,0,583.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8509093,584,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","AJAX load Flash object *after* tested it's required",3,"1.5 loads flash object and all the required HTML then client side a test is done to decide which to use.\n\nIf HTML5 is available then the flash object is ignored.\n\nWe should AJAX load the flash object after we have tested and \ndecided that flash is required so that HTML5 users do not need Flash at all.\n","2011-10-19T05:45:10.000+00:00","2012-02-28T09:40:23.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-02-28T09:40:23.000+00:00",0.0,0,584.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8518253,585,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Use of the \"back\" browser button gives SimpleSAMLphp error",4,"In many cases when users for whatever reason use the \"back\" button of the browser they will go back to a SimpleSAMLphp page which in most cases reults in an error page like:\n\n\n<pre><code>Exception: State information lost, and no way to restart the request.\n\n0: /usr/share/simplesamlphp/lib/SimpleSAML/Auth/State.php:158 (SimpleSAML_Auth_State::loadState)\n1: /usr/share/simplesamlphp/modules/saml/www/sp/saml2-acs.php:24 (require)\n2: /usr/share/simplesamlphp/www/module.php:135 (N/A)\n\nURL:\nhttps://filesender.surfnet.nl/simplesaml/module.php/saml/sp/saml2-acs.php/default-sp\n</code></pre>\n\nThis is a common case when using SSP (not only with FileSender) and I'm not sure if it is fixable or where it should be 'fixed'. A few posibilities to handle this:\n\n- Disable the Back button (if possible but even when it is possible it looks intrusive/confusing to do that)\n- Leave it as is and make a FAQ entry\n- Do a 'redirect' from the/a first FileSender landing page to the 'New Upload' page so that when people do use the Back button they go back to a FileSender page and not a SSP page ?\n\nFYI: at SURFnet I almost get no support questions (it does seem to work without questions for most people) except for the occasional error report about this one. Jan also got them at UNINETT. My standard reply (\"Don't use the Back button\") somehow doesn't feel good ;-) It does happen in 1.0/1,1 but also in 1.5 if you never leave the New Upload page.","2011-10-19T09:21:53.000+00:00","2012-03-01T07:30:49.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,585.0,0,0,3325193,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8568263,586,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Inconsistent help.php header format",3,"In about.php, the \"About\" header text is bold and white with some padding on the left, as per the headers in about.php and help.php in the 1.0.1 release. However the \"Help\" header in help.php is unbolded and black with no padding on the left. ","2011-10-20T03:24:38.000+00:00","2011-10-20T22:14:44.000+00:00",593383,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2011-10-20T22:14:44.000+00:00",0.0,0,586.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8718633,587,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","cron.php when logging (logEntry) creates logfiles owned by root",2,"Currentky some debug statements will add a log entry to the filesender logfile (not the specific CRON logfile). When that logfile doesn't exist yet it will be created but owned by the root user. That will meand that the web user gets:\n\nWarning: fopen(/var/www/filesender-proto/log/20111024.log.txt) [function.fopen]: failed to open stream: Permission denied in /var/www/filesender-1.5-svn/includes/ErrorHandler.php on line 97\ncan't open file\n","2011-10-24T08:54:30.000+00:00","2012-05-06T11:04:54.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-05-06T11:04:54.000+00:00",0.0,0,2.0999999046325684,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [8884833,588,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Problematic downloads using Chrome on Windows7-before-SP1",3,"As discovered and reported by Xander Jansen:\n\nDownloads using Chrome on Win7 *without SP1 or the relevant hotfix* are seemingly OK (no error message) but are incomplete (way too small). Applying a MS Hotfix *or* updating to Win7 SP1 appears to fix the problem. \n\nEven then there is the issue that Win7 still seems to be silent about filled disks :( \n\nAnother strange thing is that the Win7 Resource Monitor seems to have a problem measuring the network load when uploading with Chrome. It reports something like 500Kbps when the actual\nupload performance was more like 30 Mbps or more.\n\n\nThe bug is more or less mentioned/described in http://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=21055 (comments 56 and 57 are relevant). \nRelevant link to Microsoft knowledge base: http://support.microsoft.com/kb/2498472\n\nThis is NOT a bug in FileSender hence not something we can fix but it *is* an issue that will affect the FileSender user experience and therefore is documented here.\n","2011-10-26T07:25:08.000+00:00","2016-02-26T13:28:17.000+00:00",675223,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2016-02-26T13:28:17.000+00:00",0.0,0,588.0,0,1,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T13:28:17.000+00:00",null]
