tickets, [10485303,600,"bZ7dTif7Gr4zu5acwqjQWU",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Editable alerts if IdP has not provided enough information",3,"Hi, \n\nnow, if some IdP has not provided enough information (in our case some IdPs don't provide attribute email) user can see alert \"Although you have authenticated with an Identity Provider. It appears your IdP has not provided enough information for this application to continue\" but users usually don't know anything about IdP so it tells them nothing and they don't come back anymore....\nThe problem is that this alert is compiled into flash so we can't change it. Is there any way to move this alert from flash into config file to be editable? We would like to change this text to our language and provide some more information what our users should do to fix that...\n\nWe install filesender from deb-packages so it's not such a good idea to change this text in sourcecode, compile and replace some files in deb-instalation afterwards...\n\nflex/src/filesender.mxml:                                               Alert.show(\"Although you have authenticated with an Identity Provider. It appears your IdP has not provided enough information for this application to continue\",\"Error: Contact Administrator\")\n\nThx a lot","2011-11-25T23:19:43.000+00:00","2014-10-21T22:20:05.000+00:00",114011,null,"bZ7dTif7Gr4zu5acwqjQWU,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,cqcmdkRjmr4lZSeJe4gwI3",null,0.0,0,600.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [10489103,601,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","HTML5 (or Gears) upload with a backslash or double quote in the filename fails",3,"With 1.1 using HTML5 and also with 1.0.1 using Gears uploads of a file containg a \\ in the filename fails after upload. User gets a 'Cannot move file' popup and on the backend a \"Cannot find File in Temp Folder\" is logged in the administrator Error logs (accesible from the UI).\n\nThis is caused by the way the filename is passed on to the backend on two different\noccasions in two different ways. \n\nDuring the upload (of each chunk) the filename is passed through a POST/GET and the \\ gets escaped (say hi to the magic quotes :():\n\n    [n] => back\\\\slash.jpg\n\nAfter the upload when the file is moved from temp storage to final storage the filename is sent in a json-encoded block and the \\ is not escaped:\n\n   [fileoriginalname] => back\\slash.jpg\n\nSince the filename is used for generating a hashed temporary filename on the backend there will be a *different* tempfilename on both occasions and the move will fail.\n\nA structural solution would be to use the same method on both occasions to pass the filename from UI to backend (so any escaping/encoding/etc will be the same) or use one moment in the workflow to generate the tempfilename and use the result on all occasions where the tempfilename is needed.\n\nWorkarounds for this case could be:\n\n- put the \\ on the list of invalid characters in the filename (function fnCheckString in the flex source in two src files) Needs careful checking on Windows where the \\ has a special meaning.\n- use stripslashes on the input during uploads: this might work but is highly dependent on the 'magic quotes' mess we all learned to love and will definitely introduce complications\n- turn of magic quotes ? (needs testing and sanity checking)\n\nNote that this will be taken care of in 1.5 in a structural way, see #405\n","2011-11-26T09:38:20.000+00:00","2016-12-12T19:44:13.000+00:00",593383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-06-03T13:20:38.000+00:00",0.0,0,601.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [10498313,602,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Download of file with double quote in filename breaks content-disposition header ",4,"When downloading a file with a \" in the filename the actual download suggests a 'broken' filename (the part up till the \"). For example:\n\ntest\".jpg -> test\n\nQuick fix (for 1.1) is to replace all double quotes in the filename with _ in the content-disposition header.\n\nNote that it is possible to upload files with a \" in the name with Flash. See also #601 .","2011-11-26T20:22:46.000+00:00","2012-06-03T13:21:07.000+00:00",593383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-06-03T13:21:07.000+00:00",0.0,0,602.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [10532323,603,"ccUPoWSBur3RuveJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Syntax-check of email-fields must happen prior to upload starting",3,"This weekend I had my slightly tech-fobic mother test cloudstor, version 1.1. She pasted in the email-address she was going to send to, browsed to a file etc., uploaded 200 megs over a very, very , slow link, and then, some hour later, got an error-message from the mailserver that she had used the wrong format email-address. She had pasted in: \n\n*\"Firstname Lastname\" <firstlast@recipient.org>*\n\ninstead of \n\n*firstlast@recipient.org*\n\nNot a very good impression, getting the error after the upload was finished.","2011-11-28T10:38:56.000+00:00","2015-12-01T10:24:57.000+00:00",593383,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2015-12-01T10:24:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,603.0,0,1,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-01T10:24:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [10601713,604,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Not all 'dangerous' characters displayed in My Files",3,"The backslash is not being displayed in the 1.5 My Files table (no gap is left either) (it does display in the sent email's subject and message though), but does get displayed in the 1.1 My Files table. When I enter the following into the subject and message fields:\n<pre><code>\n<tag> text &amp;\"'></?\\n'\"\n</code></pre> it appears in the My Files table as:\n<pre><code><tag> text &amp;\"'></?n'\"\n</code></pre>\n\n","2011-11-29T04:38:30.000+00:00","2011-12-29T14:13:57.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-12-29T14:13:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,604.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [10602313,605,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Subject and message field issues when adding new recipient",3,"When adding a new recipient, the Subject and Message fields are not autocompleting from the original email sent, but they did in 1.1. Also, after entering custom text into the Subject and Message fields, if I cancel and then click on the \"Add new recipient\" button for the same file again, the custom text is still displayed i.e. does not clear upon cancel (also applies to 1.1).","2011-11-29T05:01:23.000+00:00","2012-09-10T08:02:38.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2011-12-29T14:12:35.000+00:00",0.0,0,605.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
