tickets, [12091353,621,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Uploads fail when using Suhosin plugin (PHP hardening) and IE8+",4,"When using the Suhosin PHP plugin (not the 'patch') on the server uploads fail due to an (old) default Suhosin setting which appears to be incompatible with IE8+\n\nSolution is (according to http://www.hardened-php.net/suhosin/changelog.html ):\n\nDisable suhosin.session.cryptua by default because of Internet Explorer 8 \"features\"\n\nThis default is set to Off as of Suhosin plugin Version 0.9.28.\n\nNote that this setting is also active when running Suhosin in simulation mode.","2011-12-29T16:35:55.000+00:00","2016-02-26T13:28:17.000+00:00",675223,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2016-02-26T13:28:17.000+00:00",0.0,0,621.0,0,1,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T13:28:17.000+00:00",null]
