tickets, [12953943,626,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Flash upload possible without checking AuP ",3,"With non-HTML5 browsers pressing the Send will give a red warning that you must agree to the terms but the upload will start anyway. Using HTML5 capable browsers it is as intended.","2012-01-16T20:36:05.000+00:00","2012-01-18T16:46:29.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-01-18T16:46:29.000+00:00",0.0,0,626.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [13163553,627,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Improve download usability: direct download link + correct mime-type?",3,"When a recipient clicks on the download link, a web page opens with info and a big download button.  The original motivation for doing it this way was practical: we couldn't do direct downloads with the technology choices we'd made.  However, this reason is no longer there.\n\nIn addition, back in the filesender prototyping days in 2008, I remember reasoning that a user ought to have both options: a direct download-link in the email, clicking on which resulted in the file downloading (and possibly opening in the right application), with in additoin a \"click here to learn more about your file before downloading it\" anti-phishing link.\n\nWe ended up with *only* the anti-phishing option, out of necessity.  Now that it is no longer needed, we should revisit this and make it easier.\n\nThis ties in with a request I've seen for a \"direct download link\" to allow tools like wget, curl to download a file directly (automating workflow!).  Another good reason to do this is complaints I got from a number of users: the click on the link but the file doesn't open in <relevant app>.  So there is a group of users to whom it is more natural to click and see the file open.  I suggest we make this happen.\n\nIt probably involves some fiddling with sending the right  mime-type as well I'd guess.","2012-01-19T15:59:32.000+00:00","2012-01-19T15:59:32.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,627.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
