tickets, [14396843,637,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Allow for optional personal message in a guest use voucher [M]",3,"For file uploads users can enter a personalised message, explaining what they get.  This is not available for guest vouchers.  We have had requests for this from users.","2012-02-07T13:43:53.000+00:00","2013-10-28T08:09:46.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2013-07-30T05:29:40.000+00:00",0.0,0,-35.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-07-30T05:29:40.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [14451433,638,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Set up crowd-sourcing infra for localisation",3,"We need an easy to manage way to support crowd-sourcing of localisation.  Per localisation we need preferably at least 2 volunteers maintaining *that* localisation file and keeping it in sync with the \"master\".  It needs to be easy to see how much of a translation is complete and how much is missing. It also needs to be easy to submit bugs on translations (???)\n\nWhat should come out of the \"translation crowd-sourcing tool\" ultimately goes into FileSender releases.  Only language files that have at least 1 maintainer can be bundled with the filesender release.\n\nLikely tool/service:\nhttps://www.transifex.net/tour/features/translate/\n\nSupported language file formats:\nhttp://help.transifex.net/features/formats.html#user-formats\n\nThe company:\nhttp://www.indifex.com/#\n\nWhat likely needs to be done is we need to either change our language file format, or implement some gateway.\n\nWhy is this important?  With all the languages in Europe, we'll soon be swamped with language files that need maintenance....","2012-02-07T22:41:03.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:03:09.000+00:00",114623,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2016-02-26T14:03:09.000+00:00",0.0,0,638.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:03:09.000+00:00",null]
