tickets, [14559023,640,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Real time upload/download performance feedback",3,"Jeff Hagley, setting up the Internet2 FileSender install, came with this feature request.\n\nImplement real time feedback to the user through the UI on upload/download performance and feedback on that performance relative to what others get.\n\nIf we can tell a user \"the average person got 80Mbps upload and 83 Mbps download, and here is what you just got/are getting\" that would help both the user and\nthe site.\n\nThe user has the benefit of knowing whether he's within the reasonable upload/downloadspeed band or whether there is something that might need attention.\n\nThe site has the benefit of both marketing a high speed high quality network \"upload through your NREN and life is good\", and enabling a user to figure out\nwhether the problem is their bandwidth/desktop or whether there might be a service issue.\n\n\nBlue sky dream: something a-la SURFnet-Detective for FileSender specific. Give users real time feedback on upload/download performance, and on said performance\ncompared to other users.  In addition, allow them to do a pre-upload check on performance.  AdobeConnect does this, as do many DDoS clients.  That pre-upload\ncheck might then include other checks, a sort of \"can I do FileSender and how fast can I do it\" check.  Lastly would be great to include some way to help users\ndiagnose possible problems.\n\nNow this looks remarkably like the SURFnet detective but then FileSender specific.\n\nIt would require stuff in the UI.  Where we'd put it is probably clear when we've sorted out the \"where do we put advanced functionality without cluttering the\nbasic functionality\" question.  In addition there is backend code that needs to be written.\n\nJeff suggested this could work with PerfSonar.","2012-02-08T22:30:18.000+00:00","2012-08-03T12:58:24.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,640.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [14589413,641,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","PHP session management and multiple tabs/windows per browser",2,"Current workflow depends partly (a.o. for voucher uploads) on PHP session specific variables. Since a PHP session is browser specific and cannot (without extrs measures) distinguish between actions done from different browser tabs or windows this will 'break'for example simultaneous voucher uploads (multiple uploads using a voucher from the same browser session at the same time). We might need extra code to generate a window/tab specific identifier that can be used to separate actions. See a.o. http://www.php.net/manual/en/ref.session.php#74557 ","2012-02-09T08:34:05.000+00:00","2013-03-19T20:22:02.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,2.0999999046325684,0,1,3325193,1,0.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [14754463,642,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Enable \"apply action to multiple files\" in MyFiles and Vouchers tables",3,"If you have more than two files, it becomes interesting to be able to apply the \"re-send email\" and especially \"delete\" action to multiple files at once.  I don't know how this would pan out for \"add recipient\".  \n\nEnvisaged result for user:\n-tickbox or other practical method to select which files to apply action to\n-give user a good way to indicate and *know* whatever will be done now will be applied to multiple files\n-ask \"are you sure\"\n-do action\n\nMaybe a tickbox \"whatever I will do now, will be applied to multiple files\".","2012-02-10T17:35:40.000+00:00","2012-02-10T17:36:18.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,642.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [14780543,643,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Get rid of \"this email might be phishing\" when sending to gmail accounts",3,"Gmail labels filesender emails as \"possible phishing\".  I assume this issue ties in with SPF records, preventing for example apple's mail client to label filesender emails as \"spam\" etc.  So this is more of a placeholder ticket for holding the thought that making sure filesender emails get through isn't 100% wrapped up nicely.","2012-02-11T09:55:56.000+00:00","2012-02-11T09:55:56.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,643.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [14782653,644,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Voucher: send.click without entering email address results in send button confusion",3,"When clicking on send without having entered email address, red error message appears.  This is as it should be.\n\nWhen you then enter an email address and click on Send again the error message disappears but the voucher is not sent.\n\nIt takes a 3rd click to actually send the voucher.","2012-02-11T14:27:10.000+00:00","2012-07-10T06:24:00.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-05-09T19:15:54.000+00:00",0.0,0,8.100000381469727,0,1,447388,0,0.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [14782713,645,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Polish the \"are you sure\" delete dialogue boxes",3,"When deleting a voucher or file, the \"delete/cancel\" dialogue comes up.\n\n-it says \"delete\" or \"cancel\".  This should be \"yes\" or \"no\"\n-the focus is not neither of the buttons.  It should be on \"no\"\n-the layout of the dialogue needs to be done right: the texts centered, the margins left and right should be equal, and the \"yes\" and \"no\" buttons need to be nicely spaced related to eachother, and the margins.  IN addition the yes/no buttons should not be too close to eachother, should someone use a mouse to click on it.\n\nThe same goes for the \"are you sure\" dialogue when cancelling a Flash upload\n\nThe HTML5  \"are you sure\" dialogue you get when cancelling an upload already is correct in \"yes/no\", but the other layout issues remain.\n\nSee also attached file for -hopefully- clarification.","2012-02-11T14:37:29.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:23:57.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2015-12-03T11:23:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,7.099999904632568,0,1,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:23:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [14782843,646,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Confusing message when using an already used guest upload voucher",3,"When a guest upload voucher has been used, and you try to use it again, you get \"this voucher has been cancelled\" whereas it ought to be something like \"this voucher has already been used, please contact <name sender> to send you a new one\".\n\n","2012-02-11T15:00:40.000+00:00","2012-03-11T23:30:15.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-03-09T11:58:28.000+00:00",0.0,0,646.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [14802523,647,"cxFt16lZGr3Q7YeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","provide opt-in mechanism to notify of imminent file expiry",4,"It might be useful to provide users with an unobtrusive per-file-opt-in mechanism that (provided they opt in) would provide them with notification of imminent expiry of a file -- they could use this notification event to take actions such as ringing their intended recipients in a last-ditch effort to get them to download the soon-to-be-no-longer-available file, or re-upload a new file or a replacement file.\n\nOff the top of my head I could think of the attaching of an iCalendar TODO event along with the your-file-is-now-available email; users could decide for themselves whether to import the event in the iCalendar file into their personal calendars. Xander warns me that some groupware email clients (Zimbra?) automatically import such iCalendar files into their user calendars, without consulting the user.\n\nMore exotically, perhaps per-user-per-file RSS subscriptions are possible? Per-user tweets? Per-user facebook wall messages? Suggestions very welcome.","2012-02-12T18:31:37.000+00:00","2012-02-12T18:31:37.000+00:00",114011,null,"cxFt16lZGr3Q7YeJe5aVNr,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA",null,0.0,0,647.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [14853843,648,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Add italian translations",3,"","2012-02-13T16:20:52.000+00:00","2012-07-08T19:51:00.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-07-08T19:51:00.000+00:00",0.0,0,2.0999999046325684,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [15183703,649,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Incorrect on-screen notification for deleted file",3,"When a file is deleted manually and a recipient tries clicking on the url to the deleted file, the on-screen message currently (on the beta-1 preview site) reads \"This voucher has been cancelled.\".  In 1.1 the message was \"This file/voucher is no longer available\", but if we're now using different messages for files and vouchers then it should probably read something like \"This file has been deleted.\". See also related ticket #646.","2012-02-17T01:33:57.000+00:00","2012-04-22T17:25:20.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,b8-41KDuKr344jeJe5cbLA","2012-03-11T23:30:15.000+00:00",0.0,0,6.099999904632568,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
