tickets, [19221813,718,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Facilitate feedback-points in warnings/errors",3,"SimpleSamlphp throws up a feedback form whenever something \"really bad\" happens.  The ease of reporting critical errors makes people actually report those.  FileSender should have something like that.  For example when a \"$lang[\"_DISK_SPACE_ERROR\"]\" is thrown, that a pointer to the instances standard problem reporting mechanisms is included.  Or even better: a standard form.  Something like that.  \n\nThis feature suggestion is to comb through the language file and identify logical points where to do that.  Second stage is to implement a practical way to make user feedback easy but only when you as service admin *really* want it: when stuf unexpectedly has gone wrong.  Maybe a standard feedback form or something.","2012-04-20T05:36:33.000+00:00","2012-04-20T05:36:33.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,718.0,0,1,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
