tickets, [20106813,721,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload using voucher rejects valid email address",3,"An email address of a valid format (e.g. firstname.surname@domain.edu or name@domain.net.au) is rejected when trying to upload a file using a voucher (\"Invalid or missing email\" appears after clicking on \"Send\" button), but is accepted for an authenticated file upload.","2012-04-30T07:14:46.000+00:00","2012-05-06T11:13:25.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-05-02T04:43:14.000+00:00",0.0,0,721.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20107313,722,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Authenticated upload after failed attempt using voucher in another tab cancels voucher and displays Guest upload confirmation",2,"If I try to upload a file using a voucher and this fails (e.g. case in #721) and I then load the \"Send File\" page as an authenticated user and upload a file:\n* the upload confirmation page presented is that for a Guest (no \"Send File\", \"Guest Voucher\" or \"My Files\" buttons are displayed) but should be the one for an authenticated user\n* the voucher I had been trying to use is cancelled (can no longer be used, disappears from Vouchers table) \n* the uploaded file does still reflect an authenticated upload in the \"My Files\" table, in that the sender is \"Me\"","2012-04-30T07:28:39.000+00:00","2012-05-08T01:45:55.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-05-02T04:58:14.000+00:00",0.0,0,722.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20355813,723,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","add sort options to MyFiles table",3,"Referring to the discussion in #699: when adding a user to a file, should that entry pop up right above the existing file, or should it popup \"latest added first\"?  Having some logic sort options in the MyFiles table might be helpful in general.  Note that also \"how to display \"multiple file uploads\" will be an interesting one.","2012-05-03T05:29:39.000+00:00","2012-05-03T05:29:39.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,719.0,0,1,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20357863,724,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Authenticated Flash upload displays Guest upload confirmation",2,"After an authenticated upload using Flash, the upload confirmation page presented is that for a Guest (no \"Send File\", \"Guest Voucher\" or \"My Files\" of \"Logoff\" buttons are displayed) but should be the one for an authenticated user, although the upload is still recorded in the \"My Files\" table as sent from \"Me\" - tested using IE9 on Windows7 (VM) and Safari 5.0.5 on Mac OSX 10.6.8, both with Flash 11.2.202.233. The correct confirmation page is still displayed for authenticated uploads with HTML5 - tested with FF 12.0 on Mac OSX 10.6.8. As at r.1416. May be related to #722.","2012-05-03T06:27:01.000+00:00","2012-07-18T13:58:46.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-05-08T01:02:02.000+00:00",0.0,0,723.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20439313,725,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","When issuing voucher no \"Voucher Sent\" message and page does not refresh",2,"When issuing a Guest Voucher, after clicking on \"Send Voucher\" the message \"Voucher Sent\" does not appear and the page does not refresh, although the voucher has been issued and emails generated. This leaves the recipient email address still in the \"Send Vouchers to:\" field, the expiry date as the date selected by the user (if applicable) and the new voucher is not displayed in the table. However if the page is refreshed by the user, the fields reset and the issued voucher appears in the table. Note that if one clicks on the \"Send Voucher\" button a second time before manually refreshing the page, a second voucher will also be issued (and listed in the table when manually refreshed).","2012-05-04T07:11:50.000+00:00","2012-05-07T05:36:31.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-05-07T05:36:31.000+00:00",0.0,0,724.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20572163,726,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","HTML5(Not)Supported tooltip shows raw html code in language tags",3,"Since moving the supported/not supported text to a tooltip under the HTML5 logo the text in the two related language tags is shown in raw form, for example the <br /> tags but also <b> and html entities like &iexcl.\n\nThe relevant code:\nwww/index.php:                  $(\"#html5image\").attr(\"title\",\"<?php echo lang(\"_HTML5Supported\"); ?>\");\nwww/index.php:                  $(\"#html5image\").attr(\"title\",\"<?php echo lang(\"_HTML5NotSupported\"); ?>\");\n\nAnd some 'broken' examples from the current language files (the first one spotted by Wendy):\n\nlanguage/en_AU.php:$lang[\"_HTML5NotSupported\"] = \"Uploads over 2GB<br />not supported!\";\nlanguage/hu_HU.php:$lang[\"_HTML5NotSupported\"] = \"2GB-nál nagyobb fájl feltöltése<br /><b>nem támogatott</b>!\";                   \nlanguage/es_ES.php:$lang[\"_HTML5Supported\"] = \"&iexcl;Permite archivos <b>mayores</b> de 2GB!\";\n\nWe could solve this by changing the varous language tags and restrict their content to unencoded UTF8 characters (no html entities allowed) and strip all html tags.\n\nOr (if possible???) we could use some decoding/parsing function before displaying the two involved language tags (either in PHP or javascript?) Chris, would that be a possiblity?\n\n\n\n\n","2012-05-06T11:59:15.000+00:00","2012-05-09T20:51:27.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-05-09T20:51:27.000+00:00",0.0,0,725.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20779743,727,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Cancel / pause upload using voucher displays authenticated upload page and then rejects valid email address",2,"When the page is refreshed after pausing an HTML5 or Flash upload using a voucher, the url of the refreshed page ends in /index.php?s=upload#. If I am also logged on in another tab, the refreshed page displays \"Welcome [...]\" and all action buttons, while if I am not already logged on the refreshed page presents the Logon page. If I then try to continue (in the case where I am also logged on in another tab) by restarting or resuming the upload, after clicking on \"Send\" the valid email address which had been accepted for the initial upload is rejected \"Invalid or missing email\". Note that if I click on the \"Back\" button in the browser, it takes me to the url for the voucher with \"#\" at the end (with \"Welcome Guest\" and only the \"Help\", \"About\" and \"Logon\" buttons displayed in the header), then if I go back further I reach the initial voucher upload page. Seen using FF 12.0 and Safari 5.0.5 on Mac OSX with Flash 11.2.202.233.","2012-05-08T01:39:26.000+00:00","2012-05-10T02:11:49.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-05-10T02:08:14.000+00:00",0.0,0,726.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20812923,728,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Download page formatting",3,"On the Download page, the message contents text is centred with a green background (whether populated or blank) , in the style of the \"Your file has been uploaded and message sent.\" etc. on-screen message(s). This content should be left-aligned without a background, as per other contents on this page. Also the \"Start Download\" button is now small and left-centred.","2012-05-08T09:54:12.000+00:00","2012-05-09T13:15:15.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-05-08T22:45:27.000+00:00",0.0,0,727.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [20909643,729,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Design of email-workflow",3,"See #704 and #698. As Chris remarked: \"this is important to workflow changes that will happen when we do multiple file upload.\" In general, who gets mail when.","2012-05-09T11:04:36.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:50:25.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-12-03T11:50:25.000+00:00",0.0,0,728.0,0,1,3316353,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:50:25.000+00:00",null]
