tickets, [26116473,754,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.7.6: fix 2 uncovered overlooked output sanitisation issues",3,"Figure 2, Figure 3, linked to eachother, will fix for beta4\n\nFigure 4: we use encoding but might not be best way for particular encoding need at that point in time.  This will be part of structural robustness increase in ticket X\n\nFigure 5: includes/ErrorHandler.php lacks output sanitisation, will fix for beta4.","2012-06-20T08:58:40.000+00:00","2012-07-08T13:31:20.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-07-08T13:31:20.000+00:00",0.0,0,743.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26116873,755,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.2.1: store all temporary, user-uploaded and php “include” files outside the document root",3,"As far as we can tell this is already the case and the documentation seems correct.  Xander will clarify with security auditor where the exact issue is.","2012-06-20T09:04:30.000+00:00","2013-03-03T15:18:24.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2013-03-03T15:18:24.000+00:00",0.0,0,744.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-03-03T15:18:24.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [26117013,756,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 2.10.1: Require users to solve a CAPTCHA when they send many files",3,"Xander: \"Advice doesn't take into account that FileSender should be regarded as a\nMUA, all use of FS is authenticated and is not different from using a\nnormal MUA. Just as with a normal MUA the user has indeed the ability to\nspam. The risk of blacklisting can be mitigated with a configurable\nmax-recipient limit in FS or outside of FS on the sending MTA with\nstandard rate-limiting measures.\n\nUsing CAPTCHA's or comparable is nice for a simple webform where you can\nget to without real authentication but this item from the checklist just\ndoes not apply to FileSender.\"\n\nnote Jan: irrelevant because FileSender has *authenticated* users, and adding captcha adds inconvenience for users. ","2012-06-20T09:06:13.000+00:00","2012-06-20T09:06:35.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2012-06-20T09:06:34.000+00:00",0.0,0,745.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26117663,757,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.11.3: Use the session_regenerate_id() function after switching to a SSL connection.",3,"Xander: \"Currently session_destroy() is used which clears all session variables\n*except* the PHPSESSID. The PHPSESSID cookie *should* be reset with the\nsetcookie(session_name(),'') call but after investigation it appears\nthat that does not work (anymore?) as intended. However adding a expiry\ntime in the past and the 'path' to the setcookie call fixes that and\nforces the client to delete the 'compromised' cookie after which a new\nsession cookie is generated on the SSL-connection. Non-committed patch\nis running on proto\"\n\nSecurity auditors suggestion \"regenerate session id\" is probably not the best solution, what we do (and should do) is to *remove*, destroying all variables on the unsecured session when you move to the secured session.  Patch is now commited, rv1556.\n\nFix will not be applied to 1.1.1.","2012-06-20T09:17:25.000+00:00","2012-07-08T11:06:19.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-07-08T11:06:19.000+00:00",0.0,0,746.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26121303,758,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","ask Thijs about changing default php.ini settings wrt. secure cookies?",3,"now:\n\n; If your FileSender is only available over https (which it should be), enable\n; the following to have secure session cookies\n;\n; session.cookie_secure = On\n; session.cookie_httponly = On\n\nsuggested because default FileSender install already does https and sysadmins need to make an effort to run it on http:\n\n; If your FileSender is only available over https (which it should be), enable\n; the following to have secure session cookies\n;\nsession.cookie_secure = On\nsession.cookie_httponly = On","2012-06-20T09:58:08.000+00:00","2013-03-03T15:38:17.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2013-03-03T15:38:17.000+00:00",0.0,0,6.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-03-03T15:38:17.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [26121403,759,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.11.4: Set the secure flag on the session cookie using session_set_cookie_params().",3,"\"The cookies that hold the session id have to be secured with certain flags. The secure flag instructs the browser to only send a cookie over HTTPS requests. This helps to prevent interception of the session id.\"\n\nThis is a recommendation for PHP-setup (in the supplied php.ini sample\nconfig file) and left to the administrator to enforce or not depending\non the setup. Suggested feature for after 1.5 (configurable like in\nSSP). Was already a known issue and candidate for hardening document.\n\n\n; If your FileSender is only available over https (which it should be), enable\n; the following to have secure session cookies\n;\n; session.cookie_secure = On\n; session.cookie_httponly = On\n\nSee also ticket #758\n\nFor longer term, this would better be enforced by FileSender to prevent \"shoot yourself in the foot\".  SimpleSAMLphp has this, and could possibly be copied.","2012-06-20T09:59:10.000+00:00","2012-10-13T15:40:49.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,748.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26123703,760,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 2.11.2: Use the session_regenerate_id function when the user logs in to prevent session fixation.",3,"Recommendation: At moment of login, re-initialise all variables including php_sessionId to prevent session fixation.\n\nImpact score in audit is low, not deemed directly dangerous for now.  This requires more research and impact analysis, to be done post.1.5 release.\n","2012-06-20T10:09:23.000+00:00","2012-06-20T10:09:34.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,749.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26127153,761,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 2.11.5: Set the httponly flag on the session cookie using session_set_cookie_params().",3,"Is recommendation for PHP-setup. Suggested feature for after 1.5\n(configurable like in SSP). See also 2.11.4.  (#759)","2012-06-20T10:53:29.000+00:00","2012-06-20T10:53:49.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,750.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26127263,762,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.4.3: Set a restrictive anti-caching header",3,"Xander: \"In this case we rely on the defaults of the PHP-setup (which is\nnocache). We should set this explicitly in the code (never rely on\nassumed defaults).\"\n\nChris indicated this to be a simple fix that we'll just do.","2012-06-20T10:55:00.000+00:00","2012-08-30T15:58:04.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-08-30T15:58:04.000+00:00",0.0,0,7.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-08-30T15:58:04.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [26127293,763,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.6.2: Add an access check to the admin page",3,"During discussion it was unclear exactly why this would be an issue.  Xander to clarify with Pine Security.","2012-06-20T10:56:15.000+00:00","2012-10-13T15:47:21.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,752.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-13T15:47:21.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [26127533,764,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.7.2: Change sanitizeFilename to filter out all bad characters",3,"From the report:\n\n\"Issue:\nWhen the user can specify a filename, the application has to check if the filename does not contain unexpected values. For example, allowing a filename like ../file can lead to a \"path traversal\" problem.\n\nResult:\nThe Filesender application properly encodes user input before it is used within filenames. The following function could be improved, since it only replaces the first dot with an underscore, but all user input is hashed with md5 and therefore safe. This checklist item is marked as “Passed”.\"\n\nDeferred because not currently an issue.  For after 1.5: need to make a decision, either drop the function (in practice we use the hash where it matters) or fix it to prevent issues should we ever use the function for anything else.  Client-side the browsers protect users against malicious-filenames-on-download.","2012-06-20T11:00:11.000+00:00","2012-06-20T11:00:25.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,753.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26135833,765,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","remove logtime from database scripts",3,"Well-spotted by Vegard Polden.\n\nWe have a field \"logtime\" that is not used.  It is only present in the database scripts:\n\nscripts/filesender_db.sql:  logtime time with time zone,\nscripts/mysql_filesender_db.sql:  `logtime` time DEFAULT NULL,\n\nChris replies that this is deprecated.  We one time planned to use separate fields for date and time but ended up using one field for both.  So we have to get rid of that field.\n\n-remove the field from both database scripts\n-add to upgrade notes some database command to remove that deprecated field from existing databases\n\nAll of course pending X acknowledge\n\n\n","2012-06-20T12:33:59.000+00:00","2012-06-20T12:34:36.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,754.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
tickets, [26138673,766,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 2.7.6: prevent shoot-in-foot, harden more by also sanitising output not user-generated",3,"So far we made sure output that was the result of user input got sanitised.  A recommendation in the May 2012 security audit is to apply output sanitisation to *all* possible output, making FileSender more hardened against unexpected consequences of changing language files, config files etc. and hardening better against unexpected avenues of attack.\n\nThis requires a systematic effort to go through *all* output generating functionality and:\n\n-check whether output sanitisation is done\n-if not done, apply output sanitisation\n-verify that the most optimal output sanitisation function is applied for that particular context (place in workflow, point in time)\n\n","2012-06-20T12:53:35.000+00:00","2012-06-20T12:53:47.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,755.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,null,null]
