tickets, [26526323,770,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Explore expiry date calculation based on displayed date",3,"Investigate whether different kinds of expiry dates (e.g. tomorrow, configured maximum) can be calculated by Selenium (as suggested by Xander), from the information already provided in the GUI. It is possible to calculate some parameters with Selenium using 'storeEval'. See Selenium documentation sections [[url:http://seleniumhq.org/docs/02_selenium_ide.html#store-commands-and-selenium-variables|Store Commands and Selenium Variables]], [[url:http://seleniumhq.org/docs/02_selenium_ide.html#javascript-and-selenese-parameters|JavaScript and Selenese Parameters]] and [[url:http://seleniumhq.org/docs/02_selenium_ide.html#echo-the-selenese-print-command|echo - The Selenese Print Command]].","2012-06-27T01:37:57.000+00:00","2014-12-22T01:27:12.000+00:00",1051963,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,0.0,0,693.0,0,1,3316333,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-11-28T00:36:26.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [26594903,771,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Improve paging of log display in admin interface for busy installs",3,"As reported by Claude Tompers of RESTENA: \"the page counter for the download logs in my administration section are running out of my screen.\nWouldn't it be better to have something like :\n\n<< First page    < Prev. page    Page X/Y    Next page >    Last page >>\n\nThis would scale better.\"\n\nI agree and this would be a good starting point for improved web-based admin pages.  \n\n\n","2012-06-27T18:09:02.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:03:09.000+00:00",114623,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-02-26T14:03:09.000+00:00",0.0,0,742.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:03:09.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [26636093,772,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","cronjob to periodically clean non-anonomised log table",3,"The current log table grows and grows and grows.  \n\nA scheduled periodic cleanup that throws away entries older than <configurable log-retention period> needs to be implemented.  Deployment wise this fits nicely after we have the working anonimizer (part of the statistics module).  That way we can keep the log data relevant for statistics, and throw away the non-anonimised logging.  A default retention period of 6 weeks sounds sane.\n\nA first thought for implementation: make it part of the existing clean-up cronjob (found in filesender/cron/cron.php).  There's already interaction with the database there.  It would save a FileSender admin the hassle of setting up 2 cronjobs.  \n\nThank you Claude Tompers from RESTENA for reminding us about this one.\n","2012-06-28T10:19:38.000+00:00","2016-02-26T13:20:09.000+00:00",1504963,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-02-26T13:20:09.000+00:00",0.0,0,1.0,0,1,19299663,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T13:20:09.000+00:00",null]
