tickets, [31054363,805,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Unexpected behaviour when clicking on Send multiple times during upload",3,"When 'clicking' (manually or using a script) on the \"Send\" button multiple times (prior to or after the progress bar appears) during an upload, the following has been observed (HTML5 case with Firefox 15.0 on Mac OSX 10.6.8). Xander suggests that this may be a symptom of #641 / #663.\n1. *Clicking again prior to progress bar appearing (authenticated):*  progress bar at multiples of 100% (e.g. 200%, 300% etc), with a horizontal scrollbar (because the progress bar extends beyond the 100%), otherwise as expected.\n2. *Clicking again prior to progress bar appearing (using voucher):* progress bar at multiples of 100% (as above) plus one of the following. The file did not appear in the \"My Files\" table, and no emails were generated to advise that the file had been uploaded. However the voucher could no longer be used and vanished from the \"Guest Voucher\" table.\n- either an error at the top of the page with a green background \"Error accessing server\", or\n- a popup \"You are no longer authenticated. Your session may have expired or there has been a server error. Please logon again and re-try.\". After clicking on OK / the close symbol, the page loaded \"This voucher has already been used.\". Automatically logged off.\n3. *Clicking again after progress bar appearing (authenticated):* each time I clicked on \"Send\" (after the initial click) the error \"Invalid or missing email\" kept appearing under the recipient email address. *The \"Welcome Guest\" page appeared (which should have been \"Welcome [first name surname]\"* with \"Your file has been uploaded and message sent.\". Otherwise as expected.\n4. *Clicking again after progress bar appearing (authenticated):* as per 3., but *voucher was not deleted after use*.","2012-08-31T10:43:12.000+00:00","2012-09-10T08:07:35.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-09-10T08:07:35.000+00:00",0.0,0,765.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-09-10T08:07:35.000+00:00",null]
