tickets, [31421673,812,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Clicking on Send Voucher multiple times issues multiples",3,"If the \"Send Voucher\" button is clicked on multiple times, multiple unique (i.e. different url for each) vouchers and corresponding emails are generated. A message with a green background on the \"Guest Vouchers\" page \"Error accessing server\" also appears momentarily. Observed with Firefox 15.0 on Mac OSX 10.6.8.","2012-09-06T07:14:44.000+00:00","2012-10-18T03:58:47.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-10-13T21:22:47.000+00:00",0.0,0,772.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-13T21:22:47.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [31635783,813,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Remove dependency on php-gmp by simplifying IPv6 check",4,"As suggested (with contributed patch) by Thijs the dependency on php-gmp can be removed by changing/simplifying the chekIp6() function. Can be done with inet_pton() or with the filter_var($ip, FILTER_VALIDATE_IP, FILTER_FLAG_IPV6) function.","2012-09-09T11:06:45.000+00:00","2012-10-13T15:04:17.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-10-13T15:04:17.000+00:00",0.0,0,773.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-13T15:04:17.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [31656483,814,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","A normal Flash upload cancel generates E_ERROR (file NOT moved)",4,"When canceling a Flash upload the temporary file on the server is not available/removed (standard PHP mechanism) and move_uploaded_file() will return FALSE. This is always (regardless of reason) logged on the server as an ERROR in www/fs_upload.php although in this case (and possibly others) it is normal behaviour. This might be improved by looking at the specific reason (see http://www.php.net/manual/en/features.file-upload.errors.php ). For now left as a known issue.","2012-09-10T06:27:42.000+00:00","2012-10-13T21:42:22.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,774.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-13T21:42:22.000+00:00",null]
