tickets, [32450983,819,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upgrade JQuery UI ",1,"Upgrade to jquery-ui-1.8.1.custom.min.js to fix IE Dialogue box dragging and resizing issue","2012-09-20T12:40:05.000+00:00","2014-05-15T06:45:24.000+00:00",3026383,null,",bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2014-04-04T14:39:41.000+00:00",0.0,0,-3.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-04-04T14:39:41.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [32615823,820,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Separate default-expiry-date and max-expiry-date",3,"Currenty we have a max. expiry date which happens to also be the default expiry date.  I'd like to see these two separated, so I can configure them to different values.  Use case: I have customers who'd like to see a longer expiry time, but at the same time I'm pretty sure not all would like to see such a longer expiry time. ","2012-09-21T06:14:46.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:05:03.000+00:00",114623,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-02-26T14:05:03.000+00:00",0.0,0,1.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:05:03.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [32634503,821,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","form autofill (autocomplete) not working",3,"form autofill (autocomplete) is not working.  This turns out to be correct, it doesn't work when you POST using a script.  \n\nAfter discussion with Chris there look to be two complementary ways of solving this.\n\n1. make a hidden form that posts to a hidden iframe or something, to ensure the form data is saved locally in the browser\n2. use jquery autocomplete and query the files database for all To: addresses the particular user has sent to in the past.  Present that in a selectable list that's easy to grasp and use.\n\nThe one issue with (2) is that it becomes less functional should a site operator choose to prune the database for old records.  We can present that in a positive way \"we do this to ensure your address list is always up to date and never polluted with addresses that don't work\".  I don't really know what the user expectation would be so suggest we ask around a bit and try out.\n\nNote: when doing (2) we have to check whether and what kind of database optimisations are needed (!)","2012-09-21T08:10:06.000+00:00","2013-11-01T08:23:19.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2013-08-27T02:14:18.000+00:00",0.0,0,-6.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-08-27T02:14:18.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [33442173,822,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Errors after pausing authenticated upload followed by pausing upload using voucher",3,"If I pause an authenticated upload, then pause an upload of the same file using a voucher, and then:\n* try to resume the authenticated upload of the same file (whether I logged off before starting the upload using the voucher or not), I receive the warning \"Invalid or missing email\" for a valid email address\n* log off and try to resume the upload of the same file using the voucher, I get a popup \"Message. There has been an error - please contact your administrator\".\nObserved with Firefox 15.0 on Mac OSX 10.6.8.","2012-09-28T08:08:59.000+00:00","2012-10-18T05:33:21.000+00:00",394418,null,"aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,0.0,0,776.0,0,1,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-18T05:33:21.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [33786923,823,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","In Chrome: Calendar visible in lower left-hand corner in all pages except admin, always",3,"Reported by Claude Tompers, RESTENA.  \n\nUndesired visibility of the calendar dialogue when using Chrome.  it always shows in the lower left-hand corner in all pages except admin.\n\nClaude says: \"I've added 'display: none' to jquery-ui-1.8.2-custom.css:428 .ui-datepicker { ... } to hide it again.\n\n","2012-10-03T12:11:34.000+00:00","2012-10-18T03:23:54.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2012-10-18T03:23:54.000+00:00",0.0,0,777.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-18T03:23:54.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [36205663,824,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","auto-complete in To: field: allow user to choose default sort order",3,"The currently planned auto-complete feature in the To: field uses system-wide defaults.  Using Chris's suggested \"store user defaults\" functionality we can add this to the lists of defaults a user can change.  Let them pick whether to sort the auto-complete email addresses on \"most recent first\" or on \"alphabetically\".    This ticket depends on:\n\n1. implementing the basic \"allow user to set defaults\" functionality\n2. implementing the \"separate advancaed functionality in the UI\" feature","2012-10-17T12:29:01.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:16:19.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,21.0,0,1,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:16:19.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [36246743,825,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","When canceling upload - show client the server is busy canceling. ",3,"*Wendy Mason:* I've noticed that if I hit Esc while the page is resetting after cancelling an upload [...], with either HTML5 or Flash, the page remains blank. Refreshing the page brings it back though. [...]\n*Chris Richter:* This is a normal reaction of most browsers if the browser is busy and you press escape. What we should do is [...] show the user that the browser is closing off the cancelled file so that they know it is doing something - the typical reason for a user to press cancel is they think the UI is stuck and it looks like no activity is taking place. [... More] to show that we need to take into account the user experience when cancelling and the server (especially with flash) but also HTML5 has to complete it's server side action before reloading the page.","2012-10-17T19:58:14.000+00:00","2013-09-08T22:20:52.000+00:00",394418,null,"","2013-09-08T22:20:52.000+00:00",0.0,0,-2.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-09-08T22:20:52.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [36247213,826,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Consistent key interaction with all popups",3,"* \"Cancel upload\" popup when canceling upload (authenticated and using voucher):* Esc, space, Return, \"X\" and \"No\" close \"Cancel upload\" popup.\n* Re-Send Email / Add new recipient / Delete File / Delete [Voucher]:* Esc, \"X\" and \"Cancel\" / \"No\" close popup; space and Return do nothing.\nNoted by Wendy Mason.","2012-10-17T20:03:40.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:24:59.000+00:00",394418,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2015-12-03T11:24:59.000+00:00",0.0,0,-3.0,0,1,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:24:59.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [36274963,827,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","IE9 mouse pointer keeps spinning after canceling an upload",4,"As spotted by Wendy and confirmed on my Win7 box: when the page resets (with IE9 at least) after cancelling an upload, Selenium doesn't recognise that the page has finished resetting (and times out before advancing to the next step). I had originally thought this was a quirk of Selenium (which doesn't always handle waiting as expected), however I noticed that the mouse pointer keeps spinning. ","2012-10-18T06:00:57.000+00:00","2013-09-08T22:05:51.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb",null,0.0,0,-4.0,0,1,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-18T06:00:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [36471923,828,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Admin page error tab layout",3,"The labels of the 'created' and 'actual error' columns are switched and the actual error is not in the last column but in a separate row. Also the label of the 'actual error' is now _SUBJECT but _MESSAGE might be better (no new tag needed).","2012-10-20T15:09:54.000+00:00","2012-10-20T15:41:04.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-10-20T15:41:04.000+00:00",0.0,0,-5.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-10-20T15:41:04.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [36616783,829,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","# Appearing in Browser Tabs and Browser Title",3,"When pressing a button - some cases show a # symbol in the Browser Title or the Browser Tab title. \nThis is cause by either Flash or Jquery adding a history record to the browser recording a user interaction so that a user can use the back button to \"go back\".\n\nIn many cases we use 'onclick' as part of a href and leave the href as url=\"#\".\nFor consistency - any location that uses a javascript call that does not require the user to have the option of a back button will need the href replaced with a div.\n\n","2012-10-23T06:58:19.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:47:17.000+00:00",394418,null,",aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2015-12-03T11:46:54.000+00:00",0.0,0,-6.0,0,1,19299663,0,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:46:54.000+00:00",null]
