tickets, [36994613,834,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","default.css is not reread by browser after upgrading",3,"Noticed after upgrading from 1.1.x to 1.5-rc1: when the webserver doesn't specify an expiry date of a statc file (.css and .js files for example) the browser will apply its own rules which for .css might lead to long 'expiry' times and can/will lead to a garbled layout because the old style definitions ar read from the browsers cache. A reload of the page will fix that but we probably should add some 'cache buster' to important .css and .js files that contain crucial definitions. A fix should preferably be independent of which webserver or browser is used (i.e. not something that requires a different configuration of the webserver or browser). ","2012-10-27T18:07:40.000+00:00","2012-11-09T09:38:48.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2012-11-09T09:38:48.000+00:00",0.0,0,-9.0,0,1,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-11-09T09:38:48.000+00:00",null]
