tickets, [38190243,857,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Crypto: handling of 'big' files",3,"Test and verify the correct handling of 'big' files, big ranging from 100+ MB to the usual 2+ and 4+ GB files.\n\nTicket triggered by as of yet un-explained behaviour of Chrome 21 (old but capable) on a Mac where local caching seems to interfere and one specific 228M file was consistently incompletely downloaded (missing a few bytes).","2012-11-13T09:06:54.000+00:00","2014-07-10T21:34:49.000+00:00",1379273,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,-19.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,4.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-07-10T21:34:49.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [38299363,858,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Make partial download (Content-Range) possible",2,"Currently the download API only allows for full downloads. Adding the possibility to also use the 'partial download' using byte-ranges (Content-Range) makes it (amongst others) possible to do (in a future client-side implementation) for example pause/resume for downloads. For now this is only a back-end change, it is not used by the frontend and it also does not enable standard 'pause download' browser functionality.","2012-11-14T12:48:55.000+00:00","2013-11-01T08:23:19.000+00:00",3026383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2013-05-10T07:28:39.000+00:00",0.0,0,-5.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-05-10T07:28:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [38336813,859,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","\"E_ERROR: No mapping for en-au found\" when no mapping for default language is found",4,"Under some very specific conditions the logs might get polluted with:\n<pre><code>E_ERROR: No mapping for en-au found. Please check your language configuration.\n</code></pre>\nThis will happen when:\n- a customised config/locale.php does *NOT* contain a mapping for en-au\n- $config['site_defaultlanguage'] is either \"en_AU\" or not defined\n- none of the language tags sent by the browser is found in the customised config/locale.php\n\nThe 'error' here is that the en-au => en_AU.php mapping is not present in the customised config/locale.php\n\nStricty speaking this shouldn't be an error since in all cases FileSender will use the default en_AU.php definitions. The specific error message is meant to detect for example a missing mapping when $config['site_defaultlanguage'] is *not* \"en_AU\" and the corresponding mapping in locale.php is missing.","2012-11-14T20:04:20.000+00:00","2013-09-09T03:11:19.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,-14.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-07-21T22:09:40.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [38725313,860,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Disable page selection button when on the specific page",3,"For example, if you are on the upload page disable the 'Send file' button, if you are on the My Files page disable that one etc.\n\nUse case pro: people who accidently press the 'Send file' button instead of the (much bigger) Send button lose all filled in info\n\nUse case against: the 'Send file' button can be used as a kind of 'refresh'/'clear'\n\n ","2012-11-20T12:51:48.000+00:00","2012-11-20T12:51:48.000+00:00",114011,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,28.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2012-11-20T12:51:48.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [38745953,861,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Crypto: issues with downloads with Chrome on OSX",3,"- Downloading an encrypted file named FILE0003.MOV (all caps) appears to succeed but after the download Chrome doesn't show the usual 'file has been downloaded' interaction. It also isn't listed in the 'Downloads' window. Observerd with various versions (21, 23) on OSX, *not* observed on Windows","2012-11-20T16:07:58.000+00:00","2014-07-10T11:26:13.000+00:00",1379273,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2014-07-10T11:26:13.000+00:00",0.0,0,-19.0,0,0,342706,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-07-10T11:26:13.000+00:00",null]
