tickets, [38880883,863,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Frontend and backend check for invalid filename mismatch",3,"Frontend: if (/^[^\\\\\\/\\:\\*\\?\\\"\\<\\>\\|\\.]+(\\.[^\\\\\\/\\:\\*\\?\\\"\\<\\>\\|\\.]+)+$/.test(name)) \nBackend: preg_match('=^[^/?*;:{}\\\\\\\\]+\\.[^/?*;:{}\\\\\\\\]+$=',$data[\"fileoriginalname\"])\n\nIf for example a ; is used (not detected on the frontend) the backend will return a err_invalidfilename *but* that one somehow isn't shown to the user.\n\nThe regexp mismatch is fixable for 1.5 and will be handled in this ticket. The second problem is more complicated and will be handled under related ticket #864.\n","2012-11-21T23:06:25.000+00:00","2014-10-21T22:20:16.000+00:00",394418,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2013-03-03T14:40:40.000+00:00",0.0,0,-16.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-03-03T14:40:40.000+00:00",null]
