tickets, [39411233,866,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Database Upgrade Code",3,"Notify Admin that database requires upgrading when an upgrade is complete\nStore Database version in database\nProvide admin with the current Install version and database version.\nScript to upgrade current database from 1.x to 1.5.x","2012-11-29T11:14:51.000+00:00","2015-12-03T10:56:39.000+00:00",6605143,null,",dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-89.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T10:56:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [39672403,867,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","No error message when HTML5 upload javascript can no longer read file",3,"Scenario: start large file upload from USB disk, USB disk unplugges, HTML5 upload script can no longer read file, and upload hangs.\n\nWhat probably shoudl happen is that when the next chunk of file being uploaded can't be read, after a certain timeout a dialogue ought to pop up \"having trouble reading file, cancel upload yes/no?\" and maybe even include a \"should I try to resume\" question.  At the very least the user needs to be made aware of the possibility to resume.  Most people won't know this and especially for larger files it would be .... annoying.","2012-12-03T14:37:32.000+00:00","2016-02-07T21:36:50.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-19.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,4.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-09-09T03:08:29.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [39860423,868,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Minimum Include to reduce DB calls in fs_upload",3,"","2012-12-05T11:48:27.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:59:23.000+00:00",394418,null,"","2016-02-26T14:35:15.000+00:00",0.0,0,-51.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:59:23.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [40581713,869,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","space between admins in $config['admin'] means second admin won't have admin access",5,"I noticed that admins need to be entered like this:\n\n$config['admin'] = 'admin1,admin2';\n\nIf you have a space between two admins, like this:\n\n$config['admin'] = 'admin1, admin2';\n\nadmin2 won't have admin access.  Xander, can you confirm this problem?  If it turns out to be a problem, it would be nice to know whether this is something that is fixable or that we need to document in the reference guide.","2012-12-14T10:52:13.000+00:00","2013-03-01T09:53:20.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2013-02-26T18:10:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,-20.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-02-26T18:10:10.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [42380183,870,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","change project organisation page and in particular update funding",3,"consider changing name from \"project organisation\" to \"about\", which would be more in line with where most organisations put their \"about our organisation\" information.  At the very least it appears to make sense to split out funding to a separate wiki page and show funding history.","2013-01-11T14:58:55.000+00:00","2016-02-24T08:34:24.000+00:00",9227153,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-5.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-24T08:34:24.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [44446373,871,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Move footer from hardcoded in index.php to configurable via the language files",3,"Jean-Philippe Evrard, BELNET, suggests to make it easier to modify FileSenders look and feel to the one mandated by his organisation.  A simple change that would make life easier is:\n\n\nIn the filesender www/index.php is this line:\n\"<div id=\"footer\">Version <?php echo FileSender_Version::VERSION; ?></div>\"\n\nI was wondering if you could adapt this in the repository by switching the upper code with this one:\n\"<div id=\"footer\"><?php echo lang('FOOTER'); ?></div>\"\n\nWe could then just adapt in the configuration the footer text.\n\nFor keeping the current fonctionnality, you could add in the default language the following line:\n$lang['FOOTER']='Version '.FileSender_Version::VERSION;\n","2013-01-28T13:55:11.000+00:00","2013-11-01T08:23:19.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2013-08-13T06:42:56.000+00:00",0.0,0,-1.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-08-13T06:42:56.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [44558043,872,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","make it irrelevant to have a trailing / in file paths in config.php",3,"in config.php there are a number of paths that need to be specified:\n \n       // (absolute) file locations\n        $config['site_filestore'] = '/data/terasender/files/';\n        $config['site_temp_filestore'] = '/data/terasender/tmp/';\n        $config['site_simplesamllocation'] = '/var/www/terasender/simplesaml/';\n        $config['log_location'] = '/data/terasender/log/';\n\nRight now, if you omit the trailing '/' in the path, FileSender fails.  Sometimes with an error you can use (like in case of the log dir), sometimes in a less understandable way (like if you omit the / behind the filestore path, it tries to upload and you see a progress bar that just flickers NaN). \n\nIt would be pretty convenient if it didn't matter whether there was a trailing slash or not.","2013-01-29T11:38:48.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:23:12.000+00:00",114623,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-02-26T14:23:12.000+00:00",0.0,0,5.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:23:12.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [44559923,873,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","show remaining dates from previous month in date picker",3,"the date picker displays absolute calendar months.  When you're in say end of January and the default expiry is on 16 February, you'd like to see the January days you can pick as well.  That way you don't need to  go back 1 month to select a date in January.\n\nRequires small modifications to the same files as were needed for ticket #820.\n\nThese two options need to be set:\n\n                $(\"#datepicker\" ).datepicker( \"option\", \"showOtherMonths\", true );\n                $(\"#datepicker\" ).datepicker( \"option\", \"selectOtherMonths\", true );\n","2013-01-29T12:02:28.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:11:03.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-115.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:11:03.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [44754263,874,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Remaining tasks for releasing 1.5-release",1,"* Check trunk for last remaining changesets that need to be merged with branche 1.5 (Xander)\n-ticket 863, frontend and backend check for invalid filename mismatch\n-changeset dealing with including new CSS to prevent garbled layout immediately after upgrading\n\n* Check already merged changesets and update CHANGELOG.TXT accordingly (Xander)\n\n* Update CHANGELOG.TXT and Debian Changelog (Xander)\n\n* Update README (Jan)\n* Update INSTALL (Jan)\n\n* Create release download page\n-highlight changes since 1.1.1, take from changelog.txt\n\n* Fix https://www.assembla.com/spaces/file_sender/wiki/Documentation_v1-5/edit and other \"index\" pages in wiki\n* Update known issues page (Jan, can wait until after release)\n\n* Create \"Upgrade from 1.1.1\" page (Jan)\n\n* Finalise and test Linux install guide\n\n* Put advice about not to put code in publicly accessible directories somewhere in documentation, check security audit for details (Jan)\n\n* Finalise admin ref guide: local overrides, language configuration\n\n* Check remaining bug tickets for 1.5, close those which can be closed, check open ones and reprioritise these for fixing in the months to come.\n","2013-01-30T16:16:48.000+00:00","2014-04-04T15:10:31.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2014-04-04T15:10:31.000+00:00",0.0,0,-21.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-04-04T15:10:31.000+00:00",null]
