tickets, [45308283,877,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","config.php switch for terasender yes/no",3,"implement a \"terasender yes/no\" switch in config.php.\n\nIf switch is yes, use the terasender code when uploading with html5.  If switch is no, use currently available html5 upload code.  \n\nIdea is that the switch is implemented such that when \"no\", no \"new\" upload code is used.  That way we can release the feature asap as an experimental feature: not widely field tested.  But we have to be certain that when switch is \"no\" that well tested code is used.","2013-02-05T19:19:42.000+00:00","2013-03-20T12:40:30.000+00:00",2630333,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2013-03-20T12:40:30.000+00:00",0.0,0,-2.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-03-20T12:40:30.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [45348443,878,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","add option to MyFiles: show which IP address downloaded a file",3,"The current QWA MyFiles shows the dates for when a file was downloaded.  A feature request came in on the feature request forum, by James M: https://filesender.uservoice.com/admin/users/32753502-james-m\n\nIt sounds like a good idea to enable this.  It would fit best in the new MyFiles, the one from QWA.  We already have a list of the dates a file is downloaded on, in the expanded view.  The IP address is stored in the database.  So all we need is:\n-to display the ip address next to the download date, show ipv4 or ipv6 address \n-implement a config.php switch \"show download user ip address in myfiles\" to either show or not show download ip addresses in MyFiles\n\nWe'll start with IP address, but would be good to have a look at whether resolving the ip address makes sense.  It is a bit tricky, as we don't store the resolving  result in the database, so would mean \"live\" resolving resulting in possible slower display of MyFiles, not preferable.  Now that I write this, it sounds like a bad idea to do resolving live.  Might be a nice phase2 change for this functionality, with database change to store resolving result \"on download\".\n\n\n\n\n","2013-02-06T08:34:07.000+00:00","2016-02-26T15:00:28.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-02-26T14:52:45.000+00:00",0.0,0,-119.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T15:00:28.000+00:00",null]
