tickets, [50455663,887,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Filename with ' not accepted in non HTML5 browser",3,"Geoff van Brunt writes \"In non HTML 5 browser, if you try to upload a file with a single quote in it (') the file is not accepted, but no error is returned. It works fine in the HTML 5 version.\"\n\nConfirmed using IE9 on Windows 7 with FileSender 1.5-release.  I used the filename <test' document.rtf> (without the < and >).\n\n\nRelated to #863 from the looks of it.\n\n","2013-04-02T07:48:46.000+00:00","2013-04-14T08:56:57.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2013-04-14T08:56:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,-25.0,0,0,342706,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-04-14T08:56:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [50892183,888,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","PDO rowCount Query Fixes",3,"As reported by Dick Visser:\nIn several places PDOStatement::rowCount was used with a SELECT statement.\nThis seems to work OK for Posgres and MySQL, but it does not for SQLite.\nFrom http://php.net/manual/en/pdostatement.rowcount.php:\n\n\"For most databases, PDOStatement::rowCount() does not return the\nnumber of rows affected by a SELECT statement. Instead, use\nPDO::query() to issue a SELECT COUNT(*) statement with the same\npredicates as your intended SELECT statement, then use\nPDOStatement::fetchColumn() to retrieve the number of rows that will\nbe returned.\"","2013-04-05T16:22:02.000+00:00","2013-11-05T07:01:36.000+00:00",3026383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2013-11-05T07:01:36.000+00:00",0.0,0,-8.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-11-05T07:01:36.000+00:00",null]
