tickets, [57841753,915,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Do not .zip a download if only one file is selected",3,"Currently the multi-file download page will always zip-archive the selected files when the download button is pressed. This is unnecessary and confusing behaviour if only one file has been selected.","2013-06-25T10:35:31.000+00:00","2013-12-07T17:53:00.000+00:00",3839423,null,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","2013-07-02T06:59:36.000+00:00",0.0,0,-6.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-07-02T06:59:36.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [57849833,916,"bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Pause / Resume on (Multi)file Uploads",2," 'Pause/Resume' 'Suspend' and 'Cancel' buttons need to be added to the progress bar dialog box.\n\nPause should *temporarily* stop the uploading of files until the user chooses to resume them (via the same button). Using this will *not* allow the user to resume after leaving this page and is used to relieve the users bandwidth temporarily.\n\nSuspend should make it possible for users to stray away from the transaction and continue it as part of another session, this would be an explicit version of the pause/resume functionality which is currently in place. Users should be warned after choosing 'suspend' of how it works and the steps required to come back to this transaction. This should be paired with functionality which tells users they have a pending upload transaction and should continue to ask them if they wish to either continue with the upload or cancel it. \nThis will only work when the user uses the same browser&computer combination to resume the upload.\nSome way, for example via a button/dropdown list/dialog for the user to access a list of their suspended transactions. This stops the user from having to repopulate the list themselves and would essentially make the uploads page re-appear how they left if (any file uploads complete in that transaction would still be there with complete progress bars). Suspended transactions should have some form of expiration date. Requires validations/error checks to ensure the pending files still exist on disk.\n\nCancel should forfeit the transaction and stop *all* files (both those already finished and those in the queue). Downloads do not have to be paused to be cancelled, but a warning 'are you sure?' should be provided.\n\n\n","2013-06-25T11:46:55.000+00:00","2014-03-26T08:58:55.000+00:00",3839423,null,"bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU",null,0.0,0,-7.0,0,0,3316333,1,3.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-08-15T10:05:36.000+00:00",null]
