tickets, [58280223,933,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Alternating My Files table row color breaks sometimes",4,"I noticed that the alternating coloring (white/light grey) of the new My Files table rows is sometimes wrong. It looks like this is related to the number of downloads for some files. How to repeat:\n- Have three files in the My Files table, don't download any of them (counters are 0), all table rows are 'white'\n- Download the second file in the list one time, reload the My Files page, download counter should be 1, third file now has a light grey background.\n- Download the second file again, reload, counter should be 2, all table rows are white again.\n\nIt looks like the confusion happens when there is an odd number of downloads somewhere in the list.","2013-06-30T11:04:56.000+00:00","2013-11-01T08:23:20.000+00:00",3026383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2013-08-23T19:42:06.000+00:00",0.0,0,-32.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-08-23T19:42:06.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [58344003,934,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Use lang() instead of unlocalised strings ",3,"Go through the multi-file code and replace any UI strings that haven't been localised with calls to lang() (and corresponding entries in en_AU.php).","2013-07-01T13:42:52.000+00:00","2014-04-15T09:59:31.000+00:00",3839423,null,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA,bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU",null,0.0,0,-20.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-07-01T13:43:06.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [58416593,935,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Ensure ZIP files work with most common clients",3,"The ZIP files produced by Zipper.php don't currently work with the Mac OS X Archive Utility. Depending on the value of the \"version needed to extract\" header that is sent with the file, one of two behaviours occurs:\n\n* The .zip file unzips to a .cpgz file, which unzips to a .zip file, which unzips to a .cpgz file, and so on (see [[url:http://linlog.skepticats.com/entries/2012/02/Streaming_ZIP_files_in_PHP.php|here]]).\n* An error message is produced: _Error 2: No such file or directory_\n\nThe unzip terminal command appears to work without reporting any errors.\n\nWe also need to test the files with other common clients. In Windows 7 (x64), both the default Windows Explorer utility and WinRAR are able to handle the files. In Ubuntu 13.04 (x64), the unzip terminal command works fine.","2013-07-02T07:14:22.000+00:00","2013-08-07T06:58:37.000+00:00",3839423,null,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA",null,0.0,0,-21.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-07-23T09:00:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [58417173,936,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Isolate Flash code (for single file uploads) to upload.php",3,"The currently prevailing idea is that pages/multiupload.php will only contain code relevant to multi-file HTML5 uploads, and that all HTML5 capable browsers will be directed to this page. Browsers without HTML5 support will be directed to upload.php which should contain code for the Flash single file upload interface only.","2013-07-02T07:22:20.000+00:00","2013-07-04T07:32:10.000+00:00",3839423,null,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA,bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU","2013-07-04T07:32:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,-22.0,0,0,447388,0,3.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-07-04T07:32:10.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [58417473,937,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Add \"Undo\" functionality to the \"Clear all\" button in multiupload.php",3,"The \"Clear all\" button clears the list of files to upload on the multiupload.php page. Because a user might accidentally hit the button, it should be possible to undo the clear action by clicking it again. ","2013-07-02T07:26:12.000+00:00","2013-07-12T07:48:32.000+00:00",3839423,null,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA,bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU","2013-07-12T07:48:32.000+00:00",0.0,0,-23.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-07-12T07:48:32.000+00:00",null]
