tickets, [60829393,968,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Browser back button page load behaviours",3,"When leaving multiupload.php after filling in the form and then coming back to it (using the browser's back button), the \"files to upload\" box is messed up. See attached screenshot for example. jQuery also throws an error: \"Uncaught Error: cannot call methods on button prior to initialization; attempted to call method 'enable' \".\n\nCases to think about:\n\n* Pressing \"Back\" after successfully uploading a file: the form should be cleared.\n* Closing and reopening the tab/browser to the same page: the form should remember its contents.\n* Going to a different page and then back to multiupload.php (or accidentally hitting the back button while on multiupload.php): the form should remember it's contents.\n","2013-08-01T08:20:52.000+00:00","2014-10-21T22:20:18.000+00:00",3839423,null,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","2013-08-01T09:19:39.000+00:00",0.0,0,-49.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-08-01T09:19:39.000+00:00",null]
