tickets, [62933413,985,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","quick fix for \"no Cc: to downloader\" email",3,"as disussed with Xander: add \"nocc\" to the call to sendEmail in download.php.  This has the effect of NOT sending Cc:s to the downloader, thus taking care of an issue most users complained about one time or another: sending a file to a mailinglist creating a mail storm on download.\n\nThis needs to be a configurable option: \"no_download_cc = yes/no\"\n","2013-08-26T18:15:59.000+00:00","2013-11-05T07:13:27.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2013-11-05T07:13:27.000+00:00",0.0,0,-46.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-11-05T07:13:27.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [62934163,986,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Consistency check auto-complete availability voucher user vs. authenticated user",3,"As noted by Wendy: \"[...] I still feel uneasy about the autocomplete list being available when using a voucher when logged on, as other authenticated features are intentionally NOT made available when using a voucher. Do Jan and Xander still want this feature to be available when using a voucher when logged on?\" (from #821).\n\nWe need to make a consistency check and a decision on what to do with this, preferably as part of beta-2.","2013-08-26T18:23:39.000+00:00","2016-02-26T18:25:28.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-02-26T18:25:28.000+00:00",0.0,0,-8.550000190734863,0,0,19299663,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T18:25:28.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [62934523,987,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","layout consistency check",3,"*Row headings MyFiles*\nPointed out by Wendy: check row headings in MyFiles and compare with Download page \"A small thought ... perhaps the row headings should be unbolded (indicating not requiring action), as per the \"Download\" page? [...]\" (from #597)","2013-08-26T18:26:37.000+00:00","2013-10-30T04:11:36.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2013-10-30T04:11:36.000+00:00",0.0,0,-48.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-10-30T04:11:36.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [63038063,988,"bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU","aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Increase update frequency on html5 uploads",2,"Currently the progress bars only update at the end of a chunk. This is extremely undesirable with slow upload speeds as it seems as though no progress is being made for a very long time (especially if the default chunk size is high).\n\nA working solution for this exists only in the context of Mozilla Firefox (Tested 23.0.1) which has full support for using xhr.upload.onprogress events with Javascript web workers.\n\nThis solution does not apply to Google Chrome (Tested version 29.0.1547.57 m) which has support for xhr.upload.onprogress events but  NOT in the context of web workers (the event will only fire at the end of a chunk, and no time before).\n\nSolution does not apply to Internet Explorer (Tested on version 10.0.92) which does NOT have support for xhr.upload.onprogress events but DOES have limited support for xhr.onprogress but web workers will still not update this constantly, only at the end of a chunk.","2013-08-27T15:55:14.000+00:00","2014-02-03T10:03:47.000+00:00",3839423,null,"bIiF-SXuOr4ydAacwqjQWU,aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA",null,0.0,0,-60.0,0,0,133342,1,7.0,7.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-09-04T10:39:20.000+00:00",null]
