tickets, [63449943,990,"cxFt16lZGr3Q7YeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","admin tab -- two additional alerts",3,"the admin menu, on the \"general\" tab, currently shows a disk usage meter.\nIt would be useful to add a few gauges for use by webmins who don't necessarily have visibility over the lower-lying systems their filesender is running on:\n\n1) a check to show when CRON was last run -- could read something like \"files last flushed on [date/time]\"\n2) a check to see whether filesender still has connectivity to the SMTP server (an EHLO every 10 minutes would suffice)","2013-09-02T11:04:52.000+00:00","2016-01-05T10:42:59.000+00:00",114011,null,"cxFt16lZGr3Q7YeJe5aVNr",null,0.0,0,23.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-05T10:42:43.000+00:00",null]
