tickets, [64005233,999,"d4oZSslSur3R7LeJe5aVNr",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Error message required when HTML5/Terasender upload javascript can no longer read file",3,"Required for both HTML5 and Tera Sender.\n\nScenario: start large file upload from USB disk, USB disk unplugges, HTML5 upload script can no longer read file, and upload hangs.\n\nWhat probably shoudl happen is that when the next chunk of file being uploaded can't be read, after a certain timeout a dialogue ought to pop up \"having trouble reading file, cancel upload yes/no?\" and maybe even include a \"should I try to resume\" question. At the very least the user needs to be made aware of the possibility to resume. Most people won't know this and especially for larger files it would be .... annoying. ","2013-09-09T03:08:04.000+00:00","2016-02-07T21:38:10.000+00:00",3026383,null,"","2016-02-07T21:38:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,-50.0,0,0,19299663,0,1.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-07T21:38:10.000+00:00",null]
