tickets, [66784123,1015,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Reduce number of DB queries made on page load in files.php",3,"The nested table layout in files.php causes a lot of database queries to be made, particularly related to calculating number of downloads per file / per user. This scales poorly as the numbers of transactions, recipients and files increase. Many of the calculations can be performed in PHP code (or pre-calculated with the help of ticket #1014).\n\nAs suggested by Chris, it would also help to only load the basic \"top-level\" data necessary to display the main table on page load, and use AJAX to load the details if/when the user expands a table row.","2013-10-07T14:01:03.000+00:00","2013-10-14T15:05:18.000+00:00",3839423,null,"aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA",null,0.0,0,-84.0,0,0,238024,1,3.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2013-10-14T15:05:18.000+00:00",null]
