tickets, [74799673,1069,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Consider dropping (friendly name in) user greeting",3,"Thijs Kinkhorst from Tilburg University suggested to consider dropping the (friendly name in) the user greeting.  It would simplify the code and would mean less attributes to provision making for an easier deployment.\n\nWe'll do a think about this as part of the 2.0 work.  Mental note: the CN attribute (friendly name) is currently not mandatory to provision to a FileSender installation.","2014-01-09T14:38:04.000+00:00","2014-03-16T21:17:23.000+00:00",3839423,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2014-03-16T21:17:23.000+00:00",0.0,0,-106.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-03-16T21:17:23.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [75118504,1070,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Optional subject not used in upload confirmation to sender ",3,"Try sending a file with \"Email me on upload complete\" ticked and using an optional subject + message.  The email to the recipient uses the subject entered and includes the message.\n\nThe \"upload completed\" email sent to the sender doesn't contain the subject and message entered by the user.\n\nAs a sender of a bunch of files I wondered what happened, so this is probably not what a user would expect.  You'd expect the specific entered subject to be used in both emails.","2014-01-13T12:16:05.000+00:00","2014-01-13T12:16:05.000+00:00",3839423,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aTWq58rMCr4ysmacwqjQXA",null,0.0,0,-107.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-01-13T12:16:05.000+00:00",null]
