tickets, [78797523,1076,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Memory exhaustion with partial download of large files",2,"Chrome 32 and FF 27 will under circumstances request a partial download. With large files the requested byte-range can be too large for the current solution and will trigger a memory limit:\n\nFeb 19 14:04:40 filesender apache2: PHP Fatal error:  Allowed memory size of 134217728 bytes exhausted (tried to allocate 2147483648 bytes) in /usr/share/filesender/www/download.php on line 176\n\nCurrently the whole requested byte range is loaded into memory.\n\nRaising the limit might not be the best solution. Other possible solutions:\n\n- chunk the requested range (as with a full download) ?\n- disable it for now?\n- ???","2014-02-19T13:46:30.000+00:00","2014-04-04T14:09:40.000+00:00",3026383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2014-04-04T14:09:40.000+00:00",0.0,0,-71.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-04-04T14:09:40.000+00:00",null]
