tickets, [80443893,1082,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","New feature suggestion: transaction audit trail",3,"Consider an audit trail functionality.\n\nOne way to implement this is to show a historical MyFiles.  Disadvantage: requires audit trail data to hang around.  That's contrary our wish to retain least possible sensitive data on the FileSender service.\n\nAnother and  possibly easier way: once the transaction expires, wrap the entire transaction history in a PDF and ship it to the sender.  This PDF could be timestamped and signed to provide strength to the audit trail.  \n\nThis would be accompanied by a config option that says \"always on\" or \"user override\", and in case of the latter would either tick it by default or leave it open by default.  A service admin would need to be able to indicate whether this optoin is part of the standard \"always show\" options or not.","2014-03-10T11:46:26.000+00:00","2014-03-10T11:46:26.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,25.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2014-03-10T11:46:26.000+00:00",null]
