tickets, [90021653,1094,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Classes design",3,"Etienne proposes a number of changes to the classes that'll allow us to use the PHP object model: all data interaction would take place via an object abstraction layer.  For example interacting with a voucher would go via a voucher object.  This'll make it much easier to add new features and will make the code more modular.\n\nEtienne, I created a wikipage for this work here:\nhttps://www.assembla.com/spaces/file_sender/wiki/Classes_design_v2-0","2014-06-19T12:26:57.000+00:00","2015-11-09T10:55:10.000+00:00",6499953,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-11-09T10:55:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,-3.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-09T10:55:10.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [90021793,1095,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Database design document",3,"In addition to changes in the classes design for 2.0 we figure some changes in the database will make the code clearer and more modular.  In particular separating out the vouchers table from the files table and adding a table for user attributes will help our quest for easier-to-add-to code.  The database design will be documented at https://www.assembla.com/spaces/file_sender/wiki/Database_design_v2-0","2014-06-19T12:28:42.000+00:00","2015-11-09T11:28:40.000+00:00",6499953,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-11-09T11:28:40.000+00:00",0.0,0,-4.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-09T11:28:40.000+00:00",null]
