tickets, [91055453,1105,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","avZvqm96Gr47ZdacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Incorporate recommendations from code security audit",3,"Pine Security executed a code security audit on 2.0-alpha-summer2013 code and made a number of recommendations to improve security in-dept.  Roman has the report as well as the analysis by the FileSender team.  These security in-depth recommendations need to be implemented in the 2.0 code base as part of the class/database refactoring effort.\n\nWhat we should have after the refactoring effort is a 2.0 fundament that is solid *and* as secure as we can make it.","2014-07-02T11:34:31.000+00:00","2015-11-09T10:56:07.000+00:00",6499953,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,avZvqm96Gr47ZdacwqEsg8","2015-11-09T10:56:07.000+00:00",0.0,0,-10.0,0,0,3316353,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-09T10:56:07.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [91066213,1106,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","HTML5 uploads with FireFox and Chrome no longer work with 2.0",3,"Since at least two weeks ago (half-way in May) uploads with FireFox and Chrome stopped working with the current 2.0 prototype (see https://terasender.uninett.no/)\n\nThey still work on the FileSender 1.6 code though.  That seems to indicate it's not directly related to the terasender upload code.  I do remember Jack implemented a new way for processing progress events from web workers in 2.0.  This meant that progress events when using FireFox or Chrome came a lot more often, which worked especially well with large uplaods or uploads over slow lines.\n\nMy guess is something changed in the way FireFox and Chrome deal with progress events in web workers.  This bug does need to be found & fixed after the class refactor is done.","2014-07-02T13:24:53.000+00:00","2015-03-27T16:56:31.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-27T16:56:31.000+00:00",0.0,0,-2.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-27T16:56:31.000+00:00",null]
