tickets, [109486653,1154,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Add documentation for bounce handling (general explain + config directive)",3,"Add feedback email handling script and bounce handling related default config.\n\nScript can be called as :\n    \n    php cron/emailfeedback.php [options] [sources]\n    \n    options are :\n      * --remove_after_processing : remove file after processing\n      * --move_after_processing[=target] : move file to target folder after processing, if no absolute target will be considered to be under source folder, if no target given \"done\" source subfolder\nis used by default\n    \n    sources can be (several may be used at the same time) :\n      * a path to a file containing a rfc822 message\n      * a path to a folder containing rfc822 message files\n      * - to get rfc822 message from standard input\n    \n    if no sources are defined standard input is used by default\n\nNew config parameters related to bounce handling :\n\nreport_bounces, bounces reporting mode, possible values are :\n  - null / false / 0 : bounce reporting disabled (bounces are still saved and displayed in ui, just not reported by email)\n  - asap : report every bounce right away (default)\n  - daily : compile a daily report for each transfer/guest (handled by cron/cron.php)\n  - asap_then_daily : bounces in a time range (see report_bounces_asap_then_daily_range) after transfer/guest creation are reported right away, bounces comming after are reported daily\n\nreport_bounces_asap_then_daily_range, time range for asap reporting in asap_then_daily bounce reporting mode, in seconds, defaults to 15 minutes\n\n\n\nFiles Affected:\nA /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/cron/emailfeedback.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/includes/ConfigDefaults.php\n\nCommit from user: etiennemeleard\n\n.............................................................................\nMore details at:\nhttps://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/changesets/3271\n","2015-01-21T14:27:22.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:21:39.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-3.0999999046325684,0,0,133342,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:21:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [109486953,1155,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document access web service as remote user (!= remote application)",3,"Add to general API documentation (?) and config directives if needed.\n\n\"Add a way to use webservice as a remote user (!= remote application).\n\nIt must be enabled using the auth_remote_user_enabled configuration parameter (boolean, false by default).\n\nIt uses a signed request (same as remote applications), the only difference is that each user have its own secret (stored as a preference).\n\nSecrets can be automatically generated by setting auth_remote_user_autogenerate_secret configuration parameter to true (false by default).\n\nIt will allow to setup per-user based trust relationships between a filesender instance and other, potentially non-web based, applications.\n\nUse case is a Thunderbird plugin which allows to put big files on filesender, user installs the plugin and give its secret to it, then the plugin can upload files on behalf of the user.\n\nSample php client has been updated to be able to use either remote application or remote user authentication.\n\n\n\nFiles Affected:\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/auth/Auth.class.php\nA /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/auth/AuthRemoteUser.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/data/User.class.php\nA /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/exceptions/AuthRemoteUserExceptions.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/includes/ConfigDefaults.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/scripts/client/FilesenderRestClient.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/scripts/client/FilesenderRestClientExample.php\n\nCommit from user: etiennemeleard\n\n.............................................................................\nMore details at:\nhttps://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/changesets/3396\"","2015-01-21T14:30:41.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:21:39.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-3.0999999046325684,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:21:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [109487043,1156,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document user preference framework start",3,"Date: Mon, 12 Jan 2015 18:51:16\nFrom: etiennemeleard <file_sender@alerts.assembla.com>\nReply-To: filesender-alerts@filesender.org\nTo: \"filesender alerts user adminned by Jan (filesender-alerts)\" <filesender-alerts@filesender.org>\nSubject: [filesender-alerts] [Assembla] [File sender] Changeset [3397]: Add a configurable user profile page (disabled by default).\nParts/Attachments:\n   1 Shown    48 lines  Text\n   2   OK     35 lines  Text\n----------------------------------------\n\nChangeset alert by etiennemeleard in project FileSender \n\n.............................................................................\n\nAdd a configurable user profile page (disabled by default).\n\nThe goal is to create a framework for user preferences managment.\n\nTo enable it set the \"user_page\" configuration parameter to an array containing <preference_id> : <view_mode> pairs.\n\nView modes can be \"read\", \"write\" or false (same as not set, that is will not be displayed).\n\nSupported preferences are :\n\n  - lang (requires lang_userpref_enabled to true) : supports read and write\n  - auth_secret (requires auth_remote_user_enabled), supports only read\n  - created, supports only read\n\n\n\nFiles Affected:\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/data/User.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/endpoints/RestEndpointUser.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/includes/ConfigDefaults.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/language/en_AU/lang.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/language/fr_FR/lang.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/templates/menu.php\nA /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/templates/user_page.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/css/default.css\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/index.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/js/client.js\nA /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/js/user_page.js\n\nCommit from user: etiennemeleard\n\n.............................................................................\nMore details at:\nhttps://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/changesets/3397\n","2015-01-21T14:31:42.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:21:39.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-3.0999999046325684,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:21:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [109487333,1157,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document custom transfer validator",3,"Date: Tue, 13 Jan 2015 11:04:52\nFrom: etiennemeleard <file_sender@alerts.assembla.com>\nReply-To: filesender-alerts@filesender.org\nTo: \"filesender alerts user adminned by Jan (filesender-alerts)\" <filesender-alerts@filesender.org>\nSubject: [filesender-alerts] [Assembla] [File sender] Changeset [3398]: Add a way to specify custom transfer validator to conduct further checks after usual checks (size, number of recipien...\nParts/Attachments:\n   1 Shown    50 lines  Text\n   2   OK     30 lines  Text\n----------------------------------------\n\nExample of use: if you have a filesender install where you _only_ want to see big files, you should be able to decline transfers < 100 MB.\n\nAlso useful for creating blacklists of users.\n\nChangeset alert by etiennemeleard in project FileSender \n\n.............................................................................\n\nAdd a way to specify custom transfer validator to conduct further checks after usual checks (size, number of recipients ...)\n\nThis is configured using the transfer_validators configuration parameter which must be an array of callables.\n\nEach test gets the transfer object as sole argument and can either return false (reject without reason given) or throw a standard exception with a translatable id as message (messages can easily be\ntranslated in config lang files overrides).\n\nExample :\n\n$config['transfer_validators'] = array(\n    function($transfer) {\n        $blacklist = array_filter(explode(\"\\n\", file_get_contents(FILESENDER_BASE.'/config/blacklist.txt')));\n        \n        return !in_array(Auth::user()->id, $blacklist);\n    },\n    function($transfer) {\n        if(!count(array_filter($transfer->files, function($file) {\n            return $file->size > 10 * 1024 * 1024;\n        })))\n            throw new Exception('you_must_have_at_least_one_file_over_10mb');\n    }\n);\n\n\n\nFiles Affected:\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/exceptions/TransferExceptions.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/endpoints/RestEndpointTransfer.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/language/en_AU/lang.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/language/fr_FR/lang.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/js/ui.js\n\nCommit from user: etiennemeleard\n\n.............................................................................\nMore details at:\nhttps://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/changesets/3398\n","2015-01-21T14:34:46.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:21:40.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-3.0999999046325684,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:21:40.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [109487403,1158,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document option to get a link for download instead of sending to recipient",3,"Date: Tue, 13 Jan 2015 14:20:18\nFrom: etiennemeleard <file_sender@alerts.assembla.com>\nReply-To: filesender-alerts@filesender.org\nTo: \"filesender alerts user adminned by Jan (filesender-alerts)\" <filesender-alerts@filesender.org>\nSubject: [filesender-alerts] [Assembla] [File sender] Changeset [3400]: Adding an option to get a link for download instead of sending to recipient (disabled by default).\nParts/Attachments:\n   1 Shown    48 lines  Text\n   2   OK     38 lines  Text\n----------------------------------------\n\nChangeset alert by etiennemeleard in project FileSender \n\n.............................................................................\n\nAdding an option to get a link for download instead of sending to recipient (disabled by default).\n\nWhen using this an anonymous recipient is created (that is, without email) and its download link is given back to the uploader at the end of upload.\n\nWhen using this option the user can embbed the link in any mail of his choice (newsletter for example), all downloads are obviously counted as done by the single anonymous recipient.\n\nThis mode will be helpful for people wanting to use their FileSender server from another application (like big attachments handling in mail clients).\n\nThis option must be enabled in the transfer_options configuration associative array under the name get_a_link (advanced mode is ignored as well as default).\n\nAlso adding user id in user page (if enabled).\n\n\n\nFiles Affected:\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/constants/TransferOptions.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/data/Recipient.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/data/Transfer.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/endpoints/RestEndpointRecipient.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/endpoints/RestEndpointTransfer.class.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/language/en_AU/lang.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/language/fr_FR/lang.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/templates/transfers_table.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/templates/upload_page.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/templates/user_page.php\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/css/default.css\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/js/transfer.js\nM /filesender/branches/filesender-2.0/www/js/upload_page.js\n\nCommit from user: etiennemeleard\n\n.............................................................................\nMore details at:\nhttps://www.assembla.com/code/file_sender/subversion/changesets/3400\n","2015-01-21T14:36:13.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:21:40.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-10-23T09:38:44.000+00:00",0.0,0,-3.0999999046325684,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:21:40.000+00:00",null]
