tickets, [111677123,1165,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","FireFox upload hangs with 30 workers",3,"If you set the number of webworkers to be used to 30, uploading works fine with Safari and Chrome, but not with FireFox.  Confirmed on UNINETT and DeIC 2.0 test install.  Symptom: just nothing happens and nothing is logged.\n\nSet the number of workers to 16 and it also works with FireFox.\n\nEtienne provides following feedback:\n\nThe mechanism in a terasender upload is as follows:\n- a worker requests a job with the terasender job driver\n- the job driver locks (sets boolean in itself) so it doesn't respond to multiple workers.  If another worker tries to access it it tells the other worker to wait.  This ensures no chunk is given to two workers.\n- the driver gives a worker an answer; either \"here is a chunk for you\" or \"nothing more to do\".\n\nif this messaging mechanism breaks down nothing will work.\n\nThoughts:\n- maybe past a certain number of workers with each worker waiting for .5 seconds, with a lot of workers it may be just waiting?\n- maybe there's some overflow in the messaging system in FireFox?\n- upon checking the upload console: every worker is requesting a job.  First worker is given file, other worker gets “nothing to do” as a response.  Are expected to close.  First worker doesn’t even signal worker is complete.  Past specific number of workers the browser starts to handle events in a bad way.\n-Is the bug related to max number of workers or to large number of workers combined with async uplods?\n-what is the breaking number?  \n-maybe there is a limit in the global amount of “work” FireFox can do?  That Safari and Chrome doesn’t have?  Does messaging just break down?\n\nEtienne will take following actions:\n- test to see if there is a specific fixed breaking point in # webworkers\n- check Mozilla email list for similar issues and write email asking others if they've seen similar things\n- post on Stack overflow\n\nThis is not a high priority issue at the moment: just don't set the #webworkers to 30 does the trick.  But we need to figure out what causes this.  If it's a firefox bug it should be fixed.  If it is some issue in our code it should be fixed.  \n\nFor the 2.0-alpha we will -unless we find out what causes it- label this as a known issue for now.","2015-02-11T11:38:38.000+00:00","2015-02-11T11:38:38.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-12.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-02-11T11:38:38.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [111677843,1166,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Consider drag & drop enable whole screen",3,"At the moment the boxed-in area of the filesender application (the area currently in white) is drag & drop sensitive.  The black area around it is not.  From a user perspective it may be preferable to have the entire window (or tab) be a drop zone.\n\nThere might be reasons for not having the entire screen be a drop zone, there might be good reasons to limit drag & drop to a specific area.  Etienne to investigate.","2015-02-11T11:46:02.000+00:00","2015-09-17T08:54:49.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-09-17T08:54:49.000+00:00",0.0,0,-13.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-09-17T08:54:49.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [111679683,1167,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","A chunk was sent after transfer complete resulting in an error",3,"Symptom: the upload succeeds, mails are sent, but there is still an error both to user + in the logs on server side.\n\nUpload of a 5GB file on terasender.uninett.no/branches/filesender-2.0/  The upload was with Safari.  That instance is now configured with 6 webworkers.  I did the upload over the WLAN.\n\nA couple of times the message was displayed \"slower than usual, try again, quit etc.\".  I clicked try again, it hopped a bit back in\nprogress and the progressed.\n\nAt the end, the progress bar indicated the upload was complete, I got the download email, and I got an error (enclosed in this mail)\nthat there was a problem.\n\nIn the logs server side I can see there's a problem logged.\n\nOn disk the file appears to be all there:\n-rw-r--r--  1 www-data www-data 5368710144 Feb  9 11:35 397b17f7-bccf-a1d8-c600-41d72a7ca092\n\nIt also downloads again:\n-rw-r--r--@   1 meijer  staff  5368710144 Feb  9 11:18 testfile-5GB+1byte-2.dat\n\nEtienne's analysis:\n\n* When last worker finishes: triggers file complete request.  When all files are complete, transfer complete request is sent.  Normally triggers mail sending etc.\n* After this transfer complete request was sent another chunk was sent.  The webservice doesn’t accept chunks after a transfer complete is sent.  the client should NOT send chunks after transfer complete.\n* this MAY happen in one case only, with the automatic restart of stalled transfers.\n* There are TWO automatic restarts of a transfer before asking whether a transfer should restart so a user won't see if a transfer restarts only once\n\nThere might be a situation where the transfer is both complete and restarted.  Etienne will add more logging to see if restarts have an unfortunate timing.\n\nThis is a bug we need to fix.","2015-02-11T12:07:40.000+00:00","2015-02-11T14:21:01.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-14.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-02-11T12:07:40.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [112018453,1168,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feature: email daily summary to sender of transaction",3,"This feature gives the sender of a transaction the option to receive a daily update of what happened with the transfer.  Who downloaded what when, a \"transaction expired\" when the transaction expires etc.  The sender can tick the feature when initiating the transfer.  Cron ensures it's sent daily.\n\nConfiguring this is done through the transfer options.  As a service provider you should be able to indicate whether:\n- the option is available to a user\n- the option is ticked by default (or not)\n- the option is always visible in the upload form or hidden under the \"advanced\" link\n\n","2015-02-16T09:39:05.000+00:00","2016-02-10T13:21:03.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-15.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-10T13:20:59.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [112165623,1169,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Crypto: 'send' button doesn't work when upgrading to crypto version",3,"js/upload.js is not always re-fetched by browser","2015-02-17T14:30:03.000+00:00","2015-02-17T14:34:18.000+00:00",1379273,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb",null,0.0,0,-49.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-02-17T14:34:18.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [112292443,1170,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feature: in-app messaging",3,"In-app messaging:\npart are generated by client itself during upload process\npart come from server\n\nWhen upload is done: if you want to redirect user to transfer page we have to have a way to propagate message through URL.  Would need URL parameter which gives message identifier to display and some way to pass parameters: parameter complete but depending on transfer options may need some other things as well.\n\nCould display message in upload page.  But would then lose message.\n\nTwo-sided problem:\nin-app messaging area makes sense and easy to do for messages from server \nusing it to also display client-workflow related messages is a challenge.","2015-02-18T18:57:36.000+00:00","2015-10-23T09:36:33.000+00:00",114011,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,24.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-23T09:35:49.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113619103,1171,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.6.13: Generated passwords and tokens must not be predictable",3,"*Issue:* vulnerability: FileSender uses random numbers and identifiers in various places, for example in the download URL.  The reviewd 2.0 codebase uses uniq_id and mt_rand.  Both don't return a sufficiently secure random number which may result in an attacker guessing the state of the random generator.  An attacker might thus be able to guess download URLs and CSRF tokens.  Recommend to use secure random generator.\n\n*Assessment:* Issue confirmed and needs to be addressed before the 2.0 release.  Preferably without using openssl as it would add a dependency and be about 100 times (ballpark figure)  slower than using the other random generator.\n\nThe unique identifiers used in FileSender need to have two characteristics:\n•\tthe ID must be unique\n•\tthe ID must be non-guessable.  As long as you can't guess the random number in the ID you can't guess the random generator state.  \n\nFor the FileUID we check uniqueness, if a collision occurs we generate a new one.   To make the ID non-guessable Pine recommends a HMAC.  The recommendation is to use a secure random number generator like openssl but using for example /dev/urandom or mtrand and hash that combined with a salt value to an HMAC is sufficiently secure.  FileSender would need to auto-generate the salt value.\n\nPine comments that wile an attacker in this way won't be able to directly know the random number you have to be very careful you don't leak random number to user somewhere. \n\n*Response:*  Etienne will add HMAC with a random generated salt and look at making it configurable to read urandom or use mt_rand.\n","2015-03-06T16:02:09.000+00:00","2015-03-11T11:03:16.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-03-11T11:03:16.000+00:00",0.0,0,-17.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-11T11:03:16.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113620243,1172,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Securit audit 1: 2.7.1: User input must be encoded in the context where it is used",3,"*Issue:* _defence in depth:_ when FileSender receives user input the function sanitizeInput is used to ensure the input will not contain anything that will be executed.  This function currently filters the input for a number of dangerous characters and adds a space to them. Pine recommends to use escaping, the current code uses filtering.\n\nFiltering changes the input and might lead to unexpected side-effects.\n\n*Assessment*: Etienne's collegues in the Sympa mailinglist software project had a security audit executed where an issue was found using variable encoded string injection.  The offending string had to be machine-generated.  This string defeated perls regexp-based entity encoding mechanism.  The php mechanism behaved the same.  Sympa introduced a filtering fix which was reported in this FileSender audit.  \nThe filtering fix was based on a blog-article published on OWASP as a recommendation.  Unfortunately the blog article is now no longer accessible. \n\nDaan indicated he's unaware of any technique to bypass html_entities.  He tested by removing the line of code and injection of code was not possible.  The strong recommendation is to not filter on input; you don't know where the data will be used.\n\n*Response:* there is not yet consensus in the FileSender core team on the best approach.  Based on the experience of the Sympa mailinglist software team escaping alone might not be enough.  The issue found in the Sympa security audit might now have been fixed and the filtering fix no longer needed.  We will await the results of the 2nd security audit and then decide what to do.  We will address this before the 2.0 release.\n","2015-03-06T16:12:37.000+00:00","2015-03-27T17:00:58.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-18.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-11T11:01:41.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113620963,1173,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.7.3: User input must be encoded before it is used in path/filenames",3,"*Issue:* defence in depth: filenames were not escaped when used in a certain piece of code.  This was not an actual vulnerability as in the offending code it wasn't user supplied input but the overall security of the software would improve by ensuring escaped filenames, just in case the piece of code might be called in the future with user-supplied input.  \n\nAs a general recommendation: don't rely on input, and when handling input don't rely on the difference between user input and application input as roles might changes in future code.\n\n*Assessment:* the recommendation is sound.  In this particular case the offending code no longer exists.\n\n*Response:* none needed","2015-03-06T16:17:56.000+00:00","2015-03-12T16:46:03.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-03-12T16:46:03.000+00:00",0.0,0,-19.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-12T16:46:03.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113749713,1174,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.7.4 User input must be encoded before it is used in SQL commands",3,"*Issue*: _defence in depth, no vulnerability_.  Nearly all SQL commands are done using prepared statements but Daan found a number of places where variables were used in SQL commands.  The end user currently has no control over the contents of those variables but this might happen in future services.  As a general rule we should use prepared statements, don't trust input.  If we don't use prepared statements use some kind of escaping.  Cast it to an int or add escaping before printing it to a variable.\n\n*Assessment*: we use prepared statements where we can but prepared statements don't support \"in\" statements.   \n\n*Response*: Etienne will investigate whether he can construct a function that prepares a prepared statement. \n","2015-03-09T13:55:12.000+00:00","2015-03-09T13:56:57.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-09T13:56:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,-20.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-09T13:56:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113750093,1175,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.7.7: User input must be encoded before it is used in HTML output",3,"*Issue:* _vulnerability without accessible attack surface:_ there is one single case of javascript injection where not all outputs are escaped; the code allows for specification of  a REST API callback handler for iframe integration. Currently the user doesn't have any control over all inputs but might have this in future versions.\n\n*Assessment:* this is considered part of a feature which enables an application integrator to give return data to a handler of your choice idea is you give return data to handler of your choice.  Being able to point to an existing function or object method from a parent window is to be expected.  \n\n*Response:* during the discussion of the issue Etienne suggested to limit what you can give as callback.  Letters, digits, dash and underscores.  This addresses the issue.   Daan confirms.\n","2015-03-09T13:58:13.000+00:00","2015-03-09T13:59:46.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-09T13:59:46.000+00:00",0.0,0,-21.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-09T13:59:46.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113750963,1176,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.11.8: Anti-clickjacking measures must be implemented",3,"*Issue:* _vulnerability:_ there is no protection against click-jacking nor do we mention clickjacking as a risk anywhere in the installation documentation.  Recommendation is to set the x-frame-header in each request or same-origin, allow-from in the webserver config and/or document in the manual what to do if iframes are allowed.  Either we document the risks with using iframes or ensure they can't be used.\n\n*Assessment*: this is both a risk and a feature.  Integrating FileSender using an iframe is a feature.  Should you want to limit inclusion of FileSender in iframes, preliminary investigation suggests W3C's candidate recommendation Content Security Policy (CSP, http://www.w3.org/TR/CSP2/) is the standards-based way to do this.  According to http://caniuse.com/#feat=contentsecuritypolicy this is supported on most currrent browsers.  IE11 is supported by adding X-Content-Security-Policy. Daan suggests to set the same-origin header in the Apache config.   \n\n*Response*: as this is both a feature and a vulnerability we will not enforce this in the FileSender application.  We will use CSP to allow for fine-grained protection.  Rather than implement a swath of config options in FileSender we will document how to configure CSP in Apache for use with FileSender to prevent inclusion in iframes.\n","2015-03-09T14:03:52.000+00:00","2016-03-17T15:21:02.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-22.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-09T14:04:29.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113780123,1177,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.14.2: PHP object injection",3,"*Issue:* _defence in depth:_ when an exception occurs a user is redirected to a page with a serialised array containing information about the exception.  This array is unserialised and used to generate an exception object.  User input can be used when serialising and unserialising arrays.  A user can also give the application an object in this way; the application will happily unserialise object upon which the PHP interpreter will automatically call several functions on that object, e.g. wakeup, destruct, etc.   This has an unknown impact on application.  At the moment this can not be exploited but it might be exploitable in future FileSender versions.  For defense-in-depth this should be addressed.\n\n*Assessment:*\tissue confirmed. This can not be exploited now  as there is no code like wakeup or destruct that does anything when called but this might become a problem in the future.  This will be addressed by using JSON.  Daan agrees this is a good solution.\n\n*Response:* json serialisation will be used to avoid potential code injection when using native serialise/unserialise.  \n","2015-03-09T18:24:15.000+00:00","2015-03-11T07:48:05.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-11T07:48:05.000+00:00",0.0,0,-23.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-11T07:48:05.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113931733,1178,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.14.3: Template injection",3,"*Issue:* _exploitable vulnerability_:  possible to use template tags on user input which would be displayed in user output.  Could enter tag for database password on input and user would then get the password nicely displayed in output.\n\n*Assessment:* oops!\n\n*Response:* will fix by replacing template tags before inserting any user data.   \n","2015-03-11T07:50:25.000+00:00","2015-03-11T07:51:21.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-11T07:51:21.000+00:00",0.0,0,-24.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-11T07:51:21.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113931933,1179,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit 1: 2.14.4: Usage of variable variables",3,"*Issue:* _defence in depth:_ the \"variable variables\" technique is used in the template parser where variables are dynamically created.  This may lead to a situation where a user can overwrite any variable in the current symbol table like a path variable and include a php script controlled by the user like a php script included in a URL.  At the moment this is not exploitable as the user doesn't control the keys that are provided with the vars parameter.   In future versions this might change. \n\nPine recommends to switch to a different mechanism like a key/value store.\n\n*Assessment:* This is currently not a problem as there is no flow that allows a user to call the template method.  Implementing a  key/value store approach makes writing templates heavier.  For the time being we will keep this as it is and gather practical experience with the template mechanism.\n\nDetails: In the template class there's a method that when called renders a template.  This method looks for a template, resolves the template path (is it in the config directory because it's a customised template or is it in the default template directory?).  Then it includes that template file if found while creating on the fly a set of varilables that the template will use.  The method is given an associated array of key-value pairs (foo=bar) and creates variables for use in the template with name 'foo' and value 'bar'.     .  It could become\n\nissue confirmed and needs to be addressed.  Using a key/value store approach makes writing templates heavier.  Hesitating between rewrite using some kind of keystore or filtering given variables before creating variables so they don't contain unexpected stuff like globals etc., path variable.  The latter approach is error-prone, every time we introduce variable we also need to update the filter.\n\nWhen rendering for example a report at end of upload, the template process method with template name \"report\" can have a variable report=array of report objects.  In template code this then allows for a construct like \"foreach $report as report do ....\".  \n\nThis mechanism is to make for easier template writing.   It is currently not directly exploitable and needs significant other bad programming practice to make this exploitable. \n\nA possible future exploit: if at some point user input is fed directly to the template processing function, it could give a set of variables that could have post data.\n\n*Response:* this is not exploitable and needs significant bad programming practice to make it exploitable.  We will gain practical experience with the template mechanism to see if the balance ease of use vs. security in depth needs to be different in future versions. \n","2015-03-11T07:52:49.000+00:00","2015-03-11T11:20:01.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-11T11:20:01.000+00:00",0.0,0,-25.0,0,0,3316353,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-11T11:20:01.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113932133,1180,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security audit: 2.14.5: Usage of PHP weak comparison",3,"*Issue:* _vulnerability, not directly exploitable_: in most parts of the cost weak comparison is used.  PHP will try to guess the type of variable on both sides and when possible will make an integer comparison (php default) which in some situations could lead to bypassing certain filter or check.  If comparing two strings where first string is very large number and second string is also very large number then php will think they are alike.  Lets convert it to integer and make comparison.  Recommendation: always use strict comparison.  \n\n*Assessment:* oops.\n\n*Response:* will fix.\n","2015-03-11T07:54:19.000+00:00","2015-03-11T10:17:36.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-11T10:17:36.000+00:00",0.0,0,-26.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-11T10:17:36.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [113944983,1181,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security: check for possible attack using template code in file names",3,"After considering the filename issue that popped out of the 1st security audit (ticket #1173) Etienne wonders about another possible issue: using template code in file names.\n\nAs with any other user data we run filenames through html_entities before displaying.  XSS injection and such should be fine.  But we are not running it through template code protection.  An attacker might be able to upload file with a filename containing template compatible code {cfg:databaseword} and do Wrong Stuff like displaying the database password.  Measures to protect against this were implemented in the web interface but not in emails, including the user message.  \n\nEtienne will check whether this is an issue and if needed fix it","2015-03-11T10:25:11.000+00:00","2015-03-12T16:45:37.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-12T16:45:37.000+00:00",0.0,0,-27.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-12T16:45:37.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [114530893,1182,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feature: maintenance mode",3,"This allows to interrupt the service for database upgrade or even server restart without breaking uploads.\n\nWhen switched on:\n\n  - all pages are replaced with the maintenance page\n  - webservice returns specific exception to all requests\n  - clients display a popup explaining what happens\n  - clients pause uploads and put all requests they were about to make in a stack\n  - clients starts to query the server on a regular basis to see if maintenance ended (server responding with no exception status)\n  - when server exits maintenance mode clients restart uploading and run stacked requests and remove maintenance popup\n\nImplemented in changeset [[3431]] and  [[r:3534]]\n\nConfig directive is config parameter \"maintenance\" that is boolean and false by default.\n","2015-03-18T07:28:40.000+00:00","2016-01-11T15:14:05.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","2016-01-11T15:14:05.000+00:00",0.0,0,-21.5,0,0,447388,0,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-11T15:14:05.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [114532253,1183,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feature: login session expired, re-logon?",3,"When a user's login session is expired and the user tries to do something, pop up a message saying re-authentication is needed and guide user to re-authentication.\n\nChangeset [[r:3535]]","2015-03-18T07:49:14.000+00:00","2016-01-11T09:10:29.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-01-11T09:10:29.000+00:00",0.0,0,-29.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-11T09:10:29.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [114537243,1184,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feature request: multi-language emails",3,"Email templates multi-language:\nput link in email “read this online in other language”.  Disadvantage: need to keep data available for each email sent by application so translate online is not an option.  Putting language in URL means exposure to data injections.  Generated on the fly: any replacement variables like transfer-file (extract from database), environment variables that we need to keep such as.  Would need a token message that would give access to specific database records.\nput switch in options to allow sending user to select language for all recipients.\nsend email with two templates\n","2015-03-18T08:53:47.000+00:00","2015-10-23T13:07:42.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-10-23T13:07:42.000+00:00",0.0,0,-30.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-23T13:07:42.000+00:00",null]
