tickets, [115290633,1186,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Consolidate upload_chunk_size and terasender_chunk_size to one variable",3,"- less complicated when creating server-side upload map\n- no reason to keep two\n- means less code\n","2015-03-26T12:49:07.000+00:00","2015-03-26T16:05:32.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-03-26T16:05:32.000+00:00",0.0,0,-32.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-26T16:05:32.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [115295213,1187,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Decide on dropping or keeping config defaults",3,"Currently a number of config options are set by default.  This allows installs to work with a very limited config file but has the disadvantage of \"hiding\" functionality: stuff just works magically.\n\nWe need to decide on:\n- what the default set of functionality (and thus config directives) should be\n- whether this should be defined in \"hidden\" defaults\n- or whether this should be defined in a sample config file\n\nWe need to decide this before the beta, because otherwise an update might break deployed installations.","2015-03-26T13:28:28.000+00:00","2015-03-26T13:28:29.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-33.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-03-26T13:28:28.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [115781563,1188,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Security bug: REST API error message leaks sensitive data",3,"Reported by Sören Krum from UNINETT.\n\nWhen he trying to access the REST API with a remote application like\n\nhttps://archive-test.norstore.uio.no:4443/rest.php/transfer/?remote_application=norstore&timestamp=1427800819616&signature=259026d57a961164cdfcd8a51003e77844909245 \n\nwhen not authenticated an error is generated that leaks sensitive data:\n\n{\"message\":\"auth_remote_application_signature_check_failed\",\"uid\":\"551a833bd6b98\",\"details\":\"secret = hemmelig\"}\n\nIssue fixed in Changeset [[r:3576]]: Reorganize remote auth exceptions, fix secret leak.","2015-04-01T11:16:12.000+00:00","2015-04-01T11:16:12.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-04-01T11:16:12.000+00:00",0.0,0,-34.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-04-01T11:16:12.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127436143,1189,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Review value for Sender email in transfer overview when non-sender return-path configured",3,"With email options configured so the sender of emails is something like 'no-reply@domain.com' the \"Sender email\" in the transfer overview still indicates the personal email.  \n\nThis might be weird from the user's point of view, as the emails clearly do NOT have that as the Sender email.  We need to decide how to deal with this.","2015-09-01T10:37:56.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:58:39.000+00:00",9888983,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,2.0,0,0,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:58:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127436263,1190,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: can not configure multiple admins with the admin config directive",3,"Two separate reports indicate you can't configure multiple admins.  Kevin Dermody tried a variety of separators.","2015-09-01T10:39:29.000+00:00","2015-10-06T09:22:12.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-10-06T09:22:12.000+00:00",0.0,0,-36.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-06T09:22:12.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127525873,1191,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Smoothening: fix inconsistent use of file size units.  Mo, Mb, MB.",3,"Quick testing shows inconsistent use of file size units in the UI and emails.  We need to land on 1 way for doing this and make it consistent throughout the UI and emails.\n\nExamples:\n\nUI:\nUpload: Mo, Go (in file box)\nTransfers: Mb, kb\nDownload: Mb\n\nEmail:\nFiles available for download email: Mb\nDownloaded email: doesn’t come by default?\n\nNeed to discuss with Etienne and make decision for which style to use.","2015-09-02T07:52:18.000+00:00","2015-11-03T04:42:31.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-11-03T04:42:31.000+00:00",0.0,0,-37.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-03T04:42:31.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127526063,1192,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Smoothning: OSX un-archiving software in download page should be conditional on download file size.",3,"When downloading with Mac the message \"If you are running OSX you'll find a fitting un-archiving software by following the link below. : The Unarchiver.\" is visible also when the file size is < 2 GB.  A user doesn't need to do anything in case a received file is < 2GB.\n\nTwo things need to be done:\n- make this message conditional on file size and detected download OS\n- double-check whether the latest Mac OS-X version still has a 32-bit unzip.\n\nDiscuss issue with Etienne and decide on how to continue.\n\n","2015-09-02T07:54:37.000+00:00","2016-02-08T11:52:50.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","2016-02-08T11:52:50.000+00:00",0.0,0,-38.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-08T11:52:50.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127526133,1193,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Documentation: document duplicate file detection on upload",3,"Document in admin guide.  This is how the upload form behaves.  Need to document how it detects duplicate files in the upload box.","2015-09-02T07:55:50.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:41:43.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-5.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:41:43.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127833693,1194,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feedback: subject does not change when optional subject used",3,"People expect when they use subject that it is used as mail subject.  This doesn't work now.  \n\nAllowing people to change mail subject introduces possible security risk (ref. sendmail bug where people could inject bash in subject).  Raises question of why allow to change subject.  People also mentioned they missed this functionality in the guest voucher.\n\nDecision: this will follow how it works in version 1.6: when subject changed in either upload or guest invitation page, also change it in email.","2015-09-07T08:33:19.000+00:00","2015-10-06T09:32:57.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-10-06T09:32:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,-40.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-06T09:32:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127833773,1195,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feedback: language switch in translated email page hard to find",3,"Feedback from users:\n\nIn mail translation page it's not really highlighted that you can translate email by switching language.  Maybe we need some additional bigger \"switch language\" selector in middle of screen.  \n\nDecision: Etienne can feel free to test.","2015-09-07T08:34:33.000+00:00","2015-11-02T10:40:39.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-11-02T10:40:39.000+00:00",0.0,0,-41.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-02T10:40:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127834163,1196,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feedback: make Recipient email address in transfer view clickable",3,"Feedback from French test users:\n\nAnywhere in the web interface where there are mentions of recipients (like in transfer list, when you open details about transfer), you can't click on emails.  Email addresses are not clickable mailto: links.  Tooltip.\n\nPeople wondered why this didn't work.  Should be regular mailto link.\n\nTwo things in transfer\n- put entire recipient email address in overview and make it mailto: link.\n- when expand transfer, display recipient email entirely (vertically summed up) and make it into mailto: link.\n\n\n","2015-09-07T08:39:53.000+00:00","2015-09-17T09:13:39.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-09-17T09:13:39.000+00:00",0.0,0,-42.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-09-17T09:13:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127834343,1197,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: translation failure with downloads from \"link only\" transfers",3,"when you try to get audit log from transfer you asked to get a link for, all downloads are mentioned done by anonymous (because we don't know).  This goes wrong when translating.  ","2015-09-07T08:41:04.000+00:00","2015-11-02T10:45:39.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-11-02T10:45:39.000+00:00",0.0,0,-43.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-02T10:45:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127835643,1198,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Logon problem with SimpleSAMLphp in different URL space (session.cookie.path)",3,"Behaviour: after logging on a user is simply redirected to the logon page.  Logging of SimpleSAMLphp seems to indicate the user is not logged on, no authenticated session is created.\n\nFileSender 2.0 explicitly sets the session.cookie.path to the site URL on initialisation.  Usually this points to / and won't cause any\nissues for the standard setup with simplesamlphp where simplesamlphp is in a separate URL space from\nFileSender.\n\nHowever, on my testing machine and for example for launching our filesender.uninett.no/beta service this\nis a bit different and hence sessions between simplesamlphp and filesender are not accepted by filesender.\nWith Shibboleth this is not an issue as it uses its own session variable handling.  SimpleSAMLphp is in php and shares with PHP.\n\nAgreed solution: introduce a configuration parameter session_cookie_path.  When using SimpleSAMLphp in a URL path other than /, you need to configure this to for example /.  \n\nIf the parameter is not set, FileSender uses the default application path which is either specified in site_url or extracted from the application environment.\n","2015-09-07T08:58:44.000+00:00","2016-02-10T13:28:23.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-44.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-10T13:28:23.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127835983,1199,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document session_cookie_path configuration directive",3,"Put this together with simplesamlphp config directives.","2015-09-07T09:02:50.000+00:00","2015-10-06T09:26:02.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-10-06T09:26:02.000+00:00",0.0,0,-44.099998474121094,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-06T09:26:02.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127836943,1200,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: broken logic when uploading choosing \"get link instead of sending to recipients\"",3,"Reported by Kevin Dermody:\n\nSome broken logic when uploading, if I choose \"Get a link instead of sending to recipients\" I get the\nfollowing error\n\n\"Transfer has no recipients\"\n\nWhich is technically correct, but not an error :)\n\nVerified on my test instance.","2015-09-07T09:13:09.000+00:00","2016-02-10T13:33:55.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2016-02-10T13:33:55.000+00:00",0.0,0,-45.0,0,0,3316353,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-10T13:33:55.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127837693,1201,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: no code to expire user preferences",3,"Need to delete user preferences for users that haven't been active in a long time to adhere to \"small privacy footprint\" principle.\n\nRequires config parameter\n\n\"user_preference_expiry\" in days? \n\nA user log on = activity.\n\n","2015-09-07T09:21:16.000+00:00","2016-01-11T09:13:39.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-46.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-09-10T07:35:47.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127839703,1202,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Email formatting sometimes broken: raw email formatting displayed rather than pretty formatted",3,"Test platform terasender.uninett.no/branches/filesender2.0/ is based on Debian with Exim as MTA.  Test platform filesender.uninett.no/beta is based on red hat + postfix as MTA.\n\nterasender platform sends out emails that are displayed correctly at client.  Emails sent from uninett.no/beta are displayed \"raw\", mangled.  Differences in headers: \n\n=========\nGood email:\n\n--mbnd--alt--1440662171464055dec29b93c0e\nContent-Type: text/plain; charset=\"utf-8\"; format=flowed\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\n\n\nBad email:\n\n--mbnd--alt--1440520233238455dc982937416\nContent-Type: text/plain\n\nContent-Type:text/plain; charset=\"utf-8\"; format=flowed\n\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\n\n=========\n\nNot encoding the mail as quoted printable by changing utils/Mail.class.php seems to help:\n\n// Encode contents\n//        $plain = quoted_printable_encode($plain);\n\n\nEtienne thinks: mime headers are not being considered by mail client because somehow a double carriage return is introduced.  So quoted printable header is not being interpreted as a header.  Then you get garbled header.  What introduces double carriage returns in stead of single ones as we set in FileSender.\n\nFor some reason the outgoing SMTP server might be using old LF character (single \\n rather than \\r\\n).  This can be tested easily.  \n\nModify file classes/constants GlobalConstants.class.php and remove \\r.\n\nIf this now works it means SMTP server doesn't use \\r\\n for new lines, perhaps replaces \\r by \\n.\n\nJan to ask Thierry to test this on filesender.uninett.no/beta.","2015-09-07T09:43:42.000+00:00","2015-11-02T10:34:53.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-11-02T10:34:53.000+00:00",0.0,0,-47.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-02T10:34:53.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127840913,1203,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Update help text",3,"Current help text is for version 1.5.  Update this to reflect version 2.0.","2015-09-07T09:57:39.000+00:00","2015-09-17T12:39:18.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-48.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-09-15T09:49:49.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127841083,1204,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Documentation 2.0: how to configure 2.0 email settings so you will not have any SPF troubles",3,"Etienne to double-check application logic in this respect.\n\nCurrent config at https://terasender.uninett.no/branches/filesender-2.0/ is:\n\n$config['email_from'] = 'no-reply@uninett.no'; // either 'sender' or an email address\n$config['email_from_name'] = 'UNINETT FileSender - beta 2.0'; // pretty name with the From: address\n$config['email_reply_to'] ='sender'; // either 'sender' or an email address\n// $config['email_reply_to_name'] = 'pretty name'; // pretty name in case email_reply_to is a configured email address\n$config['email_return_path'] = 'no-reply@uninett.no'; // either 'sender' or an email address\n\nWe need a config template that will make a filesender installation SPF compliant.","2015-09-07T10:00:11.000+00:00","2016-05-12T09:01:56.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-11.0,0,0,133342,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T09:01:56.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127842893,1205,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Documentation 2.0: how to configure bounce handling",3,"The config variable email_return_path specifies where email bounces will be sent to.  \n\nIf this variable is not set, bounces will arrive at the sender.\nIf this varialbe is set to an email address that can receive emails then the script scripts/task/emailfeedback.php can be used to process bounces.\nIf VRRP (?) is used even if the bounce message is non-standard we can see something happened.  This introduces a variable in the email headers (?)\n\nVerify more tomorrow with Etienne.\n\n","2015-09-07T10:21:19.000+00:00","2015-10-23T09:37:25.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-10-23T09:37:25.000+00:00",0.0,0,-50.0,0,0,342706,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-23T09:37:25.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127901363,1206,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Simplify autocomplete configuration parameters",3,"Go from three to two of which only one is mandatory to make autocomplete work.\n\nSituation now:\n\nthree parameters.\n\nautocomplete = true\nautocomplete_max_shown = \nmax_stored_frequent_recipients =\n\nIf you do not specify the last one it won't work as it won't gather any records.\n\nProposed future situation with two parameters\n\nautocomplete: \n-false/0: no autocomplete\n-number: number of items returned by search\n-by default if no other parameter set, use 5xnumber for stored items\n-if that does not work for your instance (users use lots of different recipients) use second parameter which will override 5 times value\n\nautocomplete_max_pool: how many recipients to store in user preferences.\n\n","2015-09-08T08:27:49.000+00:00","2015-10-23T13:04:37.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-51.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-23T13:04:37.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127902913,1207,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Create SPF-compliant best practice configuration for FileSender",3,"Double-check which combination of email_* parameters is needed to make a FileSender instance SPF compliant and document this.  Can document in ticket, then hand ticket to me and I'll document it in the documentation","2015-09-08T08:44:48.000+00:00","2015-10-23T09:40:50.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-10-23T09:40:50.000+00:00",0.0,0,-52.0,0,0,342706,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-23T09:40:50.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [127905743,1208,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Implement different language tag in drag&drop field for legacy uploads",3,"there is currently no feedback to a user whether they use html5 upload or legacy upload.  Upload screen is exactly the same.  Only difference is in legacy upload a user would have a limit of 2 GB per individual file.  \n\nSuggest to implement a different language tag for the drag&drop box message so we can have something like \"drag and drop your files here.  You are using an old browser.  This means the individual files can NOT be larger than 2 GB\".","2015-09-08T09:18:23.000+00:00","2015-11-03T04:36:22.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-11-03T04:36:22.000+00:00",0.0,0,-53.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-03T04:36:22.000+00:00",null]
