tickets, [128584983,1214,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: unclear error on tripping the default language config validation + inconsistent documentation/reality",3,"I managed to trip this one by configuring Norwegian as the only language in locale.php while that's not set as the default language\n\nThe GUI says \"Configuration error(s), please check the server logs or ask an admin to do so.\" while the Apache server log says \"Sep 17 10:42:15 terasender apache2: ConfigValidator \"default_language\" does not validate check : default_language must be one of the available languages defined in locale.php (no)\".  \n\nThere is no logging in the FileSender log.  Where do messages from the ConfigValidator go?  If they always go to \"wherever PHP logs\" we need to state \"check your PHP server logs\" in this error.\n\nAnother consideration: we state that the hard coded language of last resort is always \"en\".  However, in this case that is not true.  So either I need to change the language config documentation or we need to change this from a fatal error to a (severe) warning?\n\n","2015-09-17T08:48:52.000+00:00","2016-01-11T09:20:36.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-59.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-09-17T10:14:18.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [128793533,1215,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","auth_sp_set_idp_as_user_organization stil used?",3,"Etienne,\n\nI double-check all configuration directives I document to ensure they are in use.\n\nroot@terasender:/usr/local/filesender/branches/filesender-2.0# grep -i -R auth_sp_set_idp_as_user_organization *\nincludes/ConfigDefaults.php:    'auth_sp_set_idp_as_user_organization' => false,\nincludes/.svn/text-base/ConfigDefaults.php.svn-base:    'auth_sp_set_idp_as_user_organization' => false,\n\nIs that one still in use?  I don't see any code related to it.","2015-09-21T09:44:53.000+00:00","2015-10-23T09:45:36.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-10-23T09:45:36.000+00:00",0.0,0,-60.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-23T09:45:36.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [128890863,1216,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Smoothening: Transfer option \"get_a_link\" inconsistent with other options, \"advanced\" not supported",3,"We should probably discuss where the tick box related to the transfer option \"get a link\" is located.  All other options are in the \"option\" box, but this one is in the \"recipient\" box.  \n\nI'd propose to simply let it behave as one of the other options, including allowing it to be displayed always or as part of the \"advanced options\" drop-out.\n\nYour thoughts are appreciated, there's probably a reason why you put it where it is :)","2015-09-22T10:18:20.000+00:00","2015-11-03T04:26:25.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","2015-11-03T04:26:25.000+00:00",0.0,0,-61.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-03T04:26:25.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [129725763,1217,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Safari 9.0 stuck at 0% during upload",3,"As reported by Enrico Cavalli and others. Analysis and possible fix from Renato Furter (tx!):\n\n---------------\n\"SyntaxError: DOM Exception 12: An invalid or illegal string was specified.\" on line 289 in upload.js\nwhich is the following line: \nxhr.setRequestHeader(\"Content-Disposition\",\" attachment; name='fileToUpload'\"); \n\nThe Content-Disposition is \"An opportunity to raise a \"File Download\" dialogue box for a known MIME type with binary format or suggest a filename for dynamic content. Quotes are necessary with special characters.”* which seams seams not really important to me for an Ajax request that uploads a file (especially that it is a ResponseHeader option and we are setting RequestHeaders here), so I just uncomment it. And then it worked for Safari 9.\n----------------\n\nFix needs confirmation\n\n","2015-10-02T19:35:36.000+00:00","2016-12-12T19:42:57.000+00:00",3026383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2015-12-30T15:24:57.000+00:00",0.0,0,-89.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-30T15:24:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [129725873,1218,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Update HEAnet logo",3,"","2015-10-02T19:36:42.000+00:00","2015-11-17T13:37:43.000+00:00",3026383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2015-11-17T13:37:43.000+00:00",0.0,0,-90.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-17T13:37:43.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [129892533,1220,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Smoothening: different message for one time guest invite use and multi-use",4,"When using a guest voucher the guest gets this message after uploading:\n\n\"Thank you for using FileSender. If your guest is enabled for multiple uploads you may use your upload link again to send other files.\"\n\nThat message should be different for the two use cases:\n- one time use guest invite useupload\n- multi-use guest\n\nWe want to make sure users don't need to think when we can prevent it.","2015-10-06T10:50:09.000+00:00","2015-10-06T10:52:29.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-63.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-06T10:50:09.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [130415993,1221,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Smoothening: make audit log easier to find",3,"Feedback from users in RENATER public beta: it's hard to get the audit logs for a transfer.  I also noted this in my own testing.\n\nAfter discussing with Etienne today, following was decided:\n-add an \"get audit log\" icon button to the actions in My Transfers (the table overview)\n-in the expanded view for a transfer, move the current \"Transfer logs\" up and make it clearer it's a button people can click on\n-change label to \"get audit log for transfer\"\n","2015-10-13T11:54:34.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:58:39.000+00:00",9888983,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,3.0,0,0,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:58:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [130416283,1222,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Smoothening: small changes to \"Transfers\" table and Transfer expanded view",3,"-Add TransferID as table column and make it more visible in the expanded view; for the latter move it to the top of the expanded view entry and make the default colour something else than greyed out\n-Add columns for Expired and Actions to table for \"Closed Transfers\".  This will align columns for both open and closed transfers so the total page becomes easier on the eyes.","2015-10-13T11:57:43.000+00:00","2016-01-11T09:18:43.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-65.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-10-14T08:44:19.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [130418083,1223,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Feature: contextual help",3,"In FileSender 1.x we used to have tooltips.  Jan to look at usability reports to check recommendations given as well as check some good web sites to see how this is done with others currently.  One option is to include question marks there where help needs to be available.  \n\nContextual help needs to be \"in your face\", without you doing anything to see it.  \n\n","2015-10-13T12:17:24.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:58:39.000+00:00",9888983,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,4.0,0,0,3325193,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:58:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [130520603,1224,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: guest voucher can not be used by unauthenticated guest",1,"Created a guest voucher with options \"no expiry\" and \"valid for multiple uploads\" and \"send only to me\".  Guest can not use voucher without being authenticated.  Upload page can be accessed, but as soon as upload starts, an error \"you need to be authenticated to do this\" pops up.","2015-10-14T10:57:30.000+00:00","2016-01-06T08:45:45.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","2016-01-06T08:45:45.000+00:00",0.0,0,-67.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-06T08:45:45.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [130974483,1225,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: wrong evaluation of maxexpires when default_days_valid not set in config?",3,"Sören Krum from UNINETT reports a possible bug in transfer.js\n\n\"in line 696 the script tries to figure out the maxexpires, but it evaluates to NaN, probably because the\nfilesender.config has no element called \"default_days_valid\". It has a one called \"max_transfer_days_valid\"\n\nThat leads to that i can submit a transfer valid for a really long time....\"\n","2015-10-20T12:53:58.000+00:00","2016-03-17T13:57:27.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","2016-03-17T13:57:27.000+00:00",0.0,0,-68.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-03-17T13:57:27.000+00:00",null]
