tickets, [133493993,1239,"dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload broken by computer sleep mode (it seems)",1,"(theory start)\n\nWhen uploading a huge file slowly at some point the computer goes to sleep.\n\nThat ends up having incomplete chunk upload requests being sent (400 code by apache, php not executed).\n\nAfter computer awakes the stalled transfer mechanism triggers (no feedback from workers over too long) but transfer cannot be restarted because XSRF token expired.\n\n(theory end)\n\nWe need a mechanism able to figure out that nothing happened over more than XSRF token lifetime and refresh said token (not over WS call obviously, more like an hidden iframe in which we load the home page and fetch the token from it, possible since same domain).\n\nThis could be an extension of stalled transfer detection.","2015-11-17T10:54:44.000+00:00","2016-01-11T09:10:56.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-82.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-11-19T17:14:28.000+00:00",null]
