tickets, [133521583,1241,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Handling decomposed unicode in filenames",3,"On (at least) Mac OSX filenames with certain Unicode characters tend to be represented as 'decomposed unicode' (see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unicode_equivalence for an explanation). Although FileSender transparantly handles those decomposed characters and leaves the actual handling to the browser and OS it looks like most notably Windows (when storing a file with 'decomposed unicode' characters from FireFox/Chrome) and IE11 (when displaying those files in My Files or a download page) doesn't handle those characters as expected.\n\nWe might consider 'fixing' this in FileSender by normalizing 'decomposed unicode' to 'precomposed unicode'. \n\nConsiderations:\n- The normalizer_normalize function of the PHP intl extension can be used for this, this requires PHP 5.3+ and adds extra dependencies (php5-intl, libicu)\n- Should we normalize when uploading (before storing the filename into the database) or only when displaying/downloading?\n\n\nThis ticket was cloned from the 1.6 milestone: we need to check whether this is still an issue with the current 2.0 code and if it is, whether we can resolve it.","2015-11-17T13:53:05.000+00:00","2016-02-08T15:35:00.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-85.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-08T15:35:00.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134431863,1242,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: transfer delete by Admin user does not work",3,"Reported by Søren Krum (UNINETT): \n\nHe tried to delete a transfer of a user other than his own user, as Admin, via the Admin page. The function is there in the overview table.  \n\n\"A popup occurs, but if i click ok, nothing seems to happen. I checked the network traffic from the browser, and it looks like\nnothing is send back to the server?!\n\nDeleting my own transfers in the view \"My transfers\" works fine...\"\n\nEtienne, do you remember whehter this was intended, that this functionality is accessible for the Admin?  If the answer is yes, two things need to happen:\n\n- I need to document this as functionality\n- You need to make it work ;)\n\nIf no: we need to remove that functionality from the Transfer overview table for the Admin.","2015-11-30T08:37:24.000+00:00","2016-02-08T12:31:03.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-85.0,0,0,133342,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-08T10:45:22.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134543373,1243,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Download email generated even if user clicks on \"Cancel\" rather than \"Save File\"",3,"The email advising that a file has been downloaded is generated when one clicks on the \"Start Download\" button, not when the download finishes. This give the impression that a recipient has downloaded the file, even if they clicked on \"Cancel\" rather than \"Save File\" when prompted. This could result in the uploader prematurely manually deleting an uploaded file, thinking that their recipient has already downloaded it.","2015-12-01T09:54:45.000+00:00","2015-12-01T10:05:48.000+00:00",394418,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-12-01T09:55:39.000+00:00",0.0,0,-49.0,0,0,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-01T10:05:48.000+00:00",null]
