tickets, [134546353,1247,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Filename with international characters other than ISO-8859-1 will look 'funny' when downloaded with IE",3,"When using international characters in filenames other than ISO-8859-1 the filename will look 'funny' when downloaded with Internet Explorer and possibly other browsers other than FireFox, Chrome or Safari. The file is however correctly downloaded and usable.  \n\nThe \"Content-Dispositon\" problem\n\nAt the moment the labeling of a string as UTF-8 encoded is not done when a file containing special characters is downloaded. The download process uses the HTTP Content-Disposition header with a filename parameter. This header is only defined for filenames containing characters from the (single byte) ISO-8859-1 character set.\n\nAlthough there are currently ongoing standardisation efforts to make it possible to use other character sets there is no universally adopted way of transmitting a UTF-8 encoded filename yet (see http://greenbytes.de/tech/webdav/draft-ietf-httpbis-content-disp-latest.html for details). The current filesender code therefore relies on what is called 'encoding sniffing' in browsers such as FireFox, Chrome and Safari. Internet Explorer can only handle ISO-8859-1 (single byte) encoded filenames.\n\nSee our developer documentation on International_Character_Handling","2015-12-01T10:22:10.000+00:00","2016-08-18T07:32:10.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-08-18T07:32:10.000+00:00",0.0,0,-87.0,0,0,447388,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-08-18T07:32:10.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134564213,1248,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: Recipient removal breaks audit log",2,"The audit log is supposed to give an overview of what happend to a transfer when and by whom.  \n\nThe current audit log is implemented in such a way that it stores identifiers to for example a recipient entry in the recipient table rather than the actual values.  Deleting a recipient leads to dangling identifiers in the audit log.  This again breaks audit log viewing in the web interface and sending the audit log by email.\n\nThere are several ways to solve this, not all are equally desirable.  We need to revisit what exactly the audit log shoudl provide as a feature before making a decision.  This ticket will be linked to a feature specification ticket for that reason.","2015-12-01T13:34:45.000+00:00","2016-01-11T09:21:11.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-88.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-01T14:05:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134564383,1249,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Audit trail",3,"During a transfer actions happen to it: files are downloadedWhen a transfer is closed the owner of that transfer can get \n\nFor each action that happens to a transfer an entry in an audit log is created.\n\nEach audit trail entry contains a timestamp with timezone.\nWhere relevant (audit trail events triggered by clients) an IP-address is included.\n","2015-12-01T13:36:54.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:54:15.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-1.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-01T13:36:54.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134632983,1250,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Establish policy for dealing with known issues",3,"With every release we have had and will have known issues: stuff we know is broken but we either will not (lack of resources/priority) or can not (3rd party issues) fix.   We kept track of these issues so we could try and fix them in new releases.  So far we've done this with putting an issue in the \"Deferred\" state: an issue is deferred to a later time.  However, deferred is an open ticket status.  I have a strong desire to be able to close milestones; it makes it much clearer what we are working on and what not.  This would also allow us to start using Assembla for more than ticket adminstration; we can start using its project management features to have better control over our efforts.\n\nAs an example: release 1.1 and 1.5 we are not working on.  Tickets in those milestones will never be worked on again.  Still they remain open.  \n\nWhat I want is:\n- a milestone per release and the ability to close milestones we no longer work on\n- a record of known issues per release without those issues remaining open tickets after we've decided we will not work on them for that particular release.\n\nAny change of the policy for dealing with known issues will need to be updated in the ticket status guide https://www.assembla.com/spaces/file_sender/wiki/Ticket_Status_Guide\n\n","2015-12-02T07:52:51.000+00:00","2016-02-10T20:44:02.000+00:00",9227153,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-1.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T10:40:30.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134633973,1251,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Update policy alpha and beta release",3,"Alpha: Has not undergone structured client side (workflow) testing.\n\nBeta: has undergone structured client side (workflwo) testing\n\nWith beta: does not need to have undergone testing of _all_ features as long as what we have tested is clearly documented with the particular beta.\n\n-Need to review current definition of beta release in release and software lifecycle policy\n-look at definition of steps in roadmap","2015-12-02T08:08:02.000+00:00","2016-02-24T08:05:52.000+00:00",9227153,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-2.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-10T20:37:12.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134634153,1252,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Review open tickets in version 1.5, 1.6, suggested and planned features",3,"Review all currently open tickets in all milestones but in particular version 1.5, 1.6, suggested and planned features.  Goal: only have open tickets that we actively work on or want to work actively on.  \n\nclose tickets where we can using the \"known issue\" closed ticket status and transporting known issues onwards to a release milestone where we actually work on them.  \n\nTicket review needs to be completed before closing a ticket: reviewing all open tickets to see what is included / fixed in 2.0.\n\nThis is part of tidying up the project's documentation as part of starting testing version 2.0.  What features are included in 2.0 affect the testing of 2.0.","2015-12-02T08:11:06.000+00:00","2016-02-24T08:03:42.000+00:00",9227153,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-3.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T13:15:38.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134762573,1253,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Logon possible with JavaScript disabled",3,"When javascript is disabled, while the warning message \"JavaScript is turned off in your web browser. This application will not run without Javascript enabled in your web browser.\" is displayed, the logon and other menubar buttons are still active.  The user can still logon.\n\nWe need to make a decision on how this should work: should we simply say to the user \"you need to enable javascript, without it there's no point in doiong anything\" or should we allow the user in and stumble over non-functing features?\n\nI would argue that if javascript is not enabled, the user should not be let in.  Etienne, any opinion on this?","2015-12-03T11:36:51.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:36:51.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-91.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:36:51.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134762963,1254,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Modify all fixed widths to auto fit banner width",3,"css/default.css\nabout.php\nfiles.php\nhelp.php\nindex.php\ninvalidvoucher.php\nlogout.php\nvouchererror.php\n","2015-12-03T11:42:50.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:43:22.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2015-12-03T11:42:50.000+00:00",0.0,0,-93.0,0,1,19299663,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:42:57.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134763303,1255,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","# Appearing in Browser Tabs and Browser Title",3,"When pressing a button - some cases show a # symbol in the Browser Title or the Browser Tab title. \nThis is cause by either Flash or Jquery adding a history record to the browser recording a user interaction so that a user can use the back button to \"go back\".\n\nIn many cases we use 'onclick' as part of a href and leave the href as url=\"#\".\nFor consistency - any location that uses a javascript call that does not require the user to have the option of a back button will need the href replaced with a div.\n\n","2015-12-03T11:47:05.000+00:00","2015-12-03T11:47:29.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,aNSALiyQSr3482eJe5cbCb","2015-12-03T11:47:05.000+00:00",0.0,0,-94.0,0,1,19299663,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T11:47:05.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134765143,1256,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Browse button issue for automated testing with Flash",3,"When I try to create or run a Selenium-IDE script with a Firefox browser using Flash only (FF 3.6.21 on Mac OSX 10.4.11), Selenium does not recognise when I click on the \"Browse\" button, or activate the \"Browse\" button using a script I had already created using an HTML5 browser (FF 6.0 on Mac OSX 10.6.8). Both macs are running Flash 10.3.183.5. Could this be associated with the fact that the filepath field is absent in the Flash version of FileSender?","2015-12-03T12:04:24.000+00:00","2015-12-03T12:05:16.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2015-12-03T12:04:24.000+00:00",0.0,0,-95.0,0,0,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T12:04:24.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134766023,1257,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Create initial documentation for pause/resume functionality in version 2.0",3,"We had pause/resume functionality in version 1.x.  Question is do we have the same type of functionality in 2.0 and how does it behave?  This needs to be documented. \n\nEtienne, could you please do a braindump in this ticket so I can put it at the correct place in the documentation?","2015-12-03T12:12:34.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:59:39.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-8.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:59:39.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [134775173,1258,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Find alternatives to OpenIdP accounts",3,"OpenIdP will be phased out per 1 January 2016.  I've verified internally at UNINETT that the entire OpenIdP service will disappear, it also will not be accessible for me as a UNINETT employee.  AFAIK there are no current alternatives available that do the exact same.\n\nThe FileSender project uses openidp.feide.no as an IdP for the following purposes:\n\n1. test accounts for (automated, selenium-based) client-side testing.\n2. ensuring federated login is tested before we release \n3. as the default IdP new FileSender installations can authenticate against.  This ensures the 1-hour setup time.\n4. as a self-registration user account system for demo (test) instances\n\nConsiderations with the purpose 1, use for test accounts:\n- the credentials need to be able to be exposed to external services without problems, like selenium service providers.  Credential exposure should not lead to possible compromise of other services\n- we need to be able to specify which email addresses are associated with the test accounts\n\nConsiderations with purpose 3, use by new FileSender instances to test their installation\n- no default username/password should be distributed with a FileSender release\n\nWe will need to find a (combination of) alternative(s).  ","2015-12-03T13:24:53.000+00:00","2015-12-03T13:28:12.000+00:00",9227153,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-4.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-03T13:24:53.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [135285323,1259,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Decide on language file format to use",3,"We want to use a translation crowd-sourcing service like poeditor.com.  These services typically support a number of formats.  We need to decide which format we can/will use in FileSender 2.0 and then make the necessary code changes.  This ticket is to support the decision process: which format to use.  Etienne, could you please write your input in the comments?  Once a decision has been made, please create another ticket for the actual code conseequenses :)","2015-12-10T12:44:02.000+00:00","2016-02-23T14:25:14.000+00:00",1097603,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,buRYsmN0ir5zpcdmr6bg7m","2016-02-23T14:25:14.000+00:00",0.0,0,-1.0,0,0,3316353,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-23T14:25:14.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [135398973,1260,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: size units in upload form: Mb, Gb vs. MB GB",3,"I noticed today the size units in the upload form are now \"Mb\" and \"Gb\" for both filesize and upload speed.  However, the average speed seems to be actually expressed in mega_bytes_, not mega_bits_.  \n\nRegarding filesizes: we should be consistent with what operating systems present to users.  And then it's GB and MB\nRegarding transfer speed: double-check whether it displays Mbit/s or Mbyte/s.  If it does Mbyte/s the 2nd character (MB/s or GB/s) should be a capital.\n\n","2015-12-11T10:05:18.000+00:00","2015-12-11T10:05:30.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-93.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-11T10:05:18.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [135416893,1261,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Basic upload resume",3,"Etienne,\n\nI just tested a 200 GB upload, my laptop crashed for some non-related reason (I hope) about 5GB before the upload was done.  After I waited about 4 hours for the 195 GB to complete it was rather frustrating to start again from scratch especially considering we have basic upload resume in version 1.6 ;)\n\nBasic upload resume should be part of version 2.0 as well.  If you as a user select the exact same files as you had before the crash it should be possible to simply resume the upload.  I think most of the under-the-hood feature is already there?  Your comments please :)","2015-12-11T13:26:51.000+00:00","2016-01-20T14:20:22.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-95.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-11T13:26:51.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136539723,1262,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","1.6.1 bugfix release",3,"Placeholder ticket for 1.6.1 bugfix release","2015-12-30T11:14:49.000+00:00","2015-12-30T15:22:20.000+00:00",3026383,null,"bkpnJ4jEWr37jceJe5afGb","2015-12-30T15:22:20.000+00:00",0.0,0,-96.0,0,0,447388,0,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2015-12-30T15:22:20.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136712203,1263,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Admin: maintenance mode",3,"This allows to interrupt the service for database upgrade or even server restart without breaking uploads.\n\nWhen switched on:\n  - all pages are replaced with the maintenance page\n  - webservice returns specific exception to all requests\n  - clients display a popup explaining what happens\n  - clients pause uploads and put all requests they were about to make in a stack\n  - clients starts to query the server on a regular basis to see if maintenance ended (server responding with no exception status)\n  - when server exits maintenance mode clients restart uploading and run stacked requests and remove maintenance popup\n\nConfig directive is config parameter \"maintenance\" that is boolean and false by default.\n\nimplemented in ticket #1182.","2016-01-04T13:35:51.000+00:00","2016-01-05T11:08:58.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-2.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-04T13:35:51.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136789803,1264,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload: Multi-file upload in single transaction (html5)",3,"A user select multiple files which will be uploaded in one go after the user clicks \"send\".  \n\nThere is a maximum number of files that a user can select for a single transfer (server-side configurable)\nThere is a maximum total transfer size (server-side configurable).","2016-01-05T11:03:37.000+00:00","2016-01-05T11:08:25.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-3.0,0,0,6740773,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-05T11:03:48.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136790123,1265,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload: drag & drop file selection (html5)",3,"A user can select files to transfer using drag & drop.  The files show up in a file selection box in the upload page.  Files can be dropped in the entire FileSender \"window\", so it doesn't matter whether they are dropped exactly in the drag&drop box or somewhere else on the screen.","2016-01-05T11:07:00.000+00:00","2016-01-05T11:07:00.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-4.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-05T11:07:00.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136874273,1266,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: Time zone not honoured in audit log",3,"I noticed today that the time in the audit log seems to not honour the timezone.  In a test upload I did today it is one hour behind our current time, both in the email and in the web UI. \n\n In the config I did specify:\n$config['Default_TimeZone'] = 'Europe/Oslo';\n\nEtienne, can you look into this?\n\n\n\n","2016-01-06T07:53:24.000+00:00","2016-02-08T14:55:04.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-95.0,0,0,133342,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-20T14:18:10.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136904543,1267,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Reconsider default limit on #files per transfer",3,"Experience shows a transfer limit of 30 files is not enough.  We need a better reasonable default.  We need to assess whether there is a reason this can't be unlimited.\n\nPractical limits: \n- table of contents in download zip file of 2^64 files (64 bit offset) \n- maximum number of records in SQL table\n-most likely a practical limit in the file selection box, probably \"over a few 1000\" because we would be creating a lot of HTML nodes.  The page would be sloooooow.\n\nProbably not a problem to setting it to 2000, over that may have implications for memory use.\n\nWe will configure a default file limit of 2000 per transfer","2016-01-06T14:27:47.000+00:00","2016-02-08T15:38:55.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-96.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-06T14:27:47.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136904663,1268,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Investigate  detection of folders on file selection",3,"If a user selects a folder we should pop up a message that says folders are not supported.  Preferably we'd be able to just read the entire folder but lets start with a message for now.","2016-01-06T14:28:58.000+00:00","2016-05-12T09:00:02.000+00:00",9888983,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,6.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T09:00:02.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [136906463,1269,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: Mb should be MB and when using bits/s the units should be correct",3,"Units are currently typically in megabits, gigabits etc. for filesize.  That should be megabytes etc.\n\nIn the upload speedometer when using \"display bits per second\" = false, the unit is currently also Mb/s.  Should be MB/s  When display_bits_per_second the unit should be in Mb/s.","2016-01-06T14:46:15.000+00:00","2016-02-08T13:41:51.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-100.0,0,0,133342,1,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-08T10:45:33.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [137329483,1270,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: Downloading a ZIP does not include very small files",3,"When uploading two files where one is very large >6GB and one very small <1MB, the upload succeeds.\nThen, when downloading both files as one ZIP file, the ZIP file will only contain the larger file.\n\nMore specifically, I tried downloading OS X El Capitan, and I uploaded both files in the Contents/SharedSupport folder.","2016-01-12T13:23:19.000+00:00","2016-02-08T10:39:57.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-99.5,0,0,28660,1,1.0,2.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-12T13:23:19.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [137530653,1271,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Download: download all files at once into an archive",3,"Allow a user to download either all or a selection of available files in one go.  The files would end up in a .zip archive on the end user's machine.  The user should be able to open the .zip file with built-in file manaement tool (typically Windows Explorer or Apple Finder).","2016-01-14T10:06:47.000+00:00","2016-01-14T10:14:04.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-5.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-14T10:06:47.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [137762143,1272,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Email audit log",3,"When a user accesses the \"Transfer audit log\" overview (either via the button in the expanded My Transfers entry, or via the entry's icon in the My Transfers overview) the user should be able to click a button to send the audit log by email.\n\nWhen the audit log is sent, the user gets feedbackin the UI that the mail was sent.  \n\nNotes regarding current implementation (january 2016):\n- the button \"send audit log by email\" should be centered in the audit log window\n- there currently is no user feedback when the button is clicked.  This is confusing, as a user you don't know if something happened or if the button is just a \"big button that doesn't do anything\".","2016-01-18T12:41:56.000+00:00","2016-01-18T12:41:56.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-1.100000023841858,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-01-18T12:41:56.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139367053,1273,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Possible race condition on integrity check",3,"I got this non-reproducable bug once. Upon upload, I get the error that the integrity check failed. PHP logs tell me that the file doesn't exsit, while <code>ls</code> tells me that it does, so this may be a race condition?\n\nLogs follow:\n\n*Apache* \n<pre><code>\n[Thu Feb 04 11:02:34 2016] [error] [client 192.0.2.100] PHP Warning:  filesize(): stat failed for /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/files/642b0dad-d326-96bf-d0cf-4d1285f652ef in /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/storage/StorageFilesystem.class.php on line 371, referer: https://qtest.filesender.org/filesender20/?s=upload\n</code></pre>\n\n*FileSender*\n<pre><code>\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException exception uid:56b321ba9ed9e] file_integrity_check_failed\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #0 [internal function]: StorageFilesystem::completeFile(Object(File))\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #1 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/storage/Storage.class.php(172): call_user_func('StorageFilesyst...', Object(File))\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #2 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/data/File.class.php(216): Storage::completeFile(Object(File))\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #3 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/endpoints/RestEndpointFile.class.php(303): File->complete()\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #4 [internal function]: RestEndpointFile->put('2')\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #5 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/RestServer.class.php(211): call_user_func_array(Array, Array)\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #6 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/www/rest.php(37): RestServer::process()\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException trace uid:56b321ba9ed9e] #7 {main}\n[2016-02-04 10:02:34] [rest:error] [user USERNAME] [FileIntegrityCheckFailedException details uid:56b321ba9ed9e] Expected size was 60365 but size on disk is\n</code></pre>\n\n*Filesystem*\n<pre><code>\n# ls -l /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/files/642b0dad-d326-96bf-d0cf-4d1285f652ef\n-rw-r--r-- 1 www-data www-data 60365 Feb  4 11:02 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/files/642b0dad-d326-96bf-d0cf-4d1285f652ef\n</code></pre>\n","2016-02-05T08:24:01.000+00:00","2016-02-10T13:01:54.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-100.5,0,0,28660,1,3.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-05T08:24:01.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139381953,1274,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Terasender fails on small files",3,"May be related to #1270.\n\nWhen the config looks like this:\n<pre><code>\n$config['terasender_enabled'] = true; // true/false\n$config['terasender_advanced'] =  true; // true/false - terasender advanced - show advanced settings\n$config['terasender_chunk_size'] = 5 * 1024 * 1024;        // default (5) terasender chunk size\n$config['terasender_worker_count'] = 30;        // default (6) worker count\n$config['terasender_start_mode'] = 'multiple'; // \"single\" to start all workers on the first file, \"multiple\" to dispatch them on all files\n</code></pre>\n\nUploads of small files fail. I tried with a file of 329 bytes. Trial and error showed me that uploading would succeed when using at most 20 workers, 21 and more fail.\nWhen uploading fails, the file appears green just as it should and the logs show that upload succeeded, just as it should, but the UI hangs there.\nRefreshing the page shows that uploading failed and offers to try again, with the same result.\n\nChanging the chunk size didn't seem to make any difference.\n\nLogs are included\n\n*Successful upload with 20 workers*\n<pre><code>\n[2016-02-05 11:39:57] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] File#6 (FILENAME, 329 bytes) added to Transfer#6\n[2016-02-05 11:39:57] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Recipient#6 (EMAIL) added to Transfer#6\n[2016-02-05 11:39:57] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Transfer#6 started\n[2016-02-05 11:39:57] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] File#6 chunk[0..329] written\n[2016-02-05 11:39:57] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Transfer#6 upload started\n[2016-02-05 11:39:57] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] File#6 fully uploaded, took 0s\n[2016-02-05 11:39:58] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Mail#transfer_available sent to Recipient#6\n[2016-02-05 11:39:58] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Transfer#6 made available, took 1s\n</code></pre>\n\n*Failed upload with 21 workers*\n<pre><code>\n[2016-02-05 11:40:22] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] File#7 (FILENAME, 329 bytes) added to Transfer#7\n[2016-02-05 11:40:22] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Recipient#7 (EMAIL) added to Transfer#7\n[2016-02-05 11:40:22] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Transfer#7 started\n[2016-02-05 11:40:22] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] File#7 chunk[0..329] written\n[2016-02-05 11:40:22] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] Transfer#7 upload started\n[2016-02-05 11:40:22] [rest:info] [user USERNAME] File#7 fully uploaded, took 0s\n</code></pre>\n","2016-02-05T11:59:22.000+00:00","2016-02-29T14:02:58.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-120.0999984741211,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-05T11:59:22.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139458383,1275,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug from prev. release: Empty/null $config['ban_extension'] prevents sending files with no extension",3,"Cloned from a known issue in versin 1.6, ticket #1137.  Need to verify this is no longer a bug in version 2.0.  If this is a bug in 2.0 it should be fixed.\n\nsetting $config['ban_extension'] to '' (= empty string) or null should allow all extensions, including 'no' extension. However the current code takes it too literally and will prevent the sending of files without extension. So the following files will be marked as 'invalid':\n\nempty-extension.\nno-extension\n\nAs noticed by MeRC on the AARNet Cloudstor install and reported by Wendy.","2016-02-06T06:26:14.000+00:00","2016-03-10T12:04:31.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-102.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-08T15:44:01.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139458763,1276,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug from previous release: check 2.11.7 (1.6) A session-bound token must be validated for each POST request",3,"Cloned from ticket #1080, check that ticket for comments and details.\n\nEtienne, I don't think this is an issue for version 2.0 as you rewrote all token handling.  But please check ticket #1080, check the comments and write your conclusions in this ticket.  Thanks!\n\nJan\n\n\"overall include of XSRF.php needs more investigation.  \n\nAdd XSFR.php to index.php\n\nChange [\"s-token\"] != to [\"s-token\"] !== as == matches type as well as value.\n\nCheck if POST is used in any context other than $_POST[\"myJson\"]\"\n\n","2016-02-06T07:24:10.000+00:00","2016-02-08T15:44:37.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-103.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-08T15:44:37.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139473363,1277,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Bug: problem uploading in private browser mode",3,"Observed with Safari \"private\" window.  Not verified with Chrome and Firefox incognito yet.  Symptom: when you start an upload (of 16 MB) the upload just does does not start.  Probably something with a session token that doesn't get set?\n\nEtienne, perhaps you already have an idea what this can be, otherwise we need to check this also occurs in other browsers.","2016-02-07T10:41:12.000+00:00","2016-02-07T10:41:12.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-104.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-07T10:41:12.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139473433,1278,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Add timezone to transfer audit log display",3,"This relates to ticket #983 that was a left-over from version 1.6.  Time information for downloads etc. is now implemented in 2.0, but timezone is not part of it.  Experience from dealing with logs in sysadmin and security incident handling indicates timezone is always important when dealing with (audit) logs so this should be added.\n\nEtienne, can you comment on the impact of including timezone information in the audit logs?  Is this a matter of simply adding something to the code which generates display information on screen in Myfiles and in emails or does it require more?\n\nI'd like to know how much effort this would take :)\n\nPlease look at the comments in the related ticket #983 for details of the discussion we had back then regarding timezone information.","2016-02-07T10:46:13.000+00:00","2016-05-12T09:00:38.000+00:00",9888983,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,7.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T09:00:38.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139473663,1279,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","implement auto-refresh after click on download from My Transfers table",3,"implement auto-refresh after click on download in MyTransfers.\n\nThis ticket is a clone from ticket #984, remaining work from version 1.6.  \n\nWhen a user downloads a file via the My Transfer table entry, the download counters do not get incremented until the page is refreshed.  In version 1.6 we did not have a reliable way to detect whether a download was complete or cancelled.  In 2.0 we can detect up to all but  the last chunk whether a download was successfull.\n\nWe create an event in the audit trail log for \"Recipient X finished downloading <file> (size)\" on when sending the last chunk of a download (Etienne, that is correct, right?).\n\nThat means we make an assumption in the audit log that afer the last download chuk is sent the file was downloaded.  We may as well refresh the my transfer page when that event occurs in the download case of downloading via my transfers.","2016-02-07T11:09:55.000+00:00","2016-02-07T11:09:55.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-106.0,0,0,28660,1,3.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-07T11:09:55.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139481503,1280,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Create standard configuration file template with sane defaults",3,"Activating most features.  Base on config-meijer currently present in config directory.","2016-02-07T21:00:43.000+00:00","2016-02-07T21:00:43.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-107.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-07T21:00:43.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [139481853,1281,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Error message required when HTML5/Terasender upload javascript can no longer read file",3,"Clone from ticket #999.  Need to check what happens when in current 2.0-alpha the file suddenly no longer can be read (for example because it was deleted by the user while uploading).\n\nFor details see related (original) ticket #999.\n\nRequired for both HTML5 and Tera Sender.\n\nScenario: start large file upload from USB disk, USB disk unplugges, HTML5 upload script can no longer read file, and upload hangs.\n\nWhat probably shoudl happen is that when the next chunk of file being uploaded can't be read, after a certain timeout a dialogue ought to pop up \"having trouble reading file, cancel upload yes/no?\" and maybe even include a \"should I try to resume\" question. At the very least the user needs to be made aware of the possibility to resume. Most people won't know this and especially for larger files it would be .... annoying. ","2016-02-07T21:36:12.000+00:00","2016-02-29T14:03:51.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-120.0999984741211,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-07T21:36:12.000+00:00",null]
