tickets, [139990773,1292,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Automation for handling of new language tags",3,"When a new language tag appears in the code, it'll need translation.  Need to decide on a workflow for this and on automation.  Probably should NOT push it out to all translators immediately, first need to validate the tag is correct and needed.  Can we do such a thing with POedit, push to limited number of languages depending on ticke tstatus?\n\n","2016-02-12T13:07:44.000+00:00","2016-02-15T07:29:50.000+00:00",1097603,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-9.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-15T07:29:50.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [140314603,1293,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Guest voucher allowed transfer options do not propagate when using voucher",2,"When creating a voucher you can specify which transfer options the guest user will have available, for example \"get link\".  The problem is they don't work when you then use the guest voucher.  Click on the voucher URL, enter the transfer upload page, and no transfer options are available.  ","2016-02-17T11:23:10.000+00:00","2016-02-17T11:23:10.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-112.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-17T11:23:10.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [140591883,1294,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Create poeditor.com account with role email address",3,"* create email list service-accounts@filesender.org.  Core team is owner + moderator. \n* create account with www.poeditor.com with role email address \"service-accounts@filesender.org\"\n* send password for poeditor.com role account to core team\n* invite core team in as contributors\n* document poeditor.com accountand service-acccounts@filesender.org list on filesender.org project infrastructure page","2016-02-20T16:01:49.000+00:00","2016-02-20T16:02:14.000+00:00",1097603,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-10.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-20T16:01:49.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [140633043,1295,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Large files stall on Internet Explorer 11",1,"Tested in both 1.6 and 2.0.\n\nWhen uploading a large file (50GB in our case) through Internet Explorer 11, the upload stalls somewhere halfway. We've received reports stating that they stop at 12%, in my own tests they've stopped at 48% in FileSender 2.0 and 78% in FileSender 1.6. The log files make no mention of anything amiss. I wasn't able to reproduce this with other browsers.\n\nTested with Internet Explorer 11 on Windows Server 2012R2, got reports about Internet Explorer 11 on Windows 7.","2016-02-22T07:58:56.000+00:00","2016-05-12T08:21:23.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-113.0,0,0,3316333,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:21:23.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [140747193,1296,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","avZvqm96Gr47ZdacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Investigate whole testing chain with Saucelabs for 1 feature and report",3,"We need to know what it would mean to use a \"test platform as a service\" like Sauce Labs.  Sauce Labs offers selenium based testing as a service.  For open source projects the service can be used for free.\n\nIf such a service could work for us it presumably gives us:\n- an opportunity to scale testing to many more browsers without incurring an increase in time use\n- an opportunity to let anyone run tests once tests have been defined.  This opens up for including running defined end user workflow tests in the development of new features /fixing of bugs: development is ready once the existing tests succeed\n\nhttps://saucelabs.com/resources\n\nCreate a test account at Sauce Labs, take one feature from FileSender 2.0, for example the \"drag and drop file selection\" feature, and try to create a Sauce Labs test for this.  From their feature list they should have PHP bindings, I would think it would be most convenient for the FileSender project to define its Selenium-server tests in PHP.  The Sauce Labs web site has plenty of documentation to get you started :)  Sauce Labs allows to import Selenium IDE scripts, which may be useful.  Would be convenient to know if there is an effort difference between importing IDE created scripts and writing tests in code.\n\nYou can test against https://terasender.uninett.no/branches/filesender-2.0/ until further notice.  Login using an OpenIdP account, self-registration should still be possible (OpenIdP is being phased out).\n\nWhat I'm after is a first impression of using Sauce Labs for practical testing.","2016-02-23T09:30:00.000+00:00","2016-02-23T10:00:32.000+00:00",1051963,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,avZvqm96Gr47ZdacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,503.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-23T09:30:00.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141015333,1297,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","«Stop»-button has unclear behaviour",3,"When I click the «Stop» button during an upload, I get the question if I want to abort my upload.\nWhen I answer «Yes», the question disappears again but otherwise it doesn't look like the action had any effect.\n\nThe button should abort the upload as fast as possible and redirect the user back to the upload page.","2016-02-25T13:19:43.000+00:00","2016-02-25T13:19:43.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-114.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-25T13:19:43.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141129023,1298,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Establish list of beta and release candidate sites",3,"our release policy states a release candidate will be field-tested on at least two FileSender release candidate test sites:\n- Production sites with at least X transfers by X unique users per day.\n- The sites run with well-known configurations making what are considered standard features available to their user bases.\n\nfor a release candidate to become a production release it needs to have been running production traffic with live users for at least two weeks on at least two release candidate test sites and shown no significant issues impairing service for the users, it can become the production (major) release.\n\nThis implies we need at least to FileSEnder release candidate sites.  A site would need to install a release candidate within a certain number of time after release, for example a week.  A release candidate site should typically get a heads up at least 2 weeks in advance before release.\n\nPreferably we would have a similar mechanism for beta testing sites so we get some organised feedback on the quality of a beta.  However, the release candidate sites are more important.\n","2016-02-26T14:00:42.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:00:42.000+00:00",9570103,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-1.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:00:42.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141131843,1299,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document feature suggestion -> implementation workflow",3,"Document the workflow for how we go from feature suggestion to feature release, including where we docuent the various steps.\n\nThe current process I envision after 2.0:\n\n- we have a list of feature suggestions somewhere\n- at some point in time we start working on a new release.  For example release 2.1.\n- release 2.1 will have a number of feature tickets under it.  \n- once we pick up on a suggestion we mark the suggestion as \"underway\" in the feature suggestion list and relate it to the relevant feature implementation ticket\n- in the feature suggestion list the feature is closed once the feature is implemented.\n\nA challenge at the moment is that we have a feature suggestion forum at uservoice and a list of suggested features in Assembla.  These should be consolidated at some point in time.  A challenge with this is that Uservoice has removed its free offer from its pricing structure.  At the moment we can still use it but I don't feel comfortable this'll last forever.  In any case it is not a desirable situation to be in.\n\nRemember to include \"language string freeze\" in the process to get from alpha to release (!)\n","2016-02-26T14:29:22.000+00:00","2016-02-26T18:19:50.000+00:00",9227153,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-6.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:29:22.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141133913,1300,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Ensure a guest invitation owner is notified of uploads by the guest",3,"Currently version 2.0 always sends an email to the guest invitation voucher owner when a guest uploaded a file.  The question is whether that is desired: it leads to email receipts the user can not switch off.  Personally I would be inclined to believe that if the guest invitation voucher simply receives a transfer audit log once a guest is done, it's equally good?","2016-02-26T14:48:41.000+00:00","2016-02-26T14:50:09.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-6.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T14:48:49.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141136253,1301,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Thorough analysis + documentation of TeraSender upload module in 2.0",3,"We keep running into problems with especially large uploads (100s of GB), using specific browsers (IE 11) or boundary conditions (25+ workers).  We need to:\n- document TeraSender functionality: implementation, design, flow\n- analyse whether this is good enough\n- change where needed\n\n","2016-02-26T15:13:05.000+00:00","2016-02-29T14:03:51.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-120.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,3.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T15:13:05.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141145893,1302,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload complete dialog should not auto-close",5,"When an upload complete, a dialog appears stating that the upload has completed. This is good. But it closes in 15 seconds, after which is redirects to the upload page again, which then shows no indication of that the previous upload succeeded.\n\nThis is annoying if you leave the computer while uploading completes, because you have to do extra work to check that the upload succeeded.\nEven more so if you checked the «Get a link instead of sending to recipients» checkbox, because then you must find the link in «My Transfers». ","2016-02-26T16:51:57.000+00:00","2016-04-04T13:24:21.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8,dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-121.0,0,0,238024,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-04-04T13:24:03.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141156993,1303,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Guest Voucher manual deletion interrupted if \"invalid or missing email\" warning triggered",3,"Copied from the version 1.6 known issue list.  This seems to still be a problem in version 2.0.\n\nOn the \"Guest Voucher\" page, if one starts to type a recipient email address and then clicks on the \"Delete\" button, the warning \"Invalid or missing email\" appears and the \"Delete\" button is highlighted, but the voucher does not delete (reported by Wendy). If one (without changing anything) then clicks on the \"Delete\" button again the confirmation dialog appears, then clicking \"Yes\" deletes the voucher and clears/reloads the page (noted by Xander).","2016-02-26T19:20:05.000+00:00","2016-02-26T19:20:05.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-122.0,0,0,133342,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T19:20:05.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141158093,1304,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Usability: When trying to click send, user is never warned the email is missing",3,"The user won't know why the send button isn't activated because there's no feedback to the user.  We need a slightly better way to let the user understand what (s)he needs to do.","2016-02-26T19:36:36.000+00:00","2016-02-26T19:36:36.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-123.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T19:36:36.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141159493,1305,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Hanging Flash uploads of large (free memory dependent) files on Mac",2,"Duplicate from versoin 1.5  See related ticket.\n\nWhen trying to upload files nearing the 2G limit (1900 to 2047 MB) it looks like Flash (?) runs out of memory. With FF the browser crashes, with Opera the progress popup appears but nothing happens (also no network activity). Also Cancel doesn't work and reloading the page will crash Opera also. Selecting a somewhat smaller file (in my case 1536 MB) results with both browsers in a period of disk read activity (and the spinning ball in FF) after which the upload actually starts. \n\nThis looks like Flash (?) tries to read the complete file into memory which may or may not be available. Can this be made less memory hungry? \n\nSeen on Mac OS 10.5.8 with Flash 10.3.183.5 and FF 3.6.19 and Opera 11.50. MacBook 5.1 with 4G RAM.","2016-02-26T19:59:42.000+00:00","2016-02-26T20:00:10.000+00:00",3026383,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","2016-02-26T19:59:42.000+00:00",0.0,0,-97.0,0,0,19299663,0,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-02-26T19:59:42.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141228483,1306,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document config directive for disclosure",3,"The config directive \"disclosure\" is not very well documented. I see that is an array and when it contains the string \"version\" the version number is printed in the footer, but a comprehensive list of valid values would be practical.","2016-02-29T08:42:56.000+00:00","2016-05-12T09:01:16.000+00:00",9569923,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-10.0,0,0,28660,1,1.0,1.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T09:01:16.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [141580443,1307,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload fails to complete on Firefox",1,"I tried uploading a large file (50GB) using Firefox, using TeraSender with 20 workers. When the upload completes, the file appears green but nothing else happens. After a while, an error message appears stating \"Transfer's files are not done uploading\", and a reference to an exception. The exception reads as follows:\n\n<pre>\nfilesender_2016-03-02_15h.log:[2016-03-02 15:59:21] [rest:error] [TransferFilesIncompleteException exception uid:56d70dd93ba42] transfer_files_incomplete\nfilesender_2016-03-02_15h.log:[2016-03-02 15:59:21] [rest:error] [TransferFilesIncompleteException trace uid:56d70dd93ba42] #0 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/endpoints/RestEndpointTransfer.class.php(568): Transfer->makeAvailable()\nfilesender_2016-03-02_15h.log:[2016-03-02 15:59:21] [rest:error] [TransferFilesIncompleteException trace uid:56d70dd93ba42] #1 [internal function]: RestEndpointTransfer->put('72')\nfilesender_2016-03-02_15h.log:[2016-03-02 15:59:21] [rest:error] [TransferFilesIncompleteException trace uid:56d70dd93ba42] #2 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/rest/RestServer.class.php(234): call_user_func_array(Array, Array)\nfilesender_2016-03-02_15h.log:[2016-03-02 15:59:21] [rest:error] [TransferFilesIncompleteException trace uid:56d70dd93ba42] #3 /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/www/rest.php(37): RestServer::process()\nfilesender_2016-03-02_15h.log:[2016-03-02 15:59:21] [rest:error] [TransferFilesIncompleteException trace uid:56d70dd93ba42] #4 {main}\nfilesender_2016-03-02_15h.log:[2016-03-02 15:59:21] [rest:error] [TransferFilesIncompleteException details uid:56d70dd93ba42] transfer = \"Transfer#72\"\n</pre>","2016-03-03T11:51:58.000+00:00","2017-05-15T21:01:00.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-126.0,0,1,3316333,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T08:21:08.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [142127393,1308,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Using `createtransfer.php` must check that it runs from the correct user.",3,"When I run <code>createtransfer.php</code> as my own user, I get a lot of the following error message:\n\n<pre>failed to open stream: Permission denied in /usr/local/filesender/filesender-2.0/classes/utils/Logger.class.php on line 353</pre>\n\nWhen I run it as root instead it works, but now I get this error when I try to run FileSender from the webbrowser. This happens because createtransfer.php may create a new logfile, and this new logfile will then be owned by the user that ran createtransfer.php.\n\nThe following things need to be taken care of:\n* If log files can't be written, the script should abort.\n* If log files can be written, they should either be chowned to the webserver, or made group-writeable.","2016-03-10T10:28:48.000+00:00","2016-03-10T10:28:48.000+00:00",6605143,null,"c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-126.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-03-10T10:28:48.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [144131953,1309,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Transfer option: redirect_url_on_upload_complete",3,"If this transfer option is set with a valid URL the user is redirected to this URL on transfer uploading completion rather than being presented with the \"upload complete\" dialogue.\n\nThis transfer option can not be set in the UI, it needs to be set with an API call.\n\nThe use case is using a separate FileSender service to upload big files to a digital exam system.\n* a student uses a digital exam to hand in an exam\n* the student wants to attach a file to the exam system by way of an external filesender service\n* on clicking the \"attach big file\" link the digital exam system creates a guest voucher for that particular student/exam session and redirects the user to the guest invitation URL.  In the guest invitation the transfer option \"redirect_url_on_upload_complete\" is set to the digital exam system\n* the user uploads the file, on upload complete the user is redirected back to the digital exam system\n* the digital exam system downloads the file to its own repository\n","2016-04-04T12:34:05.000+00:00","2016-04-04T13:09:05.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,c9JOC0LeOr5BTmacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-7.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-04-04T12:34:05.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [144134493,1310,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Transfer options in guest invitation",3,"When creating a guest invitation the authenticated user specifies which transfer options the guest's transfer will have.\n\n* the set of available transfer options the authenticated user can specify for a guest transfer is the same as for a transfer by an authenticated user (and defined by FileSender server configuration).  \n* by default a number of transfer options are set as per FileSender server configuration\n* When logged in as guest, you can see which transfer options are set but you can not change them.\n\n","2016-04-04T12:57:06.000+00:00","2016-04-04T12:57:06.000+00:00",9223393,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-8.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-04-04T12:57:06.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [144238173,1311,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document 3rd party modules for security considerations",3,"A number of 3rd party modules are used in FileSender.  These need to be documented to facilitate security audits and reviews and to document which external modules we need to track.  Note to self: we should find a way to track external modules in an automatic and systematic way.\n\nBackend e.g. dom pdf is used to generate audit trails in PDF format.  Front-end a number of JavaScript libraries are used, e.g. JQuery.\n\nThese 3rd party modules need to be listed on a separate page, with URLs to project,  to how we can see current version and how how we can track them.  We also should indicate which versions of these modules are included in a specific release.\n\n","2016-04-05T11:45:37.000+00:00","2016-04-05T11:45:37.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-2.0,0,1,133342,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-04-05T11:45:37.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [144320263,1312,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Apply consistent updated BSD license to all files in 2.0 source tree",3,"As per our LICENCE.txt.  RENATER should be included.\n\nCoordinate with Etienne.\n\n- nail license text to include\n- coordinate with Etienne\n- ask Etienne or Jørn to do actual update","2016-04-06T06:47:30.000+00:00","2016-04-06T06:48:17.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-127.0,0,1,133342,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-04-06T06:47:30.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [144474683,1313,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Upload UI: Total transfer size counter in file box does not update properly on file deletion",2,"With the upload form: When deleting a file from the file selection in the file box the total transfer size counter is reset to 0 even if there still are files in the file box.","2016-04-07T14:09:46.000+00:00","2016-04-07T14:10:12.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-128.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-04-07T14:09:46.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [147737073,1314,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Fix average upload speed counter to work properly after upload resume",3,"Issue: avg. upload speed counter goes berzerk after an upload restart.\n\nSolution: We keep track of the time upload is started or restarted (reset at restart), for each file: got global size and uploaded size. In order to know how fast we go, we take total time it took and do a division. At one point we reset one counter and not the other. Need to know “this transfer is restarting”, need to get sum of offsets, and substract it from speed computation.\n","2016-05-12T07:52:30.000+00:00","2016-05-12T07:52:30.000+00:00",6605143,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ,dgRDGuZ4ar478MacwqEsg8",null,0.0,0,-129.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-05-12T07:52:30.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [150459843,1315,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ","b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document $config['stalling_detection'] ",3,"file_sender > 3954\n\nAuthored by etiennemeleard\nParent: 3953\n2016-06-07 09:47\nAllow to configure client stalling detection.\n\nRelated config parameter is \"stalling_detection\", it may be :\n\n- A true boolean to enable detection with default behaviour :\n$config['stalling_detection'] = true;\n\n- An array including any of the following values (all optional) :\ncount_divergence : the maximum chunk count a worker can be late over the global average (last 5 chunks of every worker)\nduration_divergence : the maximum ratio between a process's current upload time and the global average (last 5 chunks of every worker)\nautomatic_retries : the number of times the upload is resumed transparently before asking the user if he/she wants to keep going\n\nFull version is (those are also the default values) :\n\n$config['stalling_detection'] = array(\n'count_divergence' => 10,\n'duration_divergence' => 7,\n'automatic_retries' => 3\n);\n\n- A false boolean to turn off detection :\n$config['stalling_detection'] = false;\n","2016-06-10T06:24:01.000+00:00","2016-06-10T06:24:01.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-14.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-06-10T06:24:01.000+00:00",null]
tickets, [151129473,1316,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,"b516sOlY8r3PPQeJe5afGb","Document known issue / FAQ regarding upload of compound file formats on Mac",3,"Apple applications (Ortelius, but also Mac Write I believe) uses a compound file format that stores stuff in a directory structure. As long as we can not transfer folders, transferring these types of files is not supported. Workaround: zip them.\n\nfilesender-nren-services-in-europe.ortl:\ntotal 920\ndrwxr-xr-x@  6 meijer  staff     204 Jun 20 14:15 .\ndrwx------  65 meijer  staff    2210 Jun 20 14:25 ..\n-rw-r--r--   1 meijer  staff   17003 Jun 20 14:03 MD_Auxiliary_Info.dat\n-rw-r--r--   1 meijer  staff  444351 Jun 20 14:03 MD_Content.drawing\n-rw-r--r--   1 meijer  staff    1078 Jun 20 14:03 MD_Info.plist\ndrwxr-xr-x   3 meijer  staff     102 Jun 20 14:03 QuickLook\n\nI wonder: if we could read through a folder, could we stream-zip it?","2016-06-20T12:35:20.000+00:00","2016-06-20T12:35:20.000+00:00",9569923,null,"dPS9kyuyur3zYrab7jnrAJ",null,0.0,0,-15.0,0,1,28660,1,0.0,0.0,0.0,0.0,"2016-06-20T12:35:20.000+00:00",null]
